Kotretsos in 2015 was a recipient of the NEON grant for her solo entitled OPEN ARTISTS STUDIO FOUNDATION at C9 MaximiliansForum in Munich, Germany. In 2014 she was nominated for the Future Generation Art Prize and the Follow Fluxus Residency &amp; Grant. In 2014 and 2015 she presented the lecture/performed entitled Socially engaged? Better, socially married! at the FIELD MEETING at the Asian Contemporary Art Week in New York; at the MediaImpact: International Festival of Activist Art in Moscow; at the FIELD MEETING Take 2: An Afterthought, collateral event 56th Venice Biennale, and at Diasporas in Thessaloniki, Greece. Her work has been presented at: Onassis Art Center, NY; the Asian Society, NY; the 4th Thessaloniki Biennale of Contemporary Art; the Tinguely Museum, Basel, La Kunsthalle Mulhouse; the Macedonian Museum of Contemporary Art, Thessaloniki, and at the Contemporary Art Museum St. Louis among other institutions in Greece and abroad. Her own work was found to concur with her action to co-found the five-year art project Boots Contemporary Art Space in St. Louis, MO - a contemporary art laboratory (2006-10). In addition, she founded and edited BootPrint (2006-10), a biannual journal made by and for artists. Between 2009-13 she was the columnist of the Inside the Artist&rsquo;s Studio for the PBS Arts Feature, Art21 Magazine. In 2014 her column was published on LABKULTUR.TV in Germany. Currently, she is working on Phase #2 of the collaborative project entitled Socially engaged? Better, socially married!, on SIRENSWAVE &ndash; an art project taking place online in collaboration with Kutloano Skosana Ricci, on KLIMA &ndash; research, a new body of work and a volume in the making with Carolina Trigo and on the collaborative project entitled IMAGINARY REPUBLIC with Brandon LaBelle, Helene Frichot, Lise Skou and Diego Rotman.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(72, 36, 'al', '<p>Georgia Kotretsos, nj&euml; artiste, studiuese, shkrimtare, aktiviste dhe drejtuese institucioni mish&euml;ron nj&euml; shembull t&euml; artistit bashk&euml;kohor multifunksional, duke kaluar nga nj&euml; rol dhe angazhim n&euml; tjetrin dhe n&euml; t&euml; nj&euml;jt&euml;n koh&euml; duke ruajtur kufinj t&euml; qart&euml; mes tyre. N&euml; bashk&euml;punim me Tirana Art Lab, Kotretsos krijoi tre tabela, t&euml; cilat u vendos&euml;n n&euml; bulevardin kryesor t&euml; Tiran&euml;s si pjes&euml; e performanc&euml;s nd&euml;rhyr&euml;se n&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml;n publike. Regjimet totalitare fashiste dhe socialiste, por mbi t&euml; gjitha ato neoliberale, e kan&euml; p&euml;rdorur vazhdimisht k&euml;t&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml; ​​t&euml; privilegjuar dhe t&euml; ngarkuar semiotike p&euml;r t&euml; shpalosur &ldquo;teatrin&rdquo; e vet&euml;promovimit p&euml;rmes artit. Tre tabelat nd&euml;rhyjn&euml; n&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml; metaforike n&euml; peizazhin e Bulevardit duke v&euml;n&euml; n&euml; pik&euml;pyetje raportin mes artit dhe politik&euml;s n&euml; regjime t&euml; ndryshme politike.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Puna u prodhua p&euml;r ekspozit&euml;n &ldquo;Triple Feature&rdquo; t&euml; orgaizuar nga&nbsp;Tirana Art Lab, pjes&euml; e projektit t&euml; bashk&euml;punimit &ldquo;Heroes We Love&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Georgia Kotretsos e lindur m&euml; 1978 n&euml; Selanik, Greqi &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; artiste pamore dhe studiuese me baz&euml; n&euml; Athin&euml;, Greqi. Ajo u transferua n&euml; Afrik&euml;n e Jugut n&euml; adoleshenc&euml;n e saj t&euml; hershme, nd&euml;rsa zhb&euml;rja e aparteidit ishte duke u zhvilluar. Kotretsos ka nj&euml; diplom&euml; MFA nga Shkolla e Institutit t&euml; Artit n&euml; Chicago p&euml;r nj&euml; burs&euml; me merit&euml; t&euml; plot&euml; n&euml; 2004 n&euml; Shtetet e Bashkuara dhe nj&euml; diplom&euml; BFA nga Instituti i Teknologjis&euml; Durban, n&euml; KwaZulu Natal, n&euml; 2000 n&euml; Afrik&euml;n e Jugut. Kotretsos n&euml; 2015 ishte fituese e &ccedil;mimit NEON p&euml;r ekspozit&euml;n e saj personal t&euml; titulluar OPEN ARTISTS STUDIO FOUNDATION n&euml; C9 MaximiliansForum n&euml; Mynih, Gjermani. N&euml; vitin 2014, ajo u nominua p&euml;r &ccedil;mimin Future Generation Art Prize dhe Follow Fluxus Residency &amp; Grant. N&euml; vitin 2014 dhe 2015 ajo prezantoi ligj&euml;rat&euml;n/performanc&euml;n me titull Socially engaged? Better, socially married! n&euml; FIELD MEETING n&euml; Jav&euml;n e Artit Bashk&euml;kohor Aziatik n&euml; New York; n&euml; MediaImpact: Festivali Nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar i Artit Aktivist n&euml; Mosk&euml;; n&euml; FIELD MEETING Take 2: An Afterthought, ngjarje kolaterale e 56-t&euml; Bienales s&euml; Venecias dhe n&euml; Diasporat n&euml; Selanik, Greqi. Puna e saj &euml;sht&euml; prezantuar n&euml;: Onassis Art Center, NY; Shoq&euml;ria Aziatike, NY; Bienalen e 4-t&euml; t&euml; Artit Bashk&euml;kohor t&euml; Selanikut; Muzeu Tinguely, Bazel, La Kunsthalle Mulhouse; Muzeu Maqedonas i Artit Bashk&euml;kohor, Selanik, dhe n&euml; Muzeun e Artit Bashk&euml;kohor St. Louis. Vet&euml; puna e saj u pa se p&euml;rputhej me veprimin e saj p&euml;r t&euml; bashk&euml;themeluar projektin pes&euml;-vje&ccedil;ar t&euml; artit Boots Contemporary Art Space n&euml; St. Louis, MO - nj&euml; laborator arti bashk&euml;kohor (2006-10). P&euml;rve&ccedil; k&euml;saj, ajo themeloi dhe redaktoi BootPrint (2006-10), nj&euml; revist&euml; dyvje&ccedil;are e b&euml;r&euml; nga dhe p&euml;r artist&euml;. Midis 2009-13 ajo ishte kolumniste e Inside the Artist&#39;s Studio p&euml;r PBS Arts Feature, Revista Art21. N&euml; vitin 2014 rubrika e saj u publikua n&euml; LABKULTUR.TV n&euml; Gjermani. Aktualisht ajo &euml;sht&euml; duke punuar n&euml; Phase#2 t&euml; projektit bashk&euml;punues me titull Socially engaged? Better, socially married!, n&euml; SIRENSWAVE &ndash; nj&euml; projekt arti q&euml; zhvillohet online n&euml; bashk&euml;punim me Kutloano Skosana Ricci, n&euml; KLIMA &ndash; nj&euml; hulumtim, nj&euml; pjes&euml; e re e pun&euml;s dhe nj&euml; v&euml;llim n&euml; p&euml;rgatitje me Carolina Trigo dhe n&euml; projektin bashk&euml;punues t&euml; titulluar IMAGINARY REPUBLIC me Brandon LaBelle, Helene Frichot, Lise Skou dhe Diego Rotman.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(73, 37, 'en', '<p>This performance happened in front of the Prime Minister Building in Tirana, at the time where a new initiative, C.O.D (Center for Openness and Dialogue) was born and was housed inside the same building built by the fascist architect Gherardio Bosio during the fascist occupation of Albania in the late &lsquo;30s. C.O.D was founded by Prime Minister Edi Rama&rsquo;s initiative as a center that would produce debate on art and politics. According to the artist, the COD produced no debate, much less &lsquo;openness&rsquo; in the service of a critical society. The performance, which comes as a response to such a situation, consists in 4 people showing at the entrance of the building a big, vertical slogan with the writing &ldquo;Feshizem&rdquo; printed on it, black on white. &ldquo;Feshizem&rdquo; is an invented word by Zaloshnja from the melting of two words/concepts: fashion and fascism. The artist justifies this conjunction by taking in consideration the thought of Walter Benjamin of the aestheticization of politics (fascism) in the place of the politicization of aesthetics (communism). According to Zaloshnja, Prime Minister Edi Rama is now offering to the country a &ldquo;total design&rdquo; of neoliberal marketing, using&mdash;on the one hand&mdash;&ldquo;aesthetics&rdquo; as a kind of Trojan Horse and&mdash;on the other hand, &mdash;50/50 public-private partnership &ldquo;concessions,&rdquo; in order to allow reforms that will uproot every possible public asset through privatization. (Ergin Zaloshnja)</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\nErgin Zaloshnja&nbsp;born in 1979 in&nbsp;Tirana, Albania is a visual artist and activist who currently lives and works in Tirana, Albania. He studied at the Academy of Fine Arts in Florence graduating in 2012. Besides his primary media - photography, installation, and video - he has developed a series of street art interventions under the pseudonym Diver Santi. He is also the founder of the political and subculture fanzine Sputnik and a collaborator of D.C.C.A, Debatik Center of Contemporary Art, Tirana. Zaloshnja is also an art educator on the subculture of street art: in 2017 he was one of the workshop leaders during the International Documentary and Short Film Festival held in Prizren, Kosova for MARUBI x DOKUPHOTO, a collaboration program between DokuFest and the Marubi National Museum of Photography in Shkoder. Apart from his solo exhibition DE-LUDII, Miza Gallery, Tirana and personal outdoors intervention Weed Nation - Gallery On The Move, Tirana , he has mainly participated in group exhibitions and collaborative projects, among which the most notable are: Videos aus Albanien, Blickle Kino - Belvedere Museum, Vienna ; shitet toka - Aktuelle Anmerkungen zu Albanien, HDA &ndash; Haus der Architektur, Graz ; Double Feature #8, Tirana Art Lab, Tirana ; Stranger than Kindness, 22nd International Onufri Prize, National Art Gallery, Tirana; Teatri i Gjelb&euml;rimit - Department of Eagles, FAB Gallery, Tirana ;&nbsp;Tirana Open1-Project Ultra - SPUTNIK production, Tirana,&nbsp;Let Us Start From The Middle, Tirana Art Lab, Tirana; Praise of Doubt, 20th International Onufri Prize, National Art Gallery, Tirana;&nbsp;Nj&euml;qind vjet vet&euml;var&euml;si, Tirana Art Lab; Tools For Revolution Or Just For Sale - ROTTE METROPOLITANE. Firenze &egrave; sommersa, Villa Romana, Florence ;&nbsp;Our Nature,&nbsp;Villa Serena, Bologna; Contested Space, Spazio Alcatraz, Stazione Leopolda, Florence; U-Topos, 2nd Tirana Biennale,&nbsp;Debatik Center of Contemporary Art, Tirana ; Networking City: La citt&agrave; della gente, Ex Macelli, Prato; The Promised Land, O&#39; Artoteca, Milan; Networking, Palazzo delle Papesse, Siena; Networking, Ex Macelli, Prato.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(74, 37, 'al', '<p>Kjo performanc&euml; ndodhi p&euml;rpara godin&euml;s s&euml; Kryeministris&euml; n&euml; Tiran&euml;, gjat&euml; periudh&euml;s s&euml; hapjes s&euml; COD (Qendra p&euml;r Hapje dhe Dialog). Kjo qend&euml;r ndodhet pik&euml;risht brenda t&euml; nj&euml;jt&euml;s godin&euml; projektuar nga arkitekti fashist Gherardo Bosio, gjat&euml; periudh&euml;s s&euml; pushtimit fashist n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri n&euml; fund t&euml; viteve &#39;30. C.O.D u themelua me nism&euml;n e kryeministrit Edi Rama si nj&euml; qend&euml;r q&euml; do t&euml; prodhonte debat mbi artin dhe politik&euml;n. Sipas Zaloshnj&euml;s, COD nuk prodhoi debat, e aq m&euml; pak &lsquo;hapje&rsquo; n&euml; sh&euml;rbim t&euml; shoq&euml;ris&euml; kritike. Performanca, e cila vjen si kund&euml;rp&euml;rgjigje ndaj nj&euml; situate t&euml; till&euml;, konsiston n&euml; 4 persona q&euml; shfaqin n&euml; hyrje t&euml; godin&euml;s nj&euml; slogan t&euml; madh horizontal me shkrimin &ldquo;Feshiz&euml;m&rdquo; mbi t&euml;, t&euml; zez&euml; mbi t&euml; bardh&euml;. &ldquo;Feshiz&euml;m&rdquo; &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; fjal&euml; e krijuar nga artisti fal&euml; shkrirjes s&euml; dy fjal&euml;ve/koncepteve: fashion dhe fashiz&euml;m. Artisti e justifikon k&euml;t&euml; lidhje duke marr&euml; n&euml; konsiderat&euml; mendimin e Walter Benjaminit p&euml;r estetizimin e politik&euml;s (fashizmit) n&euml; vend t&euml; politizimit t&euml; estetik&euml;s (komunizmit). Sipas Zaloshnj&euml;s, kryeministri Edi Rama tani po i ofron vendit nj&euml; &ldquo;dizajn total&rdquo; t&euml; marketingut neoliberal, duke p&euml;rdorur, nga nj&euml;ra an&euml;, &ldquo;estetik&euml;n&rdquo; si nj&euml; lloj kali Trojan dhe, nga ana tjet&euml;r 50/50 &ldquo;koncesionet&rdquo; e partneritetit publik-privat, p&euml;r t&euml; lejuar reforma q&euml; do t&euml; &ccedil;rr&euml;njosin &ccedil;do aset t&euml; mundsh&euml;m publik n&euml;p&euml;rmjet privatizimit. (Ergin Zaloshnja)</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">​​Ergin Zaloshnja i lindur m&euml; 1979 n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; artist dhe aktivist pamor i cili aktualisht jeton dhe punon n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. Ai studioi n&euml; Akademin&euml; e Arteve t&euml; Bukura n&euml; Firence duke u diplomuar n&euml; vitin 2012. P&euml;rve&ccedil; medias s&euml; tij kryesore - fotografis&euml;, instalacionit dhe video - ai ka zhvilluar nj&euml; s&euml;r&euml; nd&euml;rhyrjesh n&euml; artin e rrug&euml;s me pseudonimin Diver Santi. Ai &euml;sht&euml; gjithashtu themeluesi i fanzin&euml;s politike dhe subkulturore Sputnik dhe bashk&euml;pun&euml;tor i Debatik Q&euml;ndra e Artit Bashk&euml;kohor. Zaloshnja &euml;sht&euml; gjithashtu nj&euml; edukator arti n&euml; n&euml;nkultur&euml;n e artit t&euml; rrug&euml;s: n&euml; vitin 2017 ai ishte nj&euml; nga udh&euml;heq&euml;sit e seminareve gjat&euml; Festivalit Nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar t&euml; Filmit Dokumentar dhe t&euml; Shkurt&euml;r t&euml; mbajtur n&euml; Prizren, Kosov&euml; p&euml;r MARUBI x DOKUPHOTO, nj&euml; program bashk&euml;punimi midis DokuFest dhe Muzeut Komb&euml;tar i Fotografis&euml; Marubi n&euml; Shkod&euml;r. P&euml;rve&ccedil; ekspozit&euml;s s&euml; tij vetjake DE-LUDII, Galeria Miza, Tiran&euml; dhe nd&euml;rhyrjes personale n&euml; natyr&euml; Weed Nation - Galeria On The Move, Tiran&euml;, ai ka marr&euml; pjes&euml; kryesisht n&euml; ekspozita grupore dhe projekte bashk&euml;punuese, nd&euml;r t&euml; cilat m&euml; t&euml; dalluarat jan&euml;: Videos aus Albanien, Blickle Cinema - Belvedere Museum, Vienna; for sale land - Current services for Albania, HDA - House of Architecture, Graz; Double Feature # 8, Tirana Art Lab, Tiran&euml;; Stranger than Kindness, &Ccedil;mimi i 22-t&euml; Nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar Onufri, Galeria Komb&euml;tare e Arteve, Tiran&euml;; Teatri i Gjelb&euml;rimit - Departments of Eagles, Galeria FAB, Tiran&euml;; Tirana Open1-Project Ultra - prodhim SPUTNIK, Tiran&euml;, Let us start from the middle, Tirana Art Lab, Tiran&euml;; Praise of Doubt, &Ccedil;mimi i 20-t&euml; Nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar Onufri, Galeria Komb&euml;tare e Arteve, Tiran&euml;; Nj&euml;qind vjet vet&euml;var&euml;si, Tirana Art Lab; Tools For Revolution Or Just For Sale - ROTTE METROPOLITANE. Florence&#39;s sommersa, Villa Romana, Florence; Our Nature, Villa Serena, Bologna; Contested Space, Spazio Alcatraz, Stazione Leopolda, Firence; U-Topos, 2nd Tirana Biennale, Debatik Center of Contemporary Art, Tirana; Networking City: La citt&agrave; della gente, Ex Macelli, Prato; The Promised Land, O &#39;Artoteca, Milano; Networking, Palazzo delle Papesse, Siena; Networking, Ex Macelli, Prato.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(75, 38, 'en', '<p>&ldquo;Sputnik&rdquo; is a periodical publication (2013 - ongoing)&nbsp;that gets its inspiration in current developments of Albanian society with a dystopian twist. One of the only examples of methodical street art in Albania, the platform treats current social issues through a strong visual approach and gets posted around the city of Tirana. Not a comic as such, Sputnik is the front cover of an imaginary magazine - each cover depicting a social issue or situation inspired by real happenings in Albania. Using black humor and dystopian imagery, they created a tongue-in-cheek visual scenario that is designed to provoke thought and discussion. These images are then posted in various high-visibility locations around the city, with a new &ldquo;edition&rdquo; coming out periodically. Their aim is to highlight corruption and social issues and most importantly to bring it to the people and on the street. The idea of Sputnik is also to see how &ldquo;free&rdquo; Albania is and whether it can be allowed to publish such things, without any repercussions.<br />\r\nSputnik was founded by Ergin Zaloshnja in 2013. In collaboration with Pleurad Xhafa, Sokol Peci and Elian Stefa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\nErgin Zaloshnja&nbsp;born 1979 in&nbsp;Tirana, Albania is a visual artist and activist who currently lives and works in Tirana, Albania. He studied at the Academy of Fine Arts in Florence graduating in 2012. Besides his primary media - photography, installation and video - he has developed a series of street art interventions under the pseudonym Diver Santi. He is also the founder of the political and subculture fanzine Sputnik and a collaborator of D.C.C.A, Debatik Center of Contemporary Art, Tirana. Zaloshnja is also an art educator on the subculture of street art: in 2017 he was one of the workshop leaders during the International Documentary and Short Film Festival held in Prizren, Kosova for MARUBI x DOKUPHOTO, a collaboration program between DokuFest and the Marubi National Museum of Photography in Shkoder. Apart from his solo exhibition DE-LUDII, Miza Gallery, Tirana, and personal outdoors intervention Weed Nation - Gallery On The Move, Tirana, he has mainly participated in group exhibitions and collaborative projects, among which the most notable are: Videos aus Albanien, Blickle Kino - Belvedere Museum, Vienna ; shitet toka - Aktuelle Anmerkungen zu Albanien, HDA &ndash; Haus der Architektur, Graz ; Double Feature #8, Tirana Art Lab, Tirana; Stranger than Kindness, 22nd International Onufri Prize, National Art Gallery, Tirana; Teatri i Gjelb&euml;rimit - Department of Eagles, FAB Gallery, Tirana;&nbsp;Tirana Open1-Project Ultra - SPUTNIK production, Tirana,&nbsp;Let Us Start From The Middle, Tirana Art Lab, Tirana; Praise of Doubt, 20th International Onufri Prize, National Art Gallery, Tirana;&nbsp;Nj&euml;qind vjet vet&euml;var&euml;si, Tirana Art Lab; Tools For Revolution Or Just For Sale - ROTTE METROPOLITANE. Firenze &egrave; sommersa, Villa Romana, Florence ;&nbsp;Our Nature,&nbsp;Villa Serena, Bologna; Contested Space, Spazio Alcatraz, Stazione Leopolda, Florence; U-Topos, 2nd Tirana Biennale,&nbsp;Debatik Center of Contemporary Art, Tirana ; Networking City: La citt&agrave; della gente, Ex Macelli, Prato; The Promised Land, O&#39; Artoteca, Milan; Networking, Palazzo delle Papesse, Siena; Networking, Ex Macelli, Prato.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(76, 38, 'al', '<p>&ldquo;Sputnik&rdquo; &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; botim periodik (2013 - n&euml; vazhdim) i cili frym&euml;zohet nga zhvillimet aktuale t&euml; shoq&euml;ris&euml; shqiptare duke i dhene atyre nj&euml; fryme distopike. Kjo platforme &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; nga shembujt e vet&euml;m t&euml; artit metodik t&euml; rrug&euml;s n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri dhe trajton &ccedil;&euml;shtjet aktuale sociale n&euml;p&euml;rmjet nj&euml; qasjeje t&euml; fort&euml; vizuale duke u postuar vijimisht n&euml;p&euml;r t&euml; gjith&euml; qytetin e Tiran&euml;s. Sputnik &euml;sht&euml; kopertina e nj&euml; reviste imagjinare - &ccedil;do kopertin&euml; p&euml;rshkruan nj&euml; &ccedil;&euml;shtje ose situat&euml; sociale t&euml; frym&euml;zuar nga ngjarje reale n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri. Duke p&euml;rdorur humor t&euml; zi dhe imazhe distopike, Sputnik krijon nj&euml; skenar vizual i cili synon t&euml; provokoj&euml; reflektim dhe diskutim. K&euml;to imazhe postohen m&euml; pas n&euml; vende t&euml; ndryshme t&euml; cilat kan&euml; shikueshm&euml;ri t&euml; lart&euml; n&euml;p&euml;r qytet, sa her&euml; del nj&euml; &quot;edicion&quot; i ri. Synimi i tyre &euml;sht&euml; t&euml; nxjerrin n&euml; pah korrupsionin dhe problemet sociale dhe m&euml; e r&euml;nd&euml;sishmja &euml;sht&euml; ti sjellin ato tek njer&euml;zit, n&euml; rrug&euml;. Ideja e Sputnik-ut &euml;sht&euml; gjithashtu t&euml; shoh&euml; se sa &ldquo;e lir&euml;&rdquo; &euml;sht&euml; Shqip&euml;ria dhe n&euml;se mund t&euml; lejohet nje aktivitet i tille, pa patur asnj&euml; pasoj&euml;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sputnik u themelua nga Ergin Zaloshnja n&euml; vitin 2013. N&euml; bashk&euml;punim me Pleurad Xhafa, Sokol Peci dhe Elian Stefa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">​​Ergin Zaloshnja i lindur m&euml; 1979 n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; artist dhe aktivist pamor i cili aktualisht jeton dhe punon n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. Ai studioi n&euml; Akademin&euml; e Arteve t&euml; Bukura n&euml; Firence duke u diplomuar n&euml; vitin 2012. P&euml;rve&ccedil; medias s&euml; tij kryesore - fotografis&euml;, instalacionit dhe video - ai ka zhvilluar nj&euml; s&euml;r&euml; nd&euml;rhyrjesh n&euml; artin e rrug&euml;s me pseudonimin Diver Santi. Ai &euml;sht&euml; gjithashtu themeluesi i fanzin&euml;s politike dhe subkulturore Sputnik dhe bashk&euml;pun&euml;tor i Debatik Q&euml;ndra e Artit Bashk&euml;kohor. Zaloshnja &euml;sht&euml; gjithashtu nj&euml; edukator arti n&euml; n&euml;nkultur&euml;n e artit t&euml; rrug&euml;s: n&euml; vitin 2017 ai ishte nj&euml; nga udh&euml;heq&euml;sit e seminareve gjat&euml; Festivalit Nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar t&euml; Filmit Dokumentar dhe t&euml; Shkurt&euml;r t&euml; mbajtur n&euml; Prizren, Kosov&euml; p&euml;r MARUBI x DOKUPHOTO, nj&euml; program bashk&euml;punimi midis DokuFest dhe Muzeut Komb&euml;tar i Fotografis&euml; Marubi n&euml; Shkod&euml;r. P&euml;rve&ccedil; ekspozit&euml;s s&euml; tij vetjake DE-LUDII, Galeria Miza, Tiran&euml; dhe nd&euml;rhyrjes personale n&euml; natyr&euml; Weed Nation - Galeria On The Move, Tiran&euml;, ai ka marr&euml; pjes&euml; kryesisht n&euml; ekspozita grupore dhe projekte bashk&euml;punuese, nd&euml;r t&euml; cilat m&euml; t&euml; dalluarat jan&euml;: Videos aus Albanien, Blickle Cinema - Belvedere Museum, Vienna; for sale land - Current services for Albania, HDA - House of Architecture, Graz; Double Feature # 8, Tirana Art Lab, Tiran&euml;; Stranger than Kindness, &Ccedil;mimi i 22-t&euml; Nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar Onufri, Galeria Komb&euml;tare e Arteve, Tiran&euml;; Teatri i Gjelb&euml;rimit - Departments of Eagles, Galeria FAB, Tiran&euml;; Tirana Open1-Project Ultra - prodhim SPUTNIK, Tiran&euml;, Let us start from the middle, Tirana Art Lab, Tiran&euml;; Praise of Doubt, &Ccedil;mimi i 20-t&euml; Nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar Onufri, Galeria Komb&euml;tare e Arteve, Tiran&euml;; Nj&euml;qind vjet vet&euml;var&euml;si, Tirana Art Lab; Tools For Revolution Or Just For Sale - ROTTE METROPOLITANE. Florence&#39;s sommersa, Villa Romana, Florence; Our Nature, Villa Serena, Bologna; Contested Space, Spazio Alcatraz, Stazione Leopolda, Firence; U-Topos, 2nd Tirana Biennale, Debatik Center of Contemporary Art, Tirana; Networking City: La citt&agrave; della gente, Ex Macelli, Prato; The Promised Land, O &#39;Artoteca, Milano; Networking, Palazzo delle Papesse, Siena; Networking, Ex Macelli, Prato.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(77, 39, 'en', '<p>In the&nbsp;evocative and poetic installation &quot;The Nest&quot;, Kazanxhiu recreates five gigantic swallow&rsquo;s nests and installs them at the entrance of the National Historic Museum in Skanderbeg Square, Tirana&rsquo;s center. The swallow&rsquo;s nest can be found easily around buildings in Albania and it is usually accepted as part of them, creating a sense of acceptance and community. Kazanxhiu uses the nest also as a symbol of freedom, making a reference to the saying &ldquo;free as a bird&rdquo;; yet, also birds still have a home to return to. This situation echoes again with the conflicting condition of the Roma community research for a land, a home. Choosing to install the nests in front of the National Historic Museum, Kazanxhiu uses them also as a call for the institutionalization of Romani history, art, and culture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Sead Kazanxhiu born in 1987 in Fier, Albania, lives and works in Tirana, Albania. He was trained as a painter at the University of Arts in Tirana from 2006 to 2010, where he obtained his Bachelor Degree. Following his studies, he continued to work primarily in the medium of painting, whereas his more recent practice has expanded into sculpture, installation, video, and public space interventions. With nine personal shows since 2012 in Tirana, Budapest, and Brussels, and numerous group exhibitions in Tirana, Prague, Brno, Gothenburg, Berlin, Drezden, Motovun, Krakow, Bucharest, and New Orleans, Sarawak Malaysia, Kazanxhiu remains one of the most engaged younger protagonists in contemporary Albanian cultural scene. His uncompromising position with regard to unfair treatment of the Roma ethnic group presents but a platform to voice individual dissent about the racially biased dynamics that, unfortunately, continues to shape contemporary European worldviews &ndash; on a daily basis, inside and outside of official political arenas. In this sense, his image-making contributes to the positive efforts of a single artist to restore the dignity of a community forcefully and unjustly cornered at the outskirts of European democracy. Currently, he is a PAKIV board member of the European Roma Institute for Art and Culture and a Deputy Chairman of the State Committee for National Minorities in Albania.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(78, 39, 'al', '<p>N&euml;&nbsp;instalacionin emocionues dhe poetik &quot;Foleja&quot;,&nbsp;Kazanxhiu rikrijon pes&euml; fole gjigande dall&euml;ndysheje dhe i vendos ato n&euml; hyrje t&euml; Muzeut Historik Komb&euml;tar n&euml; sheshin Sk&euml;nderbej, n&euml; qend&euml;r&nbsp;t&euml;&nbsp;Tiran&euml;s. Foleja e dall&euml;ndyshes mund t&euml; gjendet leht&euml;sisht n&euml;p&euml;r nd&euml;rtesa n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri dhe zakonisht ajo pranohet si pjes&euml; e tyre nga banor&euml;t, duke krijuar k&euml;shtu nj&euml; ndjesi pranimi dhe komuniteti. Kazanxhiu e p&euml;rdor folen&euml; edhe si nj&euml; simbol lirie, duke iu referuar th&euml;nies &ldquo;i lir&euml; si zog&rdquo;; megjithat&euml;, edhe zogjt&euml; kan&euml; nj&euml; sht&euml;pi ku mund t&euml; kthehen. Kjo situat&euml; i b&euml;n s&euml;risht jehon&euml; gjendjes konfliktuale t&euml; k&euml;rkimit t&euml; komunitetit rom p&euml;r nj&euml; tok&euml;, nj&euml; sht&euml;pi. Duke zgjedhur t&euml; vendos&euml; folet&euml; n&euml; hyrje t&euml; Muzeut Historik Komb&euml;tar, Kazanxhiu i p&euml;rdor ato edhe si nje thirrje p&euml;r institucionalizimin e historis&euml;, artit dhe kultur&euml;s rome.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Sead Kazanxhiu i &nbsp;lindur m&euml; 1987 n&euml; Fier, Shqip&euml;ri, jeton dhe punon n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri.&nbsp;Ka studiur piktur&euml; n&euml; Universitetin e Arteve n&euml; Tiran&euml; nga viti 2006 deri n&euml; vitin 2010, ku ka marr&euml; Diplom&euml;n Bachelor. Pas studimeve, ai vazhdoi t&euml; punoj&euml; kryesisht n&euml;&nbsp;mediumin e piktur&euml;s, nd&euml;rsa praktika e tij s&euml; fundmi &euml;sht&euml; zgjeruar n&euml; skulptur&euml;, instalacion, video dhe nd&euml;rhyrje n&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml;n publike. Me n&euml;nt&euml; ekspozita personale q&euml; nga viti 2012 n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Budapest dhe Bruksel dhe ekspozita t&euml; shumta kolektive n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Prag&euml;, Brno, G&ouml;teborg, Berlin, Drezden, Motovun, Krakov, Bukuresht, New Orleans, Sarawak Malajzi; Kazanxhiu mbetet nj&euml; nga t&euml; rinjt&euml; m&euml; t&euml; angazhuar protagonist&euml; n&euml; sken&euml;n kulturore bashk&euml;kohore shqiptare. Pozicioni i tij i pakompromis n&euml; lidhje me trajtimin e padrejt&euml; t&euml; grupit etnik rom paraqet vet&euml;m nj&euml; platform&euml; p&euml;r t&euml; shprehur mospajtimin individual p&euml;r dinamik&euml;n e nj&euml;anshme racore q&euml;, p&euml;r fat t&euml; keq, vazhdon t&euml; form&euml;soj&euml; bot&euml;kuptimet bashk&euml;kohore evropiane &ndash; n&euml; baza ditore, brenda dhe jasht&euml; arenave politike zyrtare. N&euml; k&euml;t&euml; kuptim, krijimi i imazhit t&euml; tij kontribuon n&euml; p&euml;rpjekjet pozitive t&euml; nj&euml; artisti t&euml; vet&euml;m p&euml;r t&euml; rikthyer dinjitetin e nj&euml; komuniteti t&euml; vendosur me forc&euml; dhe padrejt&euml;sisht n&euml; periferi t&euml; demokracis&euml; evropiane. Aktualisht ai &euml;sht&euml; an&euml;tar bordi i PAKIV i Institutit Evropian t&euml; Rom&euml;ve p&euml;r Art dhe Kultur&euml; dhe Z&euml;vend&euml;s Kryetar i Komitetit Shtet&euml;ror p&euml;r Pakicat Komb&euml;tare n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL);

