INSERT INTO `aktivitete_translations` (`id`, `aktivitete_id`, `locale`, `description`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1, 1, 'en', '<p>Between January 2005 and September 2006 Stefano Roman conceived the project, 1.60 insurgent space in Tirana. The project was born out of the desire of spreading artistic initiatives throughout the city. These have materialized in exhibitions, performances or ephemeral interventions, and the project has been operating on a regular basis despite the nearly complete lack of funding. The spaces used &nbsp;included private apartments, empty buildings, public spaces and the street. These initiatives normally lasted only one day, carving a brief but always challenging presence within the city. While contesting conventional definitions of artistic practices, these projects aimed at generating a debate about the present role of the artist. These projects were normally the result of a collaboration between Romano and another Albanian or international curator. 1.60 Insurgent Space initiated collaborations between artists and curators from different countries, but also with students from the Art Academy in Tirana. (Elena Crippa)<br />\r\nStatement from 1.60 insurgent space catalog:<br />\r\n&ldquo;1.60insurgent space emerges from the idea of art as creation and diffusion of collaborative practices / in constant interaction with the urban space from which and in which is born / and for this equipped with &ldquo;impermanent citizenship&rdquo; of those places / collector of insurgent practices / destined to visualize an &ldquo;other&rdquo; image and imaginary of art / exhibitions as signals of a new mental geography of contemporary art /&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n1.60insurgent space is the name of a space that moves itself continuously inside the cities, producing exhibitions whose intent is to compare international artists with various places, different from the &ldquo;institutional ones&rdquo;, in order to create new arguments around the art and its borders. The exhibitions question themselves and the outside about the spaces they hit upon. They are programmed in Tirana and curated every month by Stefano Romano and a different curator each time.&rdquo; Stefano Romano&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(2, 1, 'al', '<p>Midis janarit 2005 dhe shtatorit 2006 Stefano Roman konceptoi projektin 1.60 Insurgent Space (1.60 hap&euml;sir&euml; ​​kryengrit&euml;se) n&euml; Tiran&euml;. Projekti lindi nga d&euml;shira p&euml;r t&euml; p&euml;rhapur iniciativa artistike n&euml; t&euml; gjith&euml; qytetin. K&euml;to iniciativa u materializuan n&euml; ekspozita, performanca apo nd&euml;rhyrje kalimtare dhe projekti arriti t&euml; funksionoj&euml; rregullisht pavar&euml;sisht munges&euml;s pothuajse t&euml; plot&euml; t&euml; financimit. Hap&euml;sirat e p&euml;rdorura p&euml;rfshinin apartamente private, nd&euml;rtesa boshe, hap&euml;sira publike dhe rrug&euml;. K&euml;to nd&euml;rhyrje zgjasnin zakonisht vet&euml;m nj&euml; dit&euml;, duke krijuar nj&euml; prani t&euml; shkurt&euml;r por gjithmon&euml; sfiduese brenda qytetit. Teksa kund&euml;rshtonin p&euml;rkufizimet konvencionale t&euml; praktikave artistike, k&euml;to projekte synonin t&euml; gjeneronin nj&euml; debat rreth rolit aktual t&euml; artistit. Projekte ishin zakonisht rezultat i nj&euml; bashk&euml;punimi midis Romanos dhe nj&euml; kuratori tjet&euml;r shqiptar apo nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar. 1.60 Insurgent Space nisi bashk&euml;punime mes artist&euml;ve dhe kurator&euml;ve nga vende t&euml; ndryshme, por edhe me student&euml; nga Akademia e Arteve n&euml; Tiran&euml;. (Elena Crippa)<br />\r\nKoncept nga katalogu i 1.60 Insurgent Space:<br />\r\n1.60 Insurgent Space lind nga ideja e artit si krijim dhe p&euml;rhapje e praktikave bashk&euml;punuese / n&euml; nd&euml;rveprim t&euml; vazhduesh&euml;m me hap&euml;sir&euml;n urbane nga e cila dhe n&euml; t&euml; cil&euml;n lindi / dhe p&euml;r k&euml;t&euml; e pajisur me &ldquo;shtet&euml;sin&euml; e p&euml;rhershme&rdquo; t&euml; atyre vendeve / mbledh&euml;s t&euml; praktikave kryengrit&euml;se / t&euml; destinuara p&euml;r t&euml; vizualizuar nj&euml; imazh &quot;tjet&euml;r&quot; dhe imagjinar t&euml; artit / ekspozita si sinjale t&euml; nj&euml; gjeografie t&euml; re mendore t&euml; artit bashk&euml;kohor /<br />\r\n1.60insurgent space &euml;sht&euml; emri i nj&euml; hap&euml;sire q&euml; l&euml;viz n&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml; t&euml; vazhdueshme brenda qyteteve, duke prodhuar ekspozita, q&euml;llimi i t&euml; cilave &euml;sht&euml; t&euml; krahasojn&euml; artist&euml;t nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar&euml; me vende t&euml; ndryshme, ndryshe nga ato &ldquo;institucional&rdquo;, p&euml;r t&euml; krijuar argumente t&euml; reja rreth artit dhe kufinjve t&euml; tij. Ekspozitat v&euml;n&euml; n&euml; dyshim veten dhe t&euml; jashtmen p&euml;r hap&euml;sirat q&euml; ato godasin. Ato programohen n&euml; Tiran&euml; dhe kurohen &ccedil;do muaj nga Stefano Romano dhe &ccedil;do her&euml; nga nj&euml; kurator tjet&euml;r. Stefano Romano<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(3, 2, 'en', '<p>ARTIVISM, was a project by Artkontakt that took place in Tirana between October 2018 and May 2019.<br />\r\n&ldquo;The purpose of ARTIVISM is to communicate through any possible form of artistic expression such as video, street art, posters, installations, performances, some critical attitudes that contemporary Albanian artists have for the perception of community members on the environments where they live, in order to turn them into actors of exerting civic pressure on local authorities. ARTIVISM aims to use art as a genuine tool of political protest, without making politics, to bring about a radical socio-cultural change that goes in the direction of the wishes and expectations of the community. Lack of sensitivity and civic response to issues related to public services (lack of quality), acute urban, environmental, identity problems, but also the lure of citizens with repeated slogans and promises during campaigns, but unfulfilled, have made absurd situations be accepted as a normal part of our reality. This situation is unhealthy for local democracy and should be discouraged, starting with the 2019 local elections. Through &lsquo;Activist Art&rsquo; (ARTIVISM) we want to raise debates about local democracy and civic participation in decision-making. ARTIVISM aims through art to give a contribution to promote reflection and awareness, to give meaning to the human existence of communities in our city and to communicate meaningful messages to the public, beyond political propaganda.&rdquo; Andi Tepelena<br />\r\nAndi Tepelena is the founder and director of Art Kontakt, a non-profit organization established in Tirana-Albania in 2007. The main objectives of Art Kontakt are the promotion of international cultural exchanges and the implementation of artistic initiatives in the fields, such as: contemporary art, cultural heritage, and cultural tourism. Andi Tepelena also assists interested bodies in improving and implementing the best practices in the field of art management in Albania. He is the author of numerous articles in Albania on the topic of management of culture and performing arts. In particular: &ldquo;Albania needs big international events&rdquo;-Gazeta Shqip 2014 &ldquo;Contemporary arts trends, a challenge for Albania&rdquo; Gazeta Shqiptare 2008 &ldquo;Nomadism in Lekurs- Revista Kult 2008 &ldquo;Art Economy of a City&rdquo;- Gazeta Standart 2007 &ldquo;Regarding the Biennial of Venice&rdquo;- Gazeta Shekulli 2007 &ldquo;The challenges of an art festival&rdquo;- Revista Kult 2007 &ldquo;The alternative funds in the field of art&rdquo;- Gazeta Metropol 2006.<br />\r\nARTIVIZM, ishte nj&euml; projekt nga Artkontakt q&euml; u zhvillua n&euml; Tiran&euml; midis Tetorit 2018 dhe Majit 2019.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(4, 2, 'al', '<p>&ldquo;Q&euml;llimi i ARTIVIZ&Euml;M &euml;sht&euml; t&euml; komunikoj&euml; me an&euml; t&euml; &ccedil;do form&euml; t&euml; mundshme t&euml; shprehjes artistike si video, street art, postera, instalacione, performanca, disa q&euml;ndrime kritike q&euml; kan&euml; artist&euml;t bashkohor&euml; shqiptar&euml; p&euml;r perceptimin e pjes&euml;tar&euml;ve t&euml; komuniteteve mbi ambjentet ku jetojn&euml;, &nbsp;me q&euml;llim q&euml; ti kthejn&euml; ata n&euml; aktor&euml; t&euml; ushtrimit t&euml; presionit qytetar ndaj autoriteteve lokale. ARTIVIZ&Euml;M synon ta p&euml;rdor artin si mjet t&euml; mir&euml;fillt&euml; protest&euml; politike, pa b&euml;r&euml; politik&euml;, p&euml;r t&euml; sjell nj&euml; ndryshim rr&euml;nj&euml;sor social-kulturor q&euml; shkon n&euml; kah t&euml; d&euml;shirave dhe pritshm&euml;rive t&euml; komunitetit. Mungesa e ndjeshm&euml;ris&euml; dhe reagimit qytetar ndaj problematikave t&euml; lidhura me sh&euml;rbimet publike (mang&euml;sia apo cil&euml;sia e tyre), problemet e mprehta urbane, mjedisore, identitare, por &nbsp;dhe joshja ndaj qytetar&euml;ve me slogane dhe premtime t&euml; p&euml;rs&euml;ritura gjat&euml; fushatave,por t&euml; pambajtura, kan&euml; b&euml;r&euml; q&euml; situata absurdi t&euml; pranohen si pjes&euml; normale e realitetit ton&euml;. Kjo situat&euml; &euml;sht&euml; e pash&euml;ndetshme p&euml;r nj&euml; demokraci lokale dhe duhet t&euml; dekurajohet, duke filluar nga zgjedhjet lokale t&euml; 2019. P&euml;rmes &lsquo;Artit Aktivist&rsquo; (ARTIVIZ&Euml;M) duam t&euml; ngrejm&euml; debate n&euml; lidhje me demokracin&euml; lokale dhe pjes&euml;marrjen qytetare n&euml; vendimarrje. ARTIVIZ&Euml;M synon q&euml; n&euml;p&euml;rmjet artit t&euml; jap nj&euml; kontribut p&euml;r t&euml; t&euml; nxitur nj&euml; reflektim dhe nd&euml;rgjegj&euml;sim, ti japi kuptim ekzistenc&euml;s njer&euml;zore t&euml; komuniteteve n&euml; qytetin ton&euml; dhe t&euml; komunikoj&euml; mesazhe domethen&euml;se p&euml;r publikun, p&euml;rtej propagand&euml;s politike.&rdquo; Andi Tepelena<br />\r\nAndi Tepelena &euml;sht&euml; themelues dhe drejtor i Art Kontakt nj&euml; organizat&euml; jofitimprur&euml;se e themeluar n&euml; Tiran&euml;-Shqip&euml;ri n&euml; vitin 2007. Objektivat kryesore t&euml; Art Kontakt jan&euml; promovimi i shk&euml;mbimeve kulturore nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tare dhe zbatimi i nismave artistike n&euml; fushat si: arti bashk&euml;kohor, trash&euml;gimia kulturore dhe turizmi kulturor. Andi Tepelena asiston gjithashtu organet e interesuara n&euml; p&euml;rmir&euml;simin dhe zbatimin e praktikave m&euml; t&euml; mira n&euml; fush&euml;n e menaxhimit t&euml; artit n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri. Ai &euml;sht&euml; autor i artikujve t&euml; shumt&euml; n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri mbi tem&euml;n e menaxhimit t&euml; kultur&euml;s dhe artit skenik. N&euml; ve&ccedil;anti: &ldquo;Shqip&euml;ria ka nevoj&euml; p&euml;r ngjarje t&euml; m&euml;dha nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tare&rdquo;-Gazeta Shqip 2014 &ldquo;Tendencat e artit bashk&euml;kohor, sfid&euml; p&euml;r Shqip&euml;rin&euml;&rdquo; Gazeta Shqiptare 2008 &ldquo;Nomadizmi n&euml; Lekurs- Revista Kult 2008 &ldquo;Arti Ekonomia e nj&euml; qyteti&rdquo;- Gazeta Standart 2007 &ldquo;N&euml; lidhje me Bienalen. i Venecias&rdquo;- Gazeta Shekulli 2007 &ldquo;Sfidat e nj&euml; festivali arti&rdquo;- Revista Kult 2007 &ldquo;Fondet alternative n&euml; fush&euml;n e artit&rdquo;- Gazeta Metropol 2006.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(5, 3, 'en', '<p>The solo show &ldquo;With Open Eyes, With Eyes&rdquo; took place from 17 May - 10 June 2018 at Bazament Art Space, Silva Agostini introduces three different projects that originate in the metaphysical re-contextualization of human and cultural traces in the Albanian reality, as well as that of Blloku neighborhood in Tirana. In this exhibition, the artist shifts between real dimensions and those beyond, stirring up the memory and associating it with spiritual moments that live unnoticed within us. Those moments are passed from generation to generation, in the everyday life and the realities we fabricate.<br />\r\nBazament is an art space dedicated to contemporary art in Tirana, Albania. Its main focus is to create an independent and sustainable contemporary art scene, by offering a new exhibition space where narratives and the discourse of Albanian contemporary art can be shown and discussed, in close relationship to the international contemporary art scene.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(6, 3, 'al', '<p>Ekspozita personale &ldquo;With Open Eyes, With Eyes&rdquo; q&euml; u zhvillua nga data 17 Maj - 10 Qershor n&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml; e artit Bazament, Silva Agostini prezanton tre projekte t&euml; ndryshme q&euml; kan&euml; origjin&euml;n n&euml; rikontekstualizimin metafizik t&euml; gjurm&euml;ve njer&euml;zore dhe kulturore n&euml; realitetin shqiptar, si dhe at&euml; t&euml; lagjes Blloku n&euml; Tiran&euml;. N&euml; k&euml;t&euml; ekspozit&euml;, artistja lundron mes dimensioneve reale dhe atyre p&euml;rtej, duke ndezur kujtes&euml;n dhe duke e shoq&euml;ruar me momente shpirt&euml;rore, q&euml; jetojn&euml; pa u v&euml;n&euml; re brenda nesh. Ato momente q&euml; kalohen brez pas brezi n&euml; p&euml;rditshm&euml;rin&euml; dhe realitetet q&euml; ne krijojm&euml;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bazamenti &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml; ​​arti kushtuar artit bashk&euml;kohor n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. Fokusi i tij kryesor &euml;sht&euml; krijimi i nj&euml; skene t&euml; pavarur dhe t&euml; q&euml;ndrueshme t&euml; artit bashk&euml;kohor, duke ofruar nj&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml; ​​t&euml; re ekspozuese ku narrativat dhe diskursi i artit bashk&euml;kohor shqiptar mund t&euml; shfaqen dhe diskutohen, n&euml; lidhje t&euml; ngusht&euml; me sken&euml;n e artit bashk&euml;kohor nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(7, 4, 'en', '<p>This exhibition &ldquo;Beyond Matter - Exhibition Artists in Residency 2020-2021&rdquo; organized by Tirana Art Lab and curated by Adela Demetja, took place from 4 -20 November 2021 at Bulevard Art and Media Institute. The show presented the projects realized by Donika &Ccedil;ina, Hanna Hildebrand and Alexander Walmsley during their two-month residency at Tirana Art Lab - Center for Contemporary Art between 2020-2021. These three artists chosen from over 90 applicants, develop new works reflecting on public space issues in the city of Tirana and Virtual Reality, contributing artistically to the discourse generated by the project BEYOND MATTER. The residency program and this exhibition is part of the large-scale cooperation project BEYOND MATTER. Cultural Heritage on the Verge of Virtual Reality, dedicated to novel, digital approaches to exhibition revival, documentation, and dissemination, and the artistic, curatorial, and museological elaboration of the chances given by virtual representation.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(8, 4, 'al', '<p>Ekspozit&euml; &ldquo;P&euml;rtej Materies - Ekspozita e Artist&euml;ve n&euml; Rezidenc&euml; 2020-2021&rdquo; e organizuar nga Tirana Art Lab dhe e kuruar nga Adela Demetja, u zvillua nga 4-20 N&euml;ntor 2021 tek Bulevard Instituti i Artit dhe Medias. N&euml; t&euml; u paraqit&euml;n projektet e realizuara nga Donika &Ccedil;ina, Hanna Hildebrand dhe Alexander Walmsley gjat&euml; q&euml;ndrimit t&euml; tyre dy mujor n&euml; Tirana Art Lab &ndash; Qendra p&euml;r Artin Bashk&euml;kohor n&euml; periudh&euml;n 2020-2021. K&euml;ta tre artist&euml; t&euml; zgjedhur nga mbi 90 aplikant&euml;, kan&euml; zhvilluan vepra t&euml; reja q&euml; reflektojn&euml; mbi &ccedil;&euml;shtjet e hap&euml;sir&euml;s publike n&euml; qytetin e Tiran&euml;s dhe realitetit virtual, duke kontribuar artistikisht n&euml; diskursin e gjeneruar nga projekti BEYOND MATTER. Programi i rezidenc&euml;s dhe kjo ekspozit&euml; jan&euml; pjes&euml; e projektit t&euml; bashk&euml;punimit &ldquo;Beyond Matter. Trash&euml;gimia kulturore n&euml; prag t&euml; realitetit virtual&rdquo;, kushtuar qasjeve inovative dixhitale t&euml; rishfaqjes, dokumentimit dhe shp&euml;rndarjes s&euml; ekspozitave, si dhe p&euml;rpunimit artistik, kuratorial dhe muzeologjik t&euml; gjeneruara nga p&euml;rfaq&euml;simi virtual.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(9, 5, 'en', '<p>DOUBLE FEATURE #03 presented works by Elton Baxhaku &amp; Fabrizio Bellomo from 29 October - 30 November 2015 at Tirana Art Lab, curated by Romeo Kodra. Fabrizio Bellomo was the third artist in residency for 2015 at Tirana Art Lab. Like many artists in residency at TAL, Bellomo&#39;s artistic research and production process is a multi-layered one, that enriches the laboratory of TAL with new meanings. His residency in the capital city resulted in the creation of a public art intervention and a video work. And in these works, like in most of his other works, Bellomo draws a thin but settled line, between the social problematics, anthropological transformations, and artistic interpretations. And on this thin but settled line, it becomes possible to feel the aesthetic or ethical vibration of an artist that keeps searching and progressing like an acrobat balancing on a wire, whose beginning is known but the ending unknown. While Bellomo finds these drifted subjects in former-workers now unemployed, be it Albanian or Italian, alienated humans as a result of the tight relationship with the tools and machines, for the second artist in Double Feature #3, Elton Baxhaku, these are the Roma community. Together with them, the artist emerges in the most miserable labyrinths of the Albanian society, where tools are still semi-primitive, but however still reciprocally affecting the relationship between man-machine. Video art functions for Elton as a means to redefine the lost purpose of documentary film. With video art Baxhaku &ndash; using image repetition and almost only autistic sounds &ndash; recharges his psycho-physical energies, gains his strength out of the social apathy of the unengaged Albanian society, in this never transiting transition, that spins around repeating itself (in sounds and images), that gives him the creative energy for an initiative, and action for new social resistance. Although repetition is quite a simple strategy to justify the artistic creation, taking in consideration Baxhaku&rsquo;s practice and works, it turns into a solid approach for both aesthetic and ethical aspects, likewise with Bellomo, with whom he shares the passion and cultivation for documentary cinema. By bringing these two artistic positions together, we have tried once again to create the combination that characterizes the Double Feature format at Tirana Art Lab. We have tried once again to highlight the concept that the genesis of art is always at the bottom, at the periphery, the lower and repellent territories of society, but as well as from inside, by the contamination of foreign artists that at the same time contaminate the local context with the art potion, by cultivating it during their residency at TAL. Thank this potion, thank new meanings produced within the Albanian social corpus, at Tirana Art Lab, and with &ldquo;Double Feature #3&rdquo;, we try once again to fulfill our mission as culture operators: to reformulate and remodify the art and culture competencies inside our social context.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(10, 5, 'al', '<p>Double Feature #3 ishte nj&euml; ekspozit&euml; nga data 29 Tetor - 30 N&euml;ntor me veprat e artist&euml;ve Elton Baxhaku &amp; Fabrizio Bellomo, tek Tirana Art Lab e kuruar nga Romeo Kodra. Atristi i tret&euml; n&euml; residenc&euml;, p&euml;r 2015-n, n&euml; Tirana Art Lab &euml;sht&euml; italiani Fabrizio Bellomo. Si t&euml; gjith&euml; artist&euml;t e tjer&euml; q&euml; kan&euml; kaluar n&euml; k&euml;t&euml; rezidenc&euml; edhe Fabrizio ka nj&euml; shtres&euml;zim dometh&euml;n&euml;s t&euml; k&euml;rkimit dhe procesit pas pun&euml;s artistike, q&euml; pasuron me kuptime t&euml; reja laboratorin e TAL. N&euml;p&euml;rmjet procesit dhe k&euml;rkimit artistik, q&euml; n&euml; rastin e rezidenc&euml;s n&euml; kryeqytet prodhuan nj&euml; vep&euml;r arti publike dhe nj&euml; video art, Bellomo - si&ccedil; b&euml;n shpesh n&euml; pun&euml;t e tij - heq nj&euml; viz&euml; sa t&euml; holl&euml; aq edhe t&euml; sigurt&euml; n&euml; mes t&euml; problematikave shoq&euml;rore, transformimeve antropologjike dhe interpretimeve artistike. Dhe &euml;sht&euml; mbi k&euml;t&euml; viz&euml; t&euml; holl&euml; dhe t&euml; q&euml;ndrueshme q&euml; ndihen t&euml; gjitha l&euml;kundjet etike dhe estetike t&euml; nj&euml; artisti q&euml; nuk rresht s&euml; k&euml;rkuari duke avancuar si nj&euml; ekuilibrist mbi k&euml;t&euml; fill, t&euml; cilit i njeh fillimin, por asnj&euml;h&euml;r&euml; fundin. N&euml;se p&euml;r Bellomo-n njer&euml;zit n&euml; rravgim jan&euml; ish-pun&euml;tor&euml;t tashm&euml; t&euml; papun&euml;, shqiptar&euml; apo italian&euml; qofshin, njer&euml;zit e alienuar prej marrdh&euml;nies tejet t&euml; af&euml;rt me veglat makinike, p&euml;r Elton Baxhakun, artistin e dyt&euml; t&euml; &ldquo;Double Feature #03&rdquo;, jan&euml; rom&euml;t. Artisti me ata zhytet m&euml; tej n&euml; labirintet e thella e t&euml; mjerueshme t&euml; shoq&euml;ris&euml; shqiptare, aty ku veglat jan&euml; ende gjysm&euml; primitive ose mekanike, por jo m&euml; pak t&euml; ndikuara dhe ndikuese karshi njeriut. P&euml;r Eltonin video arti duket si nj&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml; p&euml;r t&euml; rigjetur kuptimin e humbur t&euml; dokumentar&euml;ve t&euml; tij, ose m&euml; mir&euml; t&euml; themi se &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; grad&euml; e zero e kuptimit q&euml; rimon me menefregizmin e p&euml;rgjithsh&euml;m p&euml;rkundrejt tematikave dhe plag&euml;ve shoq&euml;rore q&euml; dokumentar&euml;t prekin. Me video artin Baxhaku - duke p&euml;rdorur nj&euml; rip&euml;rs&euml;ritje imazhesh dhe tingujsh thuajse autistike - duket sikur rikarikon energjit&euml; e tij psiko-fizike, rimbledh forcat prej zbraz&euml;tis&euml; s&euml; angazhimit shoq&euml;ror shqiptar, prej k&euml;tij tranzitimi q&euml; nuk tranziton, por q&euml; duke u rrotulluar n&euml; vetvete, duke u rip&euml;rs&euml;ritur (n&euml; tinguj dhe imazhe) i jep artistit energji kreative p&euml;r nj&euml; iniciativ&euml;, nj&euml; aksion, nj&euml; rezistenc&euml; shoq&euml;rore t&euml; re. Rip&euml;rs&euml;ritja &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; gjetje shum&euml; e thjesht&euml; p&euml;r t&euml; justifikuar vepr&euml;n artistike, por, kur ajo shihet n&euml;n lenten e gjith&euml; vepr&euml;s s&euml; Baxhakut, merr nj&euml; dimension tjet&euml;r, solid nga pik&euml;pamja estetike dhe etike, e nj&euml;jt&euml; me at&euml; t&euml; Bellomo-s, me t&euml; cilin bashk&euml;ndan edhe pasionin dhe kultivimin e kinemas&euml; dokumentare. Duke i b&euml;r&euml; bashk&euml; k&euml;ta artist&euml; kemi dashur, edhe nj&euml; her&euml;, t&euml; krijojm&euml; nd&euml;rthurjen q&euml; karakterizon formatin &ldquo;Double Feature&rdquo; t&euml; Tirana Art Lab. Kemi dashur t&euml; evidentojm&euml; edhe nj&euml; her&euml; se gjeneza e artit fillon gjithmon&euml; nga posht&euml;, nga periferit&euml; dhe nga territoret m&euml; t&euml; ulta e t&euml; p&euml;rbuzura t&euml; shoq&euml;ris&euml;, por edhe nga brenda, nga kontaminimi i artist&euml;ve t&euml; huaj q&euml; n&euml; t&euml; nj&euml;jt&euml;n koh&euml; kontaminojn&euml; kontekstin me melhelmin e artit duke e kultivuar at&euml; p&euml;rgjat&euml; rezidencave t&euml; tyre n&euml; TAL. Fal&euml; k&euml;tij melhelmi, fal&euml; kuptimeve t&euml; reja q&euml; prodhon me korpusin shoq&euml;ror shqiptar, n&euml; TAL dhe me k&euml;t&euml; &ldquo;Double Feature #3&rdquo;, po mundohemi t&euml; p&euml;rmbushim edhe nj&euml; her&euml; misionin ton&euml; si operator&euml; kulturor&euml;: riformulimin dhe rikodifikimin e kompetencave t&euml; artit dhe kultur&euml;s n&euml; kontestin ton&euml; shoq&euml;ror.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(11, 6, 'en', '<p>&ldquo;Performativ Exhibition #1 - Center of Integration&rdquo; was a joint project of Tirana Art Lab and the art collective Patriotisme that had its first public appearance at Tirana Art Lab from 24 to 29 of July 2018. Various Albanian and foreign artists, curators, and theorists/researchers were invited to contribute to the program through lectures, talks, performances, and installations. Performative Exhibition&quot; is a format initiated by Tirana Art Lab &ndash; Center for Contemporary Art with the intention to disclose exhibiting and to make public through performativity not only the process of artistic creation and curating, but also find ways to include in the exhibiting process and the means of production behind and beyond the event itself. The concept of &ldquo;Performative Exhibition&rdquo; aims to find new ways of exhibiting and curating which break with the temporary/unique features of the contemporary exhibition and propose enduring ways of working together. The first exhibition of this series will be developed under the title &ldquo;Center of Integration&rdquo; and aims to reflect visually, poetically, and theoretically on the notion of integration.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(12, 6, 'al', '<p>&ldquo;Ekspozit&euml; Performative #1 - Qendra e Integrimit&rdquo; &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; projekt i p&euml;rbashk&euml;t i Tirana Art Lab dhe kolektivit artistik Patriotisme, q&euml; pati shfaqjen e par&euml; publike n&euml; Tirana Art Lab nga data 24 deri m&euml; 29 korrik 2018. Artist&euml;, kurator&euml; dhe teoricien&euml; / studiues Shqiptar&euml; dhe t&euml; huaj jan&euml; ftuar t&euml; kontribuojn&euml; n&euml; program p&euml;rmes leksioneve, bisedimeve, performancave dhe instalacioneve. &ldquo;Ekspozit&euml; Performative&rdquo; &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; format i ri i filluar nga Tirana Art Lab - Qendra p&euml;r Art Bashk&euml;kohor me q&euml;llim zb&euml;rthimin e ekspozit&euml;s si format dhe b&euml;rjes publike t&euml; proceseve artistike krijuese dhe t&euml; kurimit p&euml;rmes performativitetit. Gjithashtu synon t&euml; gjej&euml; m&euml;nyra p&euml;r t&euml; p&euml;rfshir&euml; n&euml; procesin e ekspozimit mjetet dhe kushtet e prodhimit artistik q&euml; shkojn&euml; p&euml;rtej vet&euml; ngjarjes ekspozuese. Koncepti i &quot;Ekspozit&euml;s Performative&quot; synon gjetjen e m&euml;nyrave t&euml; reja t&euml; ekspozimit dhe kurimit, t&euml; cilat thyejn&euml; tiparet e p&euml;rkohshme / unike t&euml; ekspozit&euml;s bashk&euml;kohore dhe propozojn&euml; m&euml;nyra t&euml; q&euml;ndrueshme p&euml;r t&euml; punuar s&euml; bashku. Ekspozita e par&euml; e k&euml;saj serie do t&euml; zhvillohet n&euml;n titullin &quot;Qendra e Integrimit&quot; dhe synon t&euml; pasqyroj&euml; n&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml; vizive, poetike dhe teorike, konceptin e integrimit.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(13, 7, 'en', '<p>The exhibition TRIPLE FEATURE #05 with works by &Ccedil;ETA, Georgia Kotretsos, Pleurad Xhafa, curated by Adela Demetja &amp; Romeo Kodra, took place from 3 December - 28 January 2017 at Tirana Art Lab. Double Feature is an exhibition format introduced by Tirana Art Lab with the aim of systematically displaying in our premises, two artistic positions to the Albanian, the regional, and international audience. Triple Feature #05 is a special edition of this format, where we exhibit together with the works of Albanian art collective &Ccedil;ETA, Greek artist and researcher Georgia Kotretsos, and Albanian artist Pleurad Xhafa. Triple Feature # 5 presentation, is part of &ldquo;Heroes We Love&rdquo; collaboration and multidisciplinary project on the controversial topic of the socialist heritage of 20th-century European art. The show consisted of works exhibited for the first time at Tirana Art Lab as well as two artistic interventions in the public space by &Ccedil;ETA and Georgia Kotretsos, commissioned by Tirana Art Lab. Tirana Art Lab engaged contemporary artists of the younger generation into the project through the art intervention on the selected socialist-era monuments. The interventions are aimed at stimulating public debate, initiating new interpretations, and envisaging the potentials of those artworks of the past. Triple Feature #05 was dedicated to the intersection between art and activism, art activism, and the extended role of the artist as an engaged citizen, trying to make a change not only inside the art system but also outside it, in real life. This event was co-funded by the Creative Europe Programme of the European Union.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(14, 7, 'al', '<p>Ekspozita Triple Feature #05 me Vepra nga artist&euml;t &Ccedil;ETA, Georgia Kotretsos dhe Pleurad Xhafa, kuruar nga Adela Demetja dhe Romeo Kodra, u mbajt tek Tirana Art Lab nga 3 Dhjetori deri m&euml; 28 Janar 2017. Double Feature &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; format serial ekspozitash i Tirana Art Lab, p&euml;r p&euml;rmbushjen sistematike t&euml; q&euml;llimeve t&euml; saj, ku i parashtrohen publikut dy perspektiva artistike, shqiptare, rajonale apo nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tare. Triple Feature #5 ishte nj&euml; edicion special i formatit serial, ku u ekspozuan s&euml;bashku pun&euml;t e kolektivit artistik shqiptar &Ccedil;ETA, artistes dhe hulumtueses greke Georgia Kotretsos dhe artistit shqiptar Pleurad Xhafa.<br />\r\nTriple Feature #05 ishte pjes&euml; e projektit t&euml; p&euml;rbashk&euml;t &bdquo;Heroes We Love&ldquo; dedikuar trashigimis artistike nga periudha e socializmit. Ekspozita p&euml;rb&euml;hej prej pun&euml;ve artistike q&euml; u prezantohen p&euml;r her t&euml; par&euml; n&euml; TAL, si dhe dy nd&euml;rhyrjeve artistike nga &Ccedil;eta dhe Gerogia Kotretsos n&euml; hap&euml;sira publike t&euml; komisionuara nga TAL. Tirana Art Lab angazhoi n&euml; projekt artist&euml; bashk&euml;kohore t&euml; brezit t&euml; ri, p&euml;rmes nd&euml;rhyrjeve artistike n&euml; monumentet e p&euml;rzgjedhura t&euml; epok&euml;s socialiste. Nd&euml;rhyrjet kishin p&euml;r q&euml;llim t&euml; nxisnin debatin publik, interpretime t&euml; reja dhe t&euml; evidentonin potencialet e k&euml;tyre veprave t&euml; s&euml; kaluar&euml;s. Triple Feature #05 i dedikohej nd&euml;rthurjes midis artit dhe aktivizmit, aktivizmit artistik dhe rolit t&euml; gjer&euml; t&euml; artistit t&euml; angazhuar si qytetar q&euml; synon t&euml; ndryshoj&euml; jo vet&euml;m sistemin e artit por edhe realitetin ku jeton. Ky projekt &euml;sht&euml; i bashk&euml;financuar nga Programi Europa Krijuese i Bashkimit Europian.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(15, 8, 'en', '<p>&ldquo;PIPIFAX FOR TIRANA. Through the looking glass and what we found there&rdquo;, with works by Haus am Gern (Rudolf Steiner &amp; Barbara Meyer Cesta) organized by Tirana Art Lab and curated by Adela Demetja, took place from 4-12 June 2011 at Tirana Ekspres. The exhibition presents works created by Swiss artists Haus am Gern, during their two months in residency at Tirana Art Lab. With this exhibition, the space of Tirana Express at the Magazine Block, nearby the former Tirana Train Station, was inaugurated.<br />\r\nPIPIFAX means nonsense and is of Jewish origin. Jewish refer to the word JHWH (Jahweh, Jehovah) to name God. Haus am Gern take this term and transform it into an important reference point for their artistic project. PIPIFAX symbolizes nonsense and at the same time, it can change its original meaning when trying to inverse or translate it. The concept of inverse plays a crucial role in conceiving the works of the exhibition. The second part of the exhibition title &ldquo;Through the looking glass and what we found there&rdquo; refers to the book written by Lewis Caroll in 1871. The book follows up Alice&#39;s Adventure in Wonderland. In Through the Looking Glass, the settings and the concept of the book are that everything is a mirrored image of the real world. The story takes place in a parallel mirrored world where everything is in opposite and where the time runes backward. If you see the images photographed by Barbara and Rudolf they will appear quite normal. All people involved in the photographing process play an intriguing role in the setting of the picture. The big sizes of the photos will allow the public to see every single detail of the work. All the 13 images are mirrored and the concept and elements used by the artists to develop the project can be understood and perceived by the public only from a certain distance. A common element repeated in all the photos is the Albanian flag. The black eagle with two heads, the symbol of our Flag is the only element that remains the same even if the photos are in reverse. The photos taken in key places in Tirana reflect the political changes and social dynamics that took place in the city during the last month. The artists and students involved in the project have created a series of pictures associated as metaphors for this situation. They try to provide a mirrored situation of the reality in which we live and that we are all part of this converted reality. This artwork enables us to see the world from a different perspective and to question the role that we all play in society.&nbsp;<br />\r\nWith special thanks to: Matilda Odobashi, Illir Kaso, Florjan Fejzollari, Redi Saliasi, Enkeleda Suti (TIRANA ART LAB), Dritan Nasi &amp; Team (TEN Center Tirana), Jona Matohiti / Ashraf Anwer (MAK &ndash; Albania), Klajdi Kruja, Rubin Beqo, Edmond Ramushi (TIRANA EKSPRES)&nbsp;<br />\r\nWith the participation of: Matilda Odobashi, Bashkim Kupi, Demir Kurti, Olta &amp; Redi Saliasi, Mustafa Kacurri, Marlo Ndoci, Sead Kazanxhiu, Flugers Beci , Albi Azuni, Doris Beci, Rigels Dyrmishi, Alson Dyrmishi, Redi Qondraj, Kristofer Ndreko, Miletovon Nrdeko, Dejvi Mu&ccedil;aj , Ernard Dyli, Armando Qoshku, Florjan Fejzollari, Armando Qoshku, Elvisa Pllo&ccedil;i, Olsi Odobashi, Jovana Muka, Brikena Lila, Arjola Oshafi, Bud Spender, Terence Hill, Amanda Hyseni, Ernard Dyli, Marvina &Ccedil;ela, Alketa Ramaj, Illir Kaso, Andri Ibrahimaj, Klajdi Kruja, Rubin Beqo, Edmond Ramushi<br />\r\nThis project was supported by ProHelvetia.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(16, 8, 'al', '<p>&ldquo;PIPIFAX P&Euml;R TIRAN&Euml;. N&euml;p&euml;rmjet pasqyr&euml; dhe &ccedil;far&euml; gjet&euml;m atje&rdquo;, me vepra nga Haus am Gern (Rudolf Steiner &amp; Barbara Meyer Cesta) organizuar nga Tirana Art Lab dhe kuruar nga Adela Demetja, u zhvillua nga 4-12 qershor 2011 n&euml; Tirana Ekspres. Ekspozita prezantoi veprat e krijuara nga artist&euml;t zviceran&euml; Haus am Gern, gjat&euml; dy muajve t&euml; q&euml;ndrimit t&euml; tyre n&euml; rezidenc&euml; tek Tirana Art Lab. Me k&euml;t&euml; ekspozit&euml; u p&euml;rurua hap&euml;sira e Tirana Express tek bllokun i magazinave, pran&euml; ish-Stacionit t&euml; Trenit t&euml; Tiran&euml;s.<br />\r\nPIPIFAX do t&euml; thot&euml; &ldquo;pa kuptim&rdquo; dhe &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; fjal&euml; me origjin&euml; hebraishteje. Haus am Gern e marrin k&euml;t&euml; term dhe e transformojn&euml; n&euml; nj&euml; pik&euml; t&euml; r&euml;nd&euml;sishme reference p&euml;r projektin e tyre artistik. PIPIFAX simbolizon munges&euml;n e dometh&euml;nies, t&euml; qenit pa kuptim, dhe n&euml; t&euml; nj&euml;jt&euml;n koh&euml; ai mund t&euml; ndryshoj&euml; kuptimin e tij origjinal n&euml;se p&euml;rpiqemi ta kthejm&euml; ose p&euml;rkthejm&euml; at&euml;. Koncepti i kthimit mbrapsht luan nj&euml; rol kryesor&euml; n&euml; realizimin e pun&euml;ve t&euml; ekspozit&euml;s. Pjesa e dyt&euml; e titullit t&euml; ekspozit&euml;s &rdquo;P&euml;rtej pasqyr&euml;s dhe &ccedil;far&euml; gjet&euml;m aty&rdquo;, i referohet librit t&euml; shkruar nga Lewis Caroll n&euml; vitin 1871. Libri vazhdon aventurat e Liz&euml;s n&euml; Bot&euml;n e &Ccedil;udirave. Tek libri mjediset dhe koncepti i librit &euml;sht&euml; q&euml; &ccedil;do gj&euml; &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>imazh i pasqyruar i bot&euml;s s&euml; v&euml;rtet&euml;. Historia zhvillohet n&euml; nj&euml; bot&euml; paralele t&euml; pasqyruar ku &ccedil;do gj&euml; &euml;sht&euml; n&euml; t&euml; kund&euml;rt dhe ku koha ec&euml;n mbrapsht. N&euml;se shikoni imazhet e fotografuara nga Barbara dhe Rudolf, n&euml; pamje t&euml; par&euml; ato do t&euml; duken krejt normale. T&euml; gjith&euml; njer&euml;zit e p&euml;rfshir&euml; n&euml; procesin e fotografimit luajn&euml; nj&euml; rol shum&euml; t&euml; r&euml;nd&euml;sish&euml;m dhe intrigues. T&euml; 13 imazhet n&euml; ekspozit&euml; jan&euml; t&euml; pasqyruara dhe t&euml; kthyera n&euml; an&euml; t&euml; kund&euml;rt. Nj&euml; element i p&euml;rbashk&euml;t i p&euml;rs&euml;ritura n&euml; t&euml; gjitha fotografit&euml; &euml;sht&euml; flamuri shqiptar. N&euml; disa prej fotove njer&euml;zit ose kan&euml; veshur bluze me flamurin shqiptar ose q&euml;ndrojn&euml; p&euml;rball&euml; ish Kombinatit t&euml; Tekstilit t&euml; Tiran&euml;s duke e mbajtur flamurin n&euml; preh&euml;r. Shqiponja e zez&euml; me dy koka, simboli i flamurit komb&euml;tar&euml; &euml;sht&euml; i vetmi element q&euml; nuk ndyshon edhe pse fotot jan&euml; t&euml; pasqyruara mbrapsht. Fotografit&euml; jan&euml; realizuar n&euml; vende kryesore n&euml; Tiran&euml; dhe reflektojn&euml; ndryshimet politike dhe dinamikat sociale t&euml; zhvilluara gjat&euml; muajit t&euml; fundit n&euml; qytet. Artist&euml;t dhe student&euml;t e p&euml;rfshir&euml; n&euml; projekt kan&euml; krijuar nj&euml; seri fotografish t&euml; asociuara si metafora t&euml; k&euml;saj situate. Ata p&euml;rpiqen t&euml; ofrojn&euml; nj&euml; situat&euml; t&euml; pasqyruar t&euml; realitetit t&euml; t&euml; cilin jetojm&euml; dhe q&euml; t&euml; gjith&euml; ne jemi pjes&euml; e k&euml;tij realiteti. Kjo pun&euml; na jep mund&euml;sin&euml; t&euml; shikojm&euml; bot&euml;n nga nj&euml; perspektiv&euml; tjet&euml;r dhe t&euml; ngrem&euml; pyetje mbi rolin q&euml; secili prej nesh luan n&euml; shoq&euml;ri.&nbsp;<br />\r\nMe falenderim t&euml; ve&ccedil;ant&euml; p&euml;r: Matilda Odobashi, Illir Kaso, Florjan Fejzollari, Redi Saliasi, Enkeleda Suti (TIRANA ART LAB), Dritan Nasi &amp; Team (TEN Center Tirana), Jona Matohiti / Ashraf Anwer (MAK &ndash; Albania), Klajdi Kruja, Rubin Beqo, Edmond Ramushi (TIRANA EKSPRES)<br />\r\nMe pjes&euml;marrjen e: Matilda Odobashi, Bashkim Kupi, Demir Kurti, Olta &amp; Redi Saliasi, Mustafa Kacurri, Marlo Ndoci, Sead Kazanxhiu, Flugers Beci , Albi Azuni, Doris Beci, Rigels Dyrmishi, Alson Dyrmishi, Redi Qondraj, Milionet Ndoci. Nrdeko, Dejvi Mu&ccedil;aj , Ernard Dyli, Armando Qoshku, Florjan Fejzollari, Armando Qoshku, Elvisa Pllo&ccedil;i, Olsi Odobashi, Jovana Muka, Brikena Lila, Arjola Oshafi, Bud Spender, Terence Hill, Amanda Hyseni, Ernard Dyli, Rama Alvisa, Market, Illir Kaso, Andri Ibrahimaj, Klajdi Kruja, Rubin Beqo, Edmond Ramushi<br />\r\nProjekti ky projekt u mb&euml;shtetet nga ProHelvetia.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(17, 9, 'en', '<p>&quot;Performative Exhibition #2 - Komuna e Parisit Revisited&quot;, an exhibition with Rena Raedle &amp; Vladan Jeremic and invited colleagues Valentina Bonizzi, Raino Isto, Filip Jovanovski, curated by Adela Demetja at <a href=\"http://www.tiranaartlab.org\">Tirana Art Lab</a> from 5-12 October 2019.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTirana Art Lab, was located at the ground floor of a five-floor domicile in the neighborhood Tiran&euml; e Re next to the&nbsp; street&nbsp; named&nbsp; Komuna e Parisit. Few or none of the inhabitants of this growing district are aware today of the historical connotation and importance related with the name Paris Commune. Therefore the second performative exhibition is developed under the title Komuna e Parisit Revisited and among other things aims at reflecting on the importance of the ideas of the Paris Commune and what it represents in the context of artistic, urban and social struggles. The Paris Commune marks a historical instance of political subjectivization of the working class, at a time when new bourgeois art institutions as the academy and art salons flourished in Paris. Gustave Courbet was one amongst many cultural workers and artisans who solidarized with the communards and took over important functions in the 72 days lasting workers-led self-government of Paris. The practice of him and his fellow artists was an early example of the avant-garde principle that art and life needs to be brought in one, and that artists need to become a political subject on the side of the working class. Do these practices have any significance in contemporary Albania and other European peripheries and on which level could they be re-actualized? What kind of artistic practices can be relevant in the context of social movements?<br />\r\nThe performative exhibition brings artistic practices by Rena Raedle &amp; Vladan Jeremic and invited colleagues Valentina Bonizzi, Raino Isto, Filip Jovanovski and discusses the function and use value of an artwork within social surroundings, modes of participation and possibilities of artists&rsquo; organization. The exhibition is a work in progress that will undergo different changes and transformation through out the entire duration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Organised with the support of Goethe-Zentrum Tirana as part of Deutsch October Program in Albania.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(18, 9, 'al', '<p>&quot;EKSPOZIT&Euml; PERFORMATIVE # 2 - Rivizitim: Komuna e Parisit&quot;, nj&euml; ekspozit&euml; me Rena Raedle &amp; Vladan Jeremic dhe me kolleg&euml; t&euml; ftuar Valentina Bonizzi, Raino Isto, Filip Jovanovski, kuruar nga Adela Demetja tek <a href=\"http://www.tiranaartlab.org\">Tirana Art Lab</a>, nga 5-12 Tetor 2019.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tirana Art Lab p&euml;r rreth pes&euml; vjet ka kryer aktivitetet e saj n&euml; katin e par&euml; t&euml; nj&euml; banese me pes&euml; kate n&euml; Tiran&euml;n e Re pran&euml; lagjes me emrin Komuna e Parisit. Pak ose asnj&euml; nga banor&euml;t e k&euml;saj lagjeje n&euml; rritje nuk jan&euml; t&euml; vet&euml;dijsh&euml;m sot p&euml;r konotacionin historik dhe r&euml;nd&euml;sin&euml; q&euml; lidhet me emrin Komuna e Parisit. Prandaj ekspozita e dyt&euml; performative zhvillohet n&euml;n titullin Rivizitim: Komuna e Parisit dhe nd&euml;r t&euml; tjera synon t&euml; pasqyroj&euml; r&euml;nd&euml;sin&euml; e ideve t&euml; Komun&euml;s s&euml; Parisit dhe asaj q&euml; kjo ngjarje p&euml;rfaq&euml;son n&euml; kontekstin e betejave artistike, urbane dhe sociale. Komuna e Parisit sh&euml;non nj&euml; shembull historik t&euml; subjektivizimit politik t&euml; klas&euml;s pun&euml;tore, n&euml; nj&euml; koh&euml; kur institucionet e reja t&euml; artit borgjez si akademia dhe sallonet e artit lul&euml;zonin n&euml; Paris. Gustave Courbet ishte nj&euml; nd&euml;r shum&euml; pun&euml;tor&euml; kulturor&euml; dhe artizan&euml; q&euml; u solidarizuan me komunar&euml;t dhe mor&euml;n funksione t&euml; r&euml;nd&euml;sishme n&euml; 72 dit&euml;t e vet&euml;qeverisjes s&euml; udh&euml;hequr nga pun&euml;tor&euml;t e Parisit. Praktika e tij dhe e artist&euml;ve t&euml; tjer&euml; ishte nj&euml; shembull i hersh&euml;m i parimit avangard&euml; q&euml; arti dhe jeta duhet t&euml; shkrihen n&euml; nj&euml;, dhe q&euml; artist&euml;t duhet t&euml; b&euml;hen subjekt politik n&euml; mb&euml;shtetje t&euml; klas&euml;s pun&euml;tore. A kan&euml; k&euml;to praktika ndonj&euml; r&euml;nd&euml;si n&euml; Shqip&euml;rin&euml; bashk&euml;kohore dhe periferit&euml; e tjera evropiane dhe n&euml; cilin nivel mund t&euml; ri-aktualizohen ato? Cilat praktika artistike mund t&euml; luajn nj&euml; rol dometh&euml;n&euml;s n&euml; kontekstin e l&euml;vizjeve shoq&euml;rore? Ekspozita performative sjell s&euml;bashku praktika artistike nga Rena Raedle &amp; Vladan Jeremic dhe kolleg&euml; t&euml; ftuarit Valentina Bonizzi, Raino Isto, Filip Jovanovski dhe diskuton funksionin dhe vler&euml;n e p&euml;rdorimit t&euml; nj&euml; vepre arti brenda mjedisit shoq&euml;ror, m&euml;nyrat e pjes&euml;marrjes dhe mund&euml;sit&euml; e organizimit t&euml; artist&euml;ve. Ekspozita &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; pun&euml; n&euml; zhvillim e cila do t&euml; p&euml;soj&euml; ndryshme dhe transformim gjat&euml; gjith&euml; koh&euml;zgjatjes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Organizuar me mb&euml;shtetjen e Goethe-Zentrum Tiran&euml;, pjes&euml; e programit Tetori Gjerman.</p>', NULL, NULL);
