INSERT INTO `category_translations` (`id`, `category_id`, `locale`, `description`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1, 1, 'en', '<p>In this category, we have gathered projects linked with memory and remembrance. Projects that, like waves transmit a certain content, transporting past elements into the present by creating moments of confrontation. The circular and repetitive motion of waves causes a disturbance or variation interfering with and influencing the given reality.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(2, 1, 'al', '<p>N&euml; kategorin &ldquo;Dallg&euml;t&rdquo; kemi mbledhur projekte t&euml; lidhura me memorien dhe kujtimet. Projekte te cilat po ashtu si dallg&euml;t p&euml;rcjellin nj&euml; p&euml;rmbajtje t&euml; caktuar, duke transportuar element&euml; t&euml; s&euml; shkuar&euml;s n&euml; t&euml; tashmen e duke krijuar k&euml;shtu momente p&euml;rballjeje. L&euml;vizja rrethore dhe e p&euml;rs&euml;ritur e dallg&euml;ve shkakton nj&euml; shqet&euml;sim ose ndryshim q&euml; nd&euml;rhyn dhe ndikon n&euml; realitetin ashtu sic &euml;sht&euml;.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(3, 2, 'en', '<p>A Fata Morgana is an optical phenomenon caused by atmospheric conditions, creating a form of mirage appearing above the sea horizon but can be seen on land too. In this archive, Fata Morgana stands for projects whose approach is oriented towards transformation and experimentation. With the intention to modify and reshape the way one looks at and experiences the given reality.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(4, 2, 'al', '<p>Nj&euml; Fata Morgana &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; fenomen optik i shkaktuar nga kushtet atmosferike, i cili krijon nj&euml; form&euml; mirazhi q&euml; shfaqet mbi horizontin e detit, por q&euml;&nbsp;mund t&euml; shihet edhe n&euml; tok&euml;. N&euml; k&euml;t&euml; arkiv, kategoria &ldquo;Fata Morgana&rdquo; p&euml;rmbledh ato projekte, qasja e t&euml; cilave &euml;sht&euml; e orientuar drejt transformimit dhe eksperimentimit. Me synimin p&euml;r t&euml; modifikuar dhe riformuar m&euml;nyr&euml;n se si njeriu e shikon dhe p&euml;rjeton realitetin.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(5, 3, 'en', '<p>Following the rising level of the sea with the high tide, this category includes works that bring forward a proposal. Proposals come in all sorts of expressions from a desire to rage. Like the rising water movement, these projects manifest their presence interrupting and menacing the &ldquo;norm&quot;.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(6, 3, 'al', '<p>Duke ndjekur rritjen e nivelit t&euml; detit gjat&euml; batic&euml;s, n&euml; kategorin &ldquo;Batic&euml;&rdquo; p&euml;rfshihen ato punime t&euml; cilat sjellin nj&euml; propozim. Propozime q&euml; vijn&euml; me nj&euml; shumllojshm&euml;ri shprehish, nga d&euml;shira n&euml; t&euml;rbim. Ashtu si l&euml;vizja e rritjes s&euml; ujit, k&euml;to projekte manifestojn&euml; pranin&euml; e tyre duke nd&euml;rprer&euml; dhe k&euml;rc&euml;nuar &quot;norm&euml;n&quot;.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(7, 4, 'en', '<p>A maelstrom is a powerful whirlpool of water produced by opposing currents or a current running into an obstacle and it is often regarded also as an oceanic black hole. Given the maelstrom&rsquo;s potent and unpredictable character, this category is dedicated to projects with a direct and confrontational impact. Using their actions to protest and refuse the order of things, these projects come as forms of critique and resistance.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(8, 4, 'al', '<p>Maelstrom &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; vorbull e fuqishme uji e prodhuar nga rrymat e kund&euml;rta ose nj&euml; rrym&euml; q&euml; kalon n&euml; nj&euml; penges&euml;, e cila shpesh konsiderohet si nj&euml; vrim&euml; e zez&euml; oqeanike. Duke pasur parasysh karakterin e fuqish&euml;m dhe t&euml; paparashikuesh&euml;m t&euml; vorbull&euml;s, kategoria &ldquo;Vorbull&rdquo; i dedikohet projekteve te cilat synojn&euml; nj&euml; ndikim t&euml; drejtp&euml;rdrejt&euml; dhe konfrontues. Duke p&euml;rdorur veprimet e tyre p&euml;r t&euml; protestuar dhe refuzuar rendin e gj&euml;rave, k&euml;to projekte vijn&euml; si forma t&euml; kritik&euml;s dhe rezistenc&euml;s.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(9, 5, 'en', '<p>This category of the archive includes projects which have the ability to maintain a light, almost funny approach even when dealing with serious issues. Just like the sea breeze pierces through the heat, characterized by a gentle and playful feeling, these projects also penetrate the public space with irony.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(10, 5, 'al', '<p>Kategoria &ldquo;Fllad Deti&rdquo; e arkivit p&euml;rfshin projekte t&euml; cilat kan&euml; aft&euml;sin&euml; e nj&euml; qasjeje t&euml; leht&euml;, ndonj&euml;her&euml; edhe tall&euml;se, pavarsisht se kan&euml; t&euml; b&euml;jn&euml; me &ccedil;&euml;shtje serioze. Ashtu si era e detit p&euml;rshkon brend&euml;sin&euml; e vap&euml;s, e karakterizuar nga nj&euml; ndjenj&euml; e but&euml; dhe lozonjare, edhe k&euml;to projekte dep&euml;rtojn&euml; me ironi n&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml;n publike.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(11, 6, 'en', '<p>During a low tide, the coast exposes what is usually covered with water, creating a powerful effect of revelation. Inspired by such a context, this category includes projects aiming at disclosing and denouncing, telling the truth for the sake of the public good.</p>', NULL, NULL),
