INSERT INTO `project_translations` (`id`, `project_id`, `locale`, `description`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1, 1, 'en', '<p>This work derives from a contemplation of the Pyramid (Piramida), a pyramid-shaped building which was built in 1987 with the intention to become a funeral mausoleum for the ex-dictator Enver Hoxha. After the fall of the dictatorship, the Pyramid had many other functions, but it never became what it was meant to be. Back in 2011, the Albanian parliament decided to demolish the building; their idea was to replace it with a new, modern building housing the Albanian parliament. After hearing about such an attempt from the government, Romano &amp; &Ccedil;obo reflected on the fact that the wish to demolish one of the few remaining monuments of socialist architecture in Albania was a clear sign of the need to forget at all costs the past, without having first metabolised it. Such actions were and are often manifested in the Albanian context and they are mostly present in the approach towards history. Romano&rsquo;s and Cobo&rsquo;s collaboration developed from this idea into a performance which consisted in climbing the Pyramid and rolling out a long sheet of white paper with the word &ldquo;Histeri&rdquo; (hysteria) written on it in red. Such word makes a reference to the artists&rsquo; idea and intention because only in one letter in Albanian changes in the word &ldquo;Histori&rdquo; (history) from &ldquo;Histeri&rdquo; (hysteria). &ldquo;Hist&oelig;ri removing&rdquo; aims to provoke a reflection on the relationship Albania has with its own history, which sometimes has appeared to be irrational, absurd and even hysterical.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Stefano Romano born 1975 in Italy, is a visual artist based between Albania and Italy. His practice explores the deep contradictions that lie in social realities, often investigated in relation to architectural and urban, historical and contemporary contexts. Romano&#39;s work translates into temporary actions, performances, installations, video and photographic works built according to a rigid grammatical structure capable of always generating unexpected situations and a flexible temporary structure. Some of his solo shows &amp; performances include: Columns curated by Claudia Santeroni, Paper Gallery, Prishtina, Kosovo; Monumenti impermanenti curated by Gabi Scardi, Fondazione Adolfo Pini, Milan, Italy; Study for a Monument, performance in Thessaloniki, part of SKG Bridges Festival 2019, Thessaloniki, Greece; Axis Mundi Trilogy, film premiere, Millennium Cinema, Tirana, Albania; RGB, Zeta Gallery, Tirana, Albania; Quarto movimento - performance for a single person, Metropol theater, Tirana, Albania; There must be something in between, afo - architekturforum ober&ouml;sterreich, Linz, Austria; a Manifesto; Tulla Culture Center, Tirana, Albania; Post fata resurgo - Performance in the frame of ArtDate - Dialogo nel tempo as DZT collective, Palazzo della Misericordia, Bergamo, Italy; HIST&OElig;RI removing, UpperLab, Bergamo, Italy; memoria collettiva, microgallery - portable gallery in miniature, c/o The Office - contemporary art affair, Tirana, Albania and many more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Eriselda &Ccedil;obo born 1979 in Fier, Albania is an experienced planning and urban management professional with several years of experience in territorial development and institutional administration. In the role of the Urban Planning and Regional Development Expert she gave a direct contribution on drafting the Territorial Planning legislation, and also technical Manuals, for implementing the relevant legislation from 2010 to 2012. Between 2005 and 2016 she was involved as territorial planner in designing the Local General Plans of several Albanian municipalities, such as: Tirana, Kor&ccedil;a, Fier, Librazhd, Prrenjas, C&euml;rrik, etc. Furthermore has experience as Guest Lecturer for the courses of: Territorial Planning and Urban Legislation at private universities as Albanian University from 2012 to 2013 and public ones in Albania as Faculty of Architecture and Urban Planning from 2017 to date. She has been engaged for more than 10 years in the public administration in Albania: during 2005 - 2010 in the role of Deputy Mayor of Fier municipality for urban planning and public services issues, also from 2016 to date she holds the position of National Coordinator for strategic projects in the Department of Development and Good Governance within the Prime Minister&rsquo;s Office. In addition to her primary profession she is co-founder of the Microgallery exhibition space and of the DZT collective, likewise co-authored several artistic projects with Stefano Romano.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(2, 1, 'al', '<p>Kjo vep&euml;r rrjedh nga nj&euml; reflektim mbi Piramid&euml;n, nj&euml; nd&euml;rtes&euml; n&euml; form&euml; piramide e cila u nd&euml;rtua n&euml; vitin 1987 me q&euml;llimin p&euml;r t&#39;u kthyer n&euml; nj&euml; mauzoleum p&euml;r ish diktatorin Enver Hoxha. Pas r&euml;nies s&euml; diktatur&euml;s, Piramida pati shum&euml; funksione t&euml; tjera, por nuk u b&euml; kurr&euml; ajo q&euml; duhej t&euml; ishte sipas projektimit fillestar. N&euml; vitin 2011, parlamenti shqiptar vendosi prishjen e godin&euml;s; ideja e tyre ishte ta z&euml;vend&euml;sonin Piramid&euml;n me nj&euml; nd&euml;rtes&euml; t&euml; re dhe moderne, ku do t&euml; zhvendosej parlamenti shqiptar. Romano &amp; &Ccedil;obo, pasi d&euml;gjuan p&euml;r nj&euml; p&euml;rpjekje t&euml; till&euml; nga qeveria, reflektuan mbi faktin se d&euml;shira p&euml;r t&euml; prishur nj&euml; nga t&euml; paktat monumente t&euml; mbetura t&euml; arkitektur&euml;s socialiste n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri ishte nj&euml; shenj&euml; e qart&euml; e nevoj&euml;s p&euml;r t&euml; harruar me &ccedil;do kusht t&euml; shkuar&euml;n, pa patur fillimisht mund&euml;sin&euml; p&euml;r ta kuptuar dhe p&euml;rballur at&euml;. Veprime t&euml; tilla jan&euml; shfaqur dhe vazhdojn&euml; t&euml; shfaqen shpesh n&euml; kontekstin shqiptar dhe jan&euml; m&euml; s&euml; shumti t&euml; pranishme n&euml; qasjen ndaj historis&euml;. Bashk&euml;punimi mes Romanos dhe &Ccedil;obos nisi nga kjo ide per tu zhvilluar n&euml; nj&euml; performanc&euml; q&euml; konsistonte n&euml; ngjitjen e Piramid&euml;s dhe rrokullisjen e nj&euml; flet&euml; t&euml; gjat&euml; letre t&euml; bardh&euml; me fjal&euml;n &quot;Histeri&quot; (histeri) t&euml; shkruar me ngjyr&euml; t&euml; kuqe. Nj&euml; fjal&euml; e till&euml; i referohet ides&euml; dhe synimit t&euml; artist&euml;ve, sepse n&euml; gjuh&euml;n shqipe vet&euml;m n&euml; nj&euml; shkronj&euml; ndryshojn&euml; fjal&euml;t &quot;Histori&quot; dhe &quot;Histeri&quot;. &ldquo;Hist&oelig;ri Removing&rdquo; synon t&euml; provokoj&euml; nj&euml; reflektim mbi marr&euml;dh&euml;nien q&euml; ka Shqip&euml;ria me vet&euml; historin&euml; e saj, e cila ndonj&euml;her&euml; &euml;sht&euml; shfaqur si irracionale, absurde dhe madje histerike.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Stefano Romano i lindur m&euml; 1975 n&euml; Itali, &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; artist pamor q&euml; jeton e punon &nbsp;n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri dhe Itali. Praktika e tij eksploron kontradiktat e thella q&euml; q&euml;ndrojn&euml; n&euml; realitetet shoq&euml;rore, shpesh t&euml; hulumtuara n&euml; lidhje me kontekstet arkitekturore dhe urbane, historike dhe bashk&euml;kohore. Puna e Romanos p&euml;rkthehet n&euml; nd&euml;rhyrje t&euml; p&euml;rkohshme, performanca, instalacione, video dhe fotografike t&euml; nd&euml;rtuara sipas nj&euml; strukture gramatikore t&euml; fort&euml; t&euml; aft&euml; p&euml;r t&euml; gjeneruar gjithmon&euml; situata t&euml; papritura dhe nj&euml; struktur&euml; t&euml; p&euml;rkohshme fleksib&euml;l. Disa nga ekspozitat dhe performancat e tij personale p&euml;rfshijn&euml;: Columns, Paper Gallery, Prishtina, Kosovo; Monumenti impermanenti, Fondazione Adolfo Pini, Milan, Italy; Study for a Monument, performanc&euml; n&euml; Thessaloniki, pjes&euml; e SKG Bridges Festival 2019, Thessaloniki, Greece; Axis Mundi Trilogy, premier&euml;, Millennium Cinema, Tirana, Albania; RGB, Zeta Gallery, Tirana, Albania; Quarto movimento, Metropol theater, Tirana, Albania; There must be something in between, afo - architekturforum ober&ouml;sterreich, Linz, Austria; a Manifesto; Tulla Culture Center, Tirana, Albania; Post fata resurgo - Performanc&euml; n&euml; kuadrin e ArtDate - Dialogo nel tempo as DZT collective, Palazzo della Misericordia, Bergamo, Italy; HIST&OElig;RI removing, UpperLab, Bergamo, Italy; memoria collettiva, microgallery - portable gallery in miniature, c/o The Office - contemporary art affair, Tirana, Albania e shum&euml; t&euml; tjera.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Eriselda &Ccedil;obo e lindur n&euml; vitin 1979 n&euml; Fier, Shqip&euml;ri &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; profesioniste n&euml; planifikim dhe menaxhim urban me p&euml;rvoj&euml; disavje&ccedil;are n&euml; zhvillimin e territorit dhe administrimin institucional. N&euml; rolin e Ekspertes s&euml; Planifikimit Urban dhe Zhvillimit Rajonal, ajo dha nj&euml; kontribut t&euml; drejtp&euml;rdrejt&euml; n&euml; hartimin e legjislacionit t&euml; Planifikimit t&euml; Territorit, si dhe Manualeve teknike, p&euml;r zbatimin e legjislacionit p&euml;rkat&euml;s nga viti 2010 deri n&euml; vitin 2012. Nga viti 2005 deri n&euml; 2016 &euml;sht&euml; p&euml;rfshir&euml; si planifikuese territori n&euml; hartimin e Planeve t&euml; P&euml;rgjithshme Vendore t&euml; disa bashkive shqiptare si: Tiran&euml;, Kor&ccedil;&euml;, Fier, Librazhd, Prrenjas, C&euml;rrik, etj. Gjithashtu ka p&euml;rvoj&euml; si Pedagog i ftuar p&euml;r l&euml;nd&euml;t: Planifikimi i Territorit dhe Legjislacioni Urban n&euml; universitetet private si Albanian University nga viti 2012 deri n&euml; 2013 dhe ato publike n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri si Fakulteti i Arkitektur&euml;s dhe Urbanistik&euml;s nga viti 2017 deri m&euml; sot. Ajo &euml;sht&euml; e angazhuar p&euml;r m&euml; shum&euml; se 10 vjet n&euml; administrat&euml;n publike n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri: gjat&euml; viteve 2005 - 2010 n&euml; rolin e n&euml;nkryetares s&euml; Bashkis&euml; Fier p&euml;r &ccedil;&euml;shtjet e planifikimit urban dhe sh&euml;rbimeve publike, gjithashtu nga viti 2016 e deri m&euml; sot ajo mban pozicionin e Koordinatores Komb&euml;tare p&euml;r projektet strategjike n&euml; Departamentin e Zhvillimit dhe Qeverisjes s&euml; Mir&euml; pran&euml; Kryeministris&euml;. P&euml;rve&ccedil; profesionit t&euml; saj par&euml;sor, ajo &euml;sht&euml; bashk&euml;themeluese e hap&euml;sir&euml;s ekspozuese Microgallery dhe e kolektivit DZT, gjithashtu bashk&euml;autore e disa projekteve artistike me Stefano Romano.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(3, 2, 'en', '<p><a href=\"https://tiranatimecapsule.beyondmatter.eu\">Tirana Time Capsule #2</a> is a browser-based virtual environment created using 3d scans and sound recordings from Kombinat, one of the peripheral neighborhoods in the south-west of Tirana. This neighborhood takes its name from the Textile Kombinat &ldquo;Stalin&rdquo;, built in the beginning of 50s with the support of the Soviet Union. Until then empty and not inhabited, the area developed into an industrial city where the workers lived and worked. With the end of Communism, all the state-owned factories were closed, abandoned, and destined to decay. With the free movement of citizens and internal migration that followed, the various factory buildings were partly privatized and partly turned into living spaces and subsequently occupied. The current plan of the Albanian Government foresees a revitalization of the Kombinat area, with the intention to demolish almost all the industrial building complexes and build new living spaces and art institutions. This would inevitably mean the displacement of the current inhabitants and small businesses within the industrial buildings. Tirana Time Capsule #2 is created by Alex Walmsley using distinctive details brought together in a non-hierarchical and anachronistic approach. The work&nbsp;investigates&nbsp;the ways in which high-fidelity digital recording techniques appropriate and reconstructs public space in the virtual sphere and through subjective remaking can become a space where personal memory and community heritage merge. Visuals and sound, edited and rearranged from an individual and subjective point of view, capture a &ldquo;reality&rdquo; that will not only drastically change but threatens to be erased soon enough. This work was produced during his residency at Tirana Art Lab as part of Beyond Matter collaborative project.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\nAlexander Walmsley born in 1992 is an artist and programmer with a background in anthropology and archaeology. He works with a range of media and tools, including photography, photogrammetry, 3D, VR, cartography, and audio field recordings. In his practice, he is broadly interested in how image-making technologies shape and mediate architecture and landscapes in both the virtual and physical worlds. Recent and upcoming exhibitions include the Sharjah Art Foundation, The Photographers&rsquo; Gallery, Glasgow Science Centre, VRHam!, Kara Agora Art and Research Centre, and the Kunstquartier Bethanien. Alongside his own practice, he is also currently a research associate at the Film University Konrad Wolf in Potsdam, Germany.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(4, 2, 'al', '<p><a href=\"https://tiranatimecapsule.beyondmatter.eu\">Kapsula Kohore e Tiran&euml;s #2</a> &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; mjedis virtual i krijuar nga skanime 3D dhe regjistrime zanore nga Kombinati, nj&euml; nga lagjet periferike n&euml; jugper&euml;ndim t&euml; Tiran&euml;s. Kjo lagje e ka marr&euml; emrin nga Kombinati i Tekstileve &ldquo;Stalin&rdquo;, i nd&euml;rtuar n&euml; fillim t&euml; viteve &lsquo;50 me mb&euml;shtetjen e Bashkimit Sovjetik. Deri at&euml;her&euml; e zbraz&euml;t dhe e pabanuar, zona u shnd&euml;rrua n&euml; nj&euml; qytet industrial ku jetonin dhe punonin pun&euml;tor&euml;t. Me fundin e komunizmit t&euml; gjitha fabrikat shtet&euml;rore u mbyll&euml;n, u braktis&euml;n dhe u shkat&euml;rruan. Me l&euml;vizjen e lir&euml; t&euml; qytetar&euml;ve dhe emigrimin e brendsh&euml;m q&euml; pasoi, nd&euml;rtesat e ndryshme t&euml; fabrikave u privatizuan pjes&euml;risht dhe nj&euml; pjes&euml; u kthyen n&euml; hap&euml;sira banimi q&euml; m&euml; pas u uzurpuan duke u kthyer n&euml; vendbanime. Plani aktual i Qeveris&euml; Shqiptare parashikon rivitalizimin e zon&euml;s s&euml; Kombinatit, q&euml; do t&euml; sjelli si rrjedhoj&euml; prishjen e &nbsp;pothuajse t&euml; gjitha komplekseve e nd&euml;rtesave industriale, p&euml;r t&euml; nd&euml;rtuar hap&euml;sira t&euml; reja banimi dhe institucione arti. Kjo do t&euml; n&euml;nkuptonte n&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml; t&euml; pashmangshme zhvendosjen e banor&euml;ve aktual&euml; dhe t&euml; bizneseve t&euml; vogla brenda nd&euml;rtesave industriale. Kapsula Kohore e Tiran&euml;s #2 &euml;sht&euml; krijuar nga Alex Walmsley duke p&euml;rdorur detaje dalluese t&euml; zun&euml;s t&euml; sjella bashk&euml; n&euml; nj&euml; qasje johierarkike dhe anakronike. Puna heton m&euml;nyrat n&euml; t&euml; cilat teknikat me besnik&euml;ri t&euml; lart&euml; t&euml; regjistrimit dixhital p&euml;rshtasin dhe rind&euml;rtojn&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml;n publike n&euml; sfer&euml;n virtuale. P&euml;rmes rind&euml;rtimit subjektive kjo pun&euml; arrin t&euml; krijojn&euml; nj&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml; t&euml; re ​​ku kujtesa personale dhe trash&euml;gimia kollektive bashkohen. Imazhet dhe tingujt, t&euml; redaktuar dhe riorganizuar nga nj&euml; k&euml;ndv&euml;shtrim individual dhe subjektiv, kapin nj&euml; &quot;realitet&quot; q&euml; jo vet&euml;m do t&euml; ndryshoj&euml; n&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml; drastike, por rrezikon t&euml; zhduket mjaft shpejt. Kjo pun&euml; u realizua gjat&euml; q&euml;ndrimit t&euml; tij n&euml; rezidenc&euml; n&euml; Tirana Art Lab si pjes&euml; e projektit bashk&euml;punues Beyond Matter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Alexander Walmsley lindur m&euml; 1992, &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; artist dhe programues me formim n&euml; antropologji dhe arkeologji. Ai punon me nj&euml; s&euml;r&euml; mediash dhe mjetesh, duke p&euml;rfshir&euml; fotografin&euml;, fotogrametrin&euml;, 3D, VR, hartografin&euml; dhe regjistrimet audio. N&euml; praktik&euml;n e tij, ai &euml;sht&euml; gjer&euml;sisht i interesuar se si teknologjit&euml; e krijimit t&euml; imazheve formojn&euml; dhe nd&euml;rmjet&euml;sojn&euml; arkitektur&euml;n dhe peizazhet si n&euml; bot&euml;n virtuale ashtu edhe n&euml; at&euml; fizike. Ekspozitat e fundit dhe t&euml; ardhshme p&euml;rfshijn&euml; Tirana Art Lab; Fondacionin e Artit Sharjah; Galerin&euml; e Fotograf&euml;ve; Qendr&euml;n Shkencore t&euml; Glasgout; VRHam!; Qendr&euml;n e Artit dhe K&euml;rkimit Kara Agora dhe Kunstquartier Bethanien. Krahas praktik&euml;s s&euml; tij, ai aktualisht &euml;sht&euml; gjithashtu k&euml;rkues i asociuar n&euml; Universitetin e Filmit Konrad Wolf n&euml; Potsdam, Gjermani.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(5, 3, 'en', '<p>In March 2005 Cenaliaj stood motionless, painted all in white, in a statue pose on what was once the pedestal of the statue of Stalin, in front of the Textile Kombinat. The Textile Kombinat was built in the early 1950s with the support of the Soviet Union and was named after Stalin. Like many other monuments from the socialist era, the statue of Stalin was removed at the beginning of the 1990s. In this intervention, the artist&#39;s body becomes a post-socialist living sculpture, which instead of identifying with the leader, now embodies the worker. Her performance, which lasted for about 40 minutes, served as a hymn for the circumstances of the working class in contemporary capitalist Albania. Even if the symbolism comes from the past, Cenaliaj draws attention to the current working conditions, by making parallelism of two diverse periods, while believing herself that working conditions have just gotten worse.<br />\r\nCenaliaj&rsquo;s performance &ldquo;Welcome dear workers&rdquo; took place in March 2005, as part of the event &ldquo;1:60 Insurgent Space&rdquo; curated by Stefano Romano.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\nEnisa Cenaliaj born 1978 in Tirana, Albania. In 2001 she graduated in Conceptual Art at the Academy of Fine Arts in Tirana. She has been announced the winner of the Marubi International Photography Exhibition, Tirana, Albania, and the Winner of the Second Prize in the International Visual Arts Competition Onufri - Performing the East, Tirana, Albania.&nbsp;She has participated in the following events: Critique of pure image - Exhibition between forgery and citation curated by Dimitrina Sevova; AMC T.I.C.A Award for Contemporary Art; International Exhibition within the Cross-Border Experience curated by Katja Kobolt, Cross Border Experience Project / The Peace Institute, Ljubljana, and many other collective exhibitions. From 2017 to 2020 she has been part of EKPHRASIS STUDIO - Arts Management &amp; Creative Industries in Tirana.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(6, 3, 'al', '<p>N&euml; mars t&euml; vitit 2005 Cenaliaj q&euml;ndroi pal&euml;vizur, e lyer e gjitha&nbsp;m&euml; t&euml; bardh&euml;, duke marr&euml; poz&euml;n e nj&euml; statuje mbi at&euml; q&euml; dikur ishte piedestali i statuj&euml;s s&euml; Stalinit, p&euml;rball&euml; Kombinatit t&euml; Tekstileve. Kombinati i Tekstileve u nd&euml;rtua n&euml; fillim t&euml; viteve 1950 me mb&euml;shtetjen e Bashkimit Sovjetik dhe mori emrin e Stalinit n&euml; nder t&euml; tij. Si shum&euml; monumente t&euml; tjera t&euml; epok&euml;s socialiste, statuja e Stalinit u hoq n&euml; fillim t&euml; viteve 1990. N&euml; k&euml;t&euml; nd&euml;rhyrje trupi i artistes shnd&euml;rrohet n&euml; nj&euml; skulptur&euml; t&euml;&nbsp;gjall&euml; postsocialiste, e cila n&euml; vend q&euml; t&euml; identifikohet me liderin, mish&euml;ron pun&euml;torin. Performanca e saj, e cila zgjati rreth 40 minuta, sh&euml;rbeu si nj&euml; himn p&euml;r rrethanat e klas&euml;s pun&euml;tore n&euml; Shqip&euml;rin&euml; kapitaliste bashk&euml;kohore. Edhe n&euml;se simbolika vjen nga e kaluara, Cenaliaj t&euml;rheq v&euml;mendjen p&euml;r kushtet aktuale t&euml; pun&euml;s, duke b&euml;r&euml; nj&euml; paraleliz&euml;m t&euml; dy periudhave t&euml; ndryshme, nd&euml;rkoh&euml; q&euml; vete artistja &euml;sht&euml; e mendimit se kushtet e pun&euml;s sa vijn&euml; e p&euml;rkeqsohen. Performanca e Cenaliajt &ldquo;Mir&euml; se vini pun&euml;tor&euml; t&euml; dashur &rdquo; ndodhi n&euml; mars 2005, si pjes&euml; e eventit &ldquo;1:60 Insurgent Space&rdquo; kuruar nga Stefano Romano.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Enisa Cenaliaj lindi m&euml; 1978 n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. N&euml; vitin 2001 u diplomua p&euml;r Art Konceptual n&euml; Akademin&euml; e Arteve t&euml; Bukura n&euml; Tiran&euml;. Ajo &euml;sht&euml; shpallur fituese e Ekspozit&euml;s Nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tare t&euml; Fotografis&euml; Marubi, Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri dhe Fituese e &Ccedil;mimit t&euml; Dyt&euml; n&euml; Konkursin Nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar t&euml; Arteve Pamore Onufri - Performing the East, Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. Ajo ka marr&euml; pjes&euml; n&euml; ngjarjet e m&euml;poshtme: Critique of Pure Image - Between Fake and Quotation Exhibition kuruar nga Dimitrina Sevova; T.I.C.A &nbsp;AMC Contemporary Art Prize; International Exhibition in the framework of the Cross Border Experience kuruar nga Katja Kobolt, organizuar nga Cross Border Experience Project, The Peace Institute, Ljubljana and shume ekspozita te tjera kolektive. Nga viti 2017 n&euml; vitin 2020 ajo ka qen&euml; pjese e EKPHRASIS STUDIO - Arts Management &amp; Creative Industries n&euml; Tiran&euml;.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(7, 4, 'en', '<p>The 8th of April is International Roma Day. On this occasion, Kazanxhiu, whose central part of research mostly deals with the condition of being a Rromani Albanian artist, creates and installs 8 large tractor wheels with the color of the Romani flag in front of the Albanian Parliament Building. As Kazanxhiu&rsquo;s work &quot;8 for 8th of April&quot; wants to provoke and challenge the traditional perception about the Romani people in Albania, the choice of installing them in front of such institution is a symbolic protest, trying to give visibility to the Roma community; a community that is part of the everyday life in Albania, but whose problems, culture and social dynamics are still largely undiscovered as a cause of prejudice. The artist himself sees this installation as a form of resistance to challenging the traditional perception of cultural resistance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Sead Kazanxhiu born in 1987 in Fier, Albania, lives and works in Tirana, Albania.&nbsp;He was trained as a painter at the University of Arts in Tirana from 2006 to 2010, where he obtained his Bachelor Degree. Following his studies, he continued to work primarily in&nbsp;the medium of painting, whereas his more recent practice has expanded into sculpture, installation, video, and public space interventions.&nbsp;With nine personal shows since 2012 in Tirana, Budapest, and Brussels, and numerous group exhibitions in Tirana, Prague, Brno, Gothenburg, Berlin, Drezden, Motovun, Krakow, Bucharest, and New Orleans, Sarawak Malaysia, Kazanxhiu remains one of the most engaged younger protagonists in contemporary Albanian cultural scene. His uncompromising position with regard to unfair treatment of the Roma ethnic group presents but a platform to voice individual dissent about the racially biased dynamics that, unfortunately, continues to shape contemporary European worldviews &ndash; on a daily basis, inside and outside of official political arenas. In this sense, his image-making contributes to the positive efforts of a single artist to restore the dignity of a community forcefully and unjustly cornered at the outskirts of European democracy. Currently, he is a PAKIV board member of the European Roma Institute for Art and Culture and a Deputy Chairman of the State Committee for National Minorities in Albania.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(8, 4, 'al', '<p>8 Prilli &euml;sht&euml; Dita Nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tare e Rom&euml;ve. P&euml;r k&euml;t&euml; rast, artisti Kazanxhiu krijoi dhe instaloi 8 rrota t&euml; m&euml;dha traktori pikturuar me ngjyr&euml;n e flamurit Rom p&euml;rpara nd&euml;rtes&euml;s s&euml; Kuvendit t&euml; Shqip&euml;ris&euml;. Nj&euml; pjes&euml; e mir&euml; e praktik&euml;s artistike dhe pun&euml;s k&euml;rkimore t&euml; Kazanxhiut fokusohet pik&euml;risht mbi situat&euml;n e t&euml; q&euml;nurit nj&euml; artist shqiptar rom. Duke qen&euml; se vepra e Kazanxhiut &quot;8 p&euml;r 8 Prillin&quot; d&euml;shiron t&euml; provokoj&euml; dhe sfidoj&euml; perceptimin tradicional p&euml;r rom&euml;t n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri, zgjedhja e vendosjes s&euml; saj p&euml;rball&euml; nj&euml; institucioni si Kuvendi i Shqiperise &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; protest&euml; simbolike. Kjo protest&euml; p&euml;rpiqet t&#39;i jap&euml; vizibilitet komunitetit rom; nj&euml; komunitet i cili &euml;sht&euml; pjes&euml; e realitetit dhe p&euml;rditshmeris&euml; n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri por mbetet ende shum&euml; i paragjykuar. P&euml;r shkak t&euml; k&euml;tyre paragjykimeve, problemet, kultura dhe dinamikat e tyre shoq&euml;rore jan&euml; ende t&euml; pazbuluara. Vet&euml; artisti e sheh k&euml;t&euml; instalacion si nj&euml; form&euml; rezistence ndaj sfidimit t&euml; perceptimit tradicional t&euml; rezistenc&euml;s kulturore.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Sead Kazanxhiu i lindur m&euml; 1987 n&euml; Fier, Shqip&euml;ri, jeton dhe punon n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. Ka studiur piktur&euml; n&euml; Universitetin e Arteve n&euml; Tiran&euml; nga viti 2006 deri n&euml; vitin 2010, ku ka marr&euml; Diplom&euml;n Bachelor. Pas studimeve, ai vazhdoi t&euml; punoj&euml; kryesisht n&euml; mediumin e piktur&euml;s, nd&euml;rsa praktika e tij s&euml; fundmi &euml;sht&euml; zgjeruar n&euml; skulptur&euml;, instalacion, video dhe nd&euml;rhyrje n&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml;n publike. Me n&euml;nt&euml; ekspozita personale q&euml; nga viti 2012 n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Budapest dhe Bruksel dhe ekspozita t&euml; shumta kolektive n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Prag&euml;, Brno, G&ouml;teborg, Berlin, Drezden, Motovun, Krakov, Bukuresht, New Orleans, Sarawak Malajzi; Kazanxhiu mbetet nj&euml; nga t&euml; rinjt&euml; m&euml; t&euml; angazhuar protagonist&euml; n&euml; sken&euml;n kulturore bashk&euml;kohore shqiptare. Pozicioni i tij i pakompromis n&euml; lidhje me trajtimin e padrejt&euml; t&euml; grupit etnik rom paraqet vet&euml;m nj&euml; platform&euml; p&euml;r t&euml; shprehur mospajtimin individual p&euml;r dinamik&euml;n e nj&euml;anshme racore q&euml;, p&euml;r fat t&euml; keq, vazhdon t&euml; form&euml;soj&euml; bot&euml;kuptimet bashk&euml;kohore evropiane &ndash; n&euml; baza ditore, brenda dhe jasht&euml; arenave politike zyrtare. N&euml; k&euml;t&euml; kuptim, krijimi i imazhit t&euml; tij kontribuon n&euml; p&euml;rpjekjet pozitive t&euml; nj&euml; artisti t&euml; vet&euml;m p&euml;r t&euml; rikthyer dinjitetin e nj&euml; komuniteti t&euml; vendosur me forc&euml; dhe padrejt&euml;sisht n&euml; periferi t&euml; demokracis&euml; evropiane. Aktualisht ai &euml;sht&euml; an&euml;tar bordi i PAKIV i Institutit Evropian t&euml; Rom&euml;ve p&euml;r Art dhe Kultur&euml; dhe Z&euml;vend&euml;s Kryetar i Komitetit Shtet&euml;ror p&euml;r Pakicat Komb&euml;tare n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(9, 5, 'en', '<p>The&nbsp;work &quot;Aftermoments&quot; is deeply connected with the artist&#39;s personal and intimate background as the technique used to produce it is a craft method she inherited from her grandmother who was a tailor. Konstandini decides to reinvent such technique into a composition of rags that correspond to photographic pixels, in order to create the mirage of an image. The final textile works are quite large and create the perception of a zoomed photograph; the feeling one can sense is that of the artist zooming in and allowing you into her intimacy, into her personal memory. The way of exhibiting the artist chooses for these artworks, opens up reflections about the personal/private context. Kostandini asks her neighbors if she can hang/exhibit her works outside their balconies, as they were clothes drying on wires. With such an action she confuses the public about what is private and what is public, what is personal, and what is shared. From the many questions this work raises, the artist asks one which is very predominant: &ldquo;How much can we push the boundaries of intimacy, how can we introduce one another&rsquo;s life in the public space?&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Ledia&nbsp;Kostandini born 1983 in Pogradec, Albania lives and works in Tirana, Albania.&nbsp;A graduate of the University of Arts, Tirana, her practice spans over diverse media, including photography, painting, installation, public interventions, and illustration. Her work refers to social transformations, the inherited or lost culture.&nbsp;She is interested in contemporary habits by associating them with archaic, obsolete&nbsp;objects, places, or venues.&nbsp;&ldquo;Identity on transition&rdquo; is her focal subject. She uses parallelism, comparison, and juxtapositions in order to reveal paradoxical situations.&nbsp;Her works try to provoke ambiguous emotions, mingling imagination, curiosity, and humor.&nbsp;Her work has been exhibited internationally and locally. Her solo shows include:&nbsp;&Ccedil;entro Estetike, Miza Gallery, Tirana; &nbsp;Blockwork, Tulla Culture Center, Tirana; Let Us Meet in Between, Bazament Art Space, Tirana; I Look at Them They Look Back at Me, Private Print Studio, Skopje. She has participated in numerous group exhibitions in Albania, Germany, France, Austria, etc.&nbsp;She was awarded the Ardhje Award in 2012. She has attended AiR programs in New York and Croatia.&nbsp;She is a freelance&nbsp;illustrator since 2008. Actually, she works as an Art Professor at Polis University.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(10, 5, 'al', '<p>Pun&euml; &quot;Pas Momenteve&quot; &euml;sht&euml; e lidhur thell&euml;sisht me dimensionin personal dhe intim t&euml; artistes pasi teknika e p&euml;rdorur p&euml;r prodhimin e saj &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; metod&euml; artizanale q&euml; ajo e ka trash&euml;guar nga gjyshja e saj e cila ishte rrobaqep&euml;se. Konstandini vendos ta rip&euml;rdor nj&euml; teknik&euml; t&euml; till&euml;, n&euml; nj&euml; kompozim p&euml;lhurash q&euml; korrespondojn&euml; me pikselat fotografik&euml;, n&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml; q&euml; t&euml; krijoj&euml; mirazhin e nj&euml; imazhi. Punimet p&euml;rfundimtare t&euml; tekstilit jan&euml; mjaft t&euml; m&euml;dha dhe krijojn&euml; perceptimin e nj&euml; fotografie t&euml; zmadhuar; ajo q&euml; mund t&euml; ndjehet &euml;sht&euml; se si artistja i zmadhon q&euml;llimisht imazhet duke krijuar nje hap&euml;sir&euml; t&euml; re dhe duke lejuar qasjen n&euml; intimitetin e saj dhe n&euml; kujtes&euml;n e saj personale. M&euml;nyra e ekspozimit q&euml; artistja zgjedh p&euml;r k&euml;to vepra, &nbsp;reflekton mbi kontekstin dhe mardh&euml;njen misid personales dhe privates. Kostandini pyet fqinj&euml;t e saj n&euml;se mund t&#39;i var&euml;/ekspozoj&euml; punimet e saj jasht&euml; ballkoneve t&euml; tyre, sikur ato t&euml; ishin rroba q&euml; thaheshin varur n&euml; tel. Me nj&euml; veprim t&euml; till&euml; ajo e b&euml;n veshguesin t&euml; mendoj mbi at&euml; se &ccedil;far&euml; &euml;sht&euml; private dhe &ccedil;far&euml; &euml;sht&euml; publike, &ccedil;far&euml; &euml;sht&euml; personale dhe &ccedil;far&euml; mund t&euml; ndahet me t&euml; tjer&euml;t. Nga pyetjet e shumta q&euml; ngre kjo vep&euml;r, artistja shtron nj&euml; pyetje q&euml; &euml;sht&euml; shum&euml; e rendesishme: &ldquo;Sa mund t&#39;i zgjerojm&euml; kufijt&euml; e intimitetit, si mund ta prezantojm&euml; jet&euml;n ton&euml; n&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml;n publike?&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Ledia Kostandini e &nbsp;lindur m&euml; 1983 n&euml; Pogradec, Shqip&euml;ri jeton dhe punon n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. E diplomuar n&euml; Universitetin e Arteve, Tiran&euml;, praktika e saj shtrihet n&euml; mediume t&euml; ndryshme, duke p&euml;rfshir&euml; fotografin&euml;, piktur&euml;n, instalacionin, nd&euml;rhyrjet publike dhe ilustrimin. Puna e saj i referohet transformimeve shoq&euml;rore, kultur&euml;s s&euml; trash&euml;guar apo t&euml; humbur. Ajo &euml;sht&euml; e interesuar p&euml;r zakonet bashk&euml;kohore duke i lidhur ato me objekte, hap&euml;sira ose vende arkaike, t&euml; vjet&euml;ruara. &ldquo;Identiteti n&euml; tranzicion&rdquo; &euml;sht&euml; tema kryesore e k&euml;rkimit te saj. Ajo p&euml;rdor paralelizmin, krahasimin dhe p&euml;rballjet p&euml;r t&euml; zbuluar situata paradoksale. Punimet e saj p&euml;rpiqen t&euml; provokojn&euml; emocione t&euml; paqarta, imagjinat&euml; t&euml; p&euml;rzier, kuriozitet dhe humor. Puna e saj &euml;sht&euml; ekspozuar n&euml; nivel nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar dhe komb&euml;tar. Disa ekspozita personale p&euml;rfshijn&euml;: &Ccedil;entro Estetike, Miza Gallery, Tirana; &nbsp;Blockwork, Tulla Culture Center, Tirana; Let Us Meet in Between, Bazament Art Space, Tirana; I Look at Them They Look Back at Me, Private Print Studio, Skopje. Ajo ka marr&euml; pjes&euml; n&euml; ekspozita t&euml; shumta kolektive n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri, Gjermani, Franc&euml;, Austri etj. Ajo &euml;sht&euml; vler&euml;suar me &Ccedil;mimin Ardhje n&euml; vitin 2012. Kostandini ka ndjekur programet e AirR n&euml; Nju Jork dhe Kroaci. Ajo &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; ilustratore e pavarur q&euml; nga viti 2008. Aktualisht punon si Profesore e Artit n&euml; Universitetin Polis, Tiran&euml;.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(11, 6, 'en', '<p>On the 5th of May 1942 Qemal Stafa, one of the founders of the Albanian Communist party, was killed by the Italian fascist forces, which had occupied Albania. After the end of the war, the date of his death anniversary was chosen as the Martyrs Day of Albania to commemorate all of those who lost their lives for Albanian&rsquo;s liberation. A monument, at the place where Qemal Stafa was killed, was built and still exists today on a street named &ldquo;5th of May&rdquo;, located next to the big market of the city of Tirana. The monument is surrounded by selling stands, appearing as an absurd construction in the middle of the trade center. Bujari duplicated the original monument in its original size and installed it in front of Tirana Art Lab, located in the very city center. In his intervention &ldquo;A Monument for a Monument&rdquo;, Bujari uses simple strategies of replication and relocation in order to change the context and at the same time the frame in which the monument is being taken into consideration, creating the possibility for debate and re-evaluation. Bujari&rsquo;s &ldquo;A monument for a monument&rdquo; was produced as part of the exhibition &ldquo;Double Feature #4 - Nikolin Bujari &amp; Nadja Prlja&rdquo; at Tirana Art Lab.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\nNikolin Bujari born 1984 in Shkodra, Albania lives and works in Tirana, Albania. He graduated from Tirana Art Academy in 2006 with Professor Edi Hila and was a guest student at the College of Design in Karlsruhe Germany in the Media class with Professor Mischa Kuball.&nbsp;Among others his works have been shown in exhibitions in institutions like: Badischer Kunstverein, Karlsruhe Germany; Nassauischer Kunstverein, Wiesbaden, Germany; Haus am L&uuml;tzowplatz, Berlin Germany; National Gallery of Art, Tirana Albania; 3-rd Tirana Biennale Albania, Tirana Art Lab - Center for Contemporary Art, etc.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(12, 6, 'al', '<p>M&euml; 5 maj 1942, Qemal Stafa, nj&euml; nga themeluesit e Partis&euml; Komuniste Shqiptare, u vra nga forcat fashiste italiane q&euml; kishin pushtuar Shqip&euml;rin&euml;. Pas p&euml;rfundimit t&euml; luft&euml;s, data e p&euml;rvjetorit t&euml; vdekjes s&euml; tij u zgjodh si Dita e D&euml;shmor&euml;ve t&euml; Shqip&euml;ris&euml; p&euml;r t&euml; p&euml;rkujtuar t&euml; gjith&euml; ata q&euml; humb&euml;n jet&euml;n p&euml;r &ccedil;lirimin e vendit. Nj&euml; monument u nd&euml;rtua n&euml; vendin ku u vra Qemal Stafa, i cili ekziston ende edhe sot n&euml; rrugen &ldquo;5 Maji&rdquo;, pran&euml; tregut t&euml; madh t&euml; Tiran&euml;s. Monumenti &euml;sht&euml; i rrethuar nga tezgat e shitjes; ai shfaqet si nj&euml; nd&euml;rtim absurd n&euml; mes t&euml; realitetit t&euml; tregut. Bujari rikrijoi monumentin origjinal n&euml; madh&euml;sin&euml; e tij origjinale dhe e vendosi at&euml; p&euml;rball&euml; Tirana Art Lab, q&euml; ndodhej n&euml; qend&euml;r t&euml; qytetit. Me k&euml;t&euml; nd&euml;rhyrje, Bujari p&euml;rdor strategjit e thjeshta t&euml; riprodhimit dhe zhvendosjes p&euml;r t&euml; ndryshuar kontekstin dhe n&euml; t&euml; nj&euml;jt&euml;n koh&euml; korniz&euml;n n&euml; t&euml; cil&euml;n monumenti merret n&euml; konsiderat&euml;, duke krijuar mund&euml;si p&euml;r debat dhe rivler&euml;sim. &ldquo;Nj&euml; monument p&euml;r nj&euml; monument&rdquo; u komisionua dhe ekspozua n&euml; ekspozit&euml;n &ldquo;Double Feature #4 - Nikolin Bujari &amp; Nadja Prlja&rdquo; n&euml; Tirana Art Lab.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Nikolin Bujari i lindur m&euml; 1984 n&euml; Shkod&euml;r, Shqip&euml;ri jeton dhe punon n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. Ai u diplomua n&euml; Akademin&euml; e Arteve n&euml; Tiran&euml; n&euml; vitin 2006 me profesor Edi Hila dhe ishte student i ftuar n&euml; Kolegjin e Dizajnit n&euml; Karlsruhe, Gjermani n&euml; klas&euml;n Media Art &nbsp;me profesor Mischa Kuball. Nd&euml;r t&euml; tjerash, veprat e tij jan&euml; shfaqur n&euml; ekspozita e institucione si: Badischer Kunstverein, Karlsruhe Gjermani; Nassauischer Kunstverein, Wiesbaden, Gjermani; Haus am L&uuml;tzowplatz, Berlin Gjermani; Galeria Komb&euml;tare e Arteve, Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri; Bienalja e 3-t&euml; e Tiran&euml;s n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri, Tirana Art Lab - Qendra p&euml;r Artin Bashk&euml;kohor, etj.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(13, 7, 'en', '<p>For the&nbsp;project &quot;Piramida&quot;, Blloshmi installs 2000 empty coca-cola plastic bottles on a pyramid skeleton-structure and calls it &ldquo;The Pyramid&rdquo;. Installed in front of the National Gallery of Arts, with this intervention the artist wants to represent the much-wanted power not only from politicians but from all individuals, even those belonging to the social-cultural sphere. Blloshmi sees in the crazy-shiny-plastic pyramid an escalation, the escalation of the desire for power: once you&rsquo;re on top of it, the dream is not yet fulfilled, satisfaction is still one step further, the hunting never ends. The bottles shine in their emptiness, reflecting on the empty and senseless condition of power and its influence on individuals obsessed with it. With &ldquo;Piramida&rdquo;, Blloshmi creates a show of irony and truth, causing mixed feelings to the perceiver, and unsteadiness on what one&rsquo;s supposed to truly feel about it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Lumturi Blloshmi born in 1944 in Tirana&nbsp;lived and worked in Tirana.&nbsp;Blloshmi graduated from the Painting Department at the Academy of Arts in Tirana in 1968. Between 1974 and 1985, she was not allowed to continue her creative practice. Until 2004, Blloshmi worked in several institutions, among which are the National Gallery of Arts and Institute of Cultural Monuments in Tirana. Afterward, she worked as an independent artist. Throughout her career, Blloshmi continuously exhibited. Several of her works are included in the collection of the National Gallery of Art in Tirana. Her practice between modern and contemporary art is a synthesis of installation, photography, drawing, and painting. Her works have been shown among others in the group and solo exhibitions in institutions like; Chelsea Art Museum in New York, Municipal Art Gallery of Bydgoszcz Poland, Alexandria Biennale for Mediterranean Countries Egypt, Albania National Gallery of Arts, Kosovo National Gallery of Arts. Lumturi Blloshmi passed away on 27 of November 2020 as a result of an infection with Covid-19.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(14, 7, 'al', '<p>P&euml;r projektin &quot;Piramida&quot; Blloshmi instalon 2000 shishe plastike boshe coca-cola mbi nj&euml; struktur&euml; skeleti piramidale dhe e quan &ldquo;Piramida&rdquo;. E vendosur p&euml;rball&euml; Galeris&euml; Komb&euml;tare t&euml; Arteve, me k&euml;t&euml; nd&euml;rhyrje artistja d&euml;shiron t&euml; simbolizoj&euml; pushtetin e shum&euml;k&euml;rkuar jo vet&euml;m nga politikan&euml;t, por nga t&euml; gjith&euml; individ&euml;t, madje edhe ata q&euml; i p&euml;rkasin sfer&euml;s social-kulturore. Blloshmi sheh n&euml; k&euml;t&euml; piramid&euml; t&euml; &ccedil;mendur, te shk&euml;lqyeshme e plastike nj&euml; p&euml;rshkall&euml;zim, p&euml;rshkall&euml;zimin e d&euml;shir&euml;s p&euml;r pushtet: kur dikush arrin n&euml; maj&euml; t&euml; saj kupton q&euml; &euml;ndrra ende nuk &euml;sht&euml; realizuar, q&euml; k&euml;naq&euml;sia &euml;sht&euml; ende nj&euml; hap m&euml; tej, q&euml; gjuetia nuk mbaron kurr&euml;. Shishet shk&euml;lqejn&euml; n&euml; zbraz&euml;tin&euml; e tyre, duke reflektuar mbi gj&euml;ndjen boshe dhe t&euml; pakuptimt&euml; t&euml; pushtetit dhe ndikimin e tij tek individ&euml;t e fiksuar pas tij. Me &ldquo;Piramid&euml;n&rdquo;, Blloshmi krijon nj&euml; shfaqje ironie dhe t&euml; v&euml;rtete, duke shkaktuar ndjenja t&euml; p&euml;rziera tek perceptuesi dhe nj&euml; lloj pavendosm&euml;rie p&euml;r at&euml; q&euml; duhet v&euml;rtet&euml; t&euml; ndjej&euml;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Lumturi Blloshmi u lindur n&euml; vitin 1944 n&euml; Tiran&euml;&nbsp;jetoi dhe punoi n&euml; Tiran&euml;. Blloshmi u diplomua n&euml; Deg&euml;n e Piktur&euml;s n&euml; Akademin&euml; e Arteve n&euml; Tiran&euml; n&euml; vitin 1968. Nga viti 1974 deri n&euml; 1985, ajo nuk u lejua t&euml; vazhdonte praktik&euml;n e saj krijuese. Deri n&euml; vitin 2004, Blloshmi ka punuar n&euml; disa institucione, nd&euml;r t&euml; cilat jan&euml; Galeria Komb&euml;tare e Arteve dhe Instituti i Monumenteve t&euml; Kultur&euml;s n&euml; Tiran&euml;. M&euml; pas, ajo punoi si artiste e pavarur. Nga 1985 deri n&euml; ndarjen e saj nga jeta Blloshmi ekspozoi vazhdimisht brenda dhe jasht vendit. Disa nga veprat e saj jan&euml; p&euml;rfshir&euml; n&euml; koleksionin e Galeris&euml; Komb&euml;tare t&euml; Arteve n&euml; Tiran&euml;. Praktika e saj mes artit modern dhe atij bashk&euml;kohor &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; sintez&euml; e instalacionit, fotografis&euml;, performanc&euml;s, vizatimit dhe piktur&euml;s. Punimet e saj jan&euml; shfaqur nd&euml;r t&euml; tjera n&euml; ekspozita kolektive dhe personale n&euml; institucione si; Muzeu i Artit Chelsea n&euml; Nju Jorg; Galeria Komunale e Arteve Bydgoszcz Poloni; Bienalja e Aleksandris&euml; p&euml;r Vendet e Mesdheut Egjipt; Galeria Komb&euml;tare e Arteve e Shqip&euml;ris&euml;, Galeria Komb&euml;tare e Arteve e Kosov&euml;s. Lumturi Blloshmi u nda nga jeta m&euml; 27 n&euml;ntor 2020 si pasoj&euml; e Covid-19.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(15, 8, 'en', '<p>With this intervention, Bujari turns our attention to one of the main problems faced by the citizens of Albania after 1992: the occupation of public spaces and spaces meant for public services. This problem has always been present and has turned into &ldquo;normality&rdquo; with the passing of time. Loyal to his ideals, Bujari decides to take over the responsibility as a citizen and as an artist by making the changes himself. During his studies at the Academy of Fine Arts, he had noticed that the sidewalk for pedestrians around the Academy building was always occupied by cars parking there illegally. Moved by this repeated scene, he produced a &ldquo;Parking Forbidden&rdquo; sign and overnight installed it illegally on that pedestrian sidewalk.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\nNikolin Bujari born 1984 in Shkodra, Albania lives and works in Tirana, Albania. He graduated from Tirana Art Academy in 2006 with Professor Edi Hila and was a guest student at the College of Design in Karlsruhe Germany at the Media class with Professor Mischa Kuball.<br />\r\nAmong others his works have been shown in exhibitions in institutions like: Badischer Kunstverein, Karlsruhe Germany; Nassauischer Kunstverein, Wiesbaden, Germany; Haus am L&uuml;tzowplatz, Berlin Germany; National Gallery of Art, Tirana Albania; 3-rd Tirana Biennale Albania, Tirana Art Lab - Center for Contemporary Art, etc.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(16, 8, 'al', '<p>Me k&euml;t&euml; nd&euml;rhyrje Bujari na e kthen v&euml;mendjen tek nj&euml; nga problemet kryesore me t&euml; cilat u p&euml;rball&euml;n qytetar&euml;t e Shqip&euml;ris&euml; pas vitit 1992: zaptimi i hap&euml;sirave publike dhe hap&euml;sirave t&euml; menduara p&euml;r sh&euml;rbime publike. Ky problem ka qen&euml; gjithmon&euml; i pranish&euml;m dhe &euml;sht&euml; kthyer n&euml; &ldquo;normalitet&rdquo; me kalimin e koh&euml;s. Besnik ndaj idealeve t&euml; tij, Bujari vendos t&euml; marr&euml; p&euml;rgjegj&euml;sin&euml; si qytetar dhe si artist duke i b&euml;r&euml; vet&euml; ndryshimet. Gjat&euml; studimeve n&euml; Akademin&euml; e Arteve, ai kishte v&euml;n&euml; re se trotuari p&euml;r k&euml;mb&euml;sor&euml;t p&euml;rreth godin&euml;s s&euml; Akademis&euml; ishte gjithmon&euml; i z&euml;n&euml; &nbsp;nga makinat q&euml; parkonin aty n&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml; t&euml; paligjshme. I prekur nga kjo sken&euml; e p&euml;rs&euml;ritur, ai prodhoi nj&euml; tabel&euml; &quot;Ndalohet parkimi&quot; dhe brenda nat&euml;s e instaloi at&euml; ilegalisht n&euml; &nbsp;trotuarin e k&euml;mb&euml;sor&euml;ve.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Nikolin Bujari i lindur m&euml; 1984 n&euml; Shkod&euml;r, Shqip&euml;ri jeton dhe punon n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. Ai u diplomua n&euml; Akademin&euml; e Arteve n&euml; Tiran&euml; n&euml; vitin 2006 me profesor Edi Hila dhe ishte student i ftuar n&euml; Kolegjin e Dizajnit n&euml; Karlsruhe, Gjermani n&euml; klas&euml;n Media Art &nbsp;me profesor Mischa Kuball. Nd&euml;r t&euml; tjerash, veprat e tij jan&euml; shfaqur n&euml; ekspozita e institucione si: Badischer Kunstverein, Karlsruhe Gjermani; Nassauischer Kunstverein, Wiesbaden, Gjermani; Haus am L&uuml;tzowplatz, Berlin Gjermani; Galeria Komb&euml;tare e Arteve, Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri; Bienalja e 3-t&euml; e Tiran&euml;s n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri, Tirana Art Lab - Qendra p&euml;r Artin Bashk&euml;kohor, etj.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(17, 9, 'en', '<p>In the&nbsp;intervention &quot;Forgotten Places&quot;, the artist reflects upon the state of a present that has forgotten the past: physically but also mentally. At Barrikada Street, the skeleton of an abandoned building that was supposed to become a hospital becomes instead the scene for Demetja&rsquo;s work. In such a location her audio installation comes alive through sounds of breathing, beating hearts, and hospital equipment transmitted by a speaker, creating a surreal symphony facing one of the busiest roads of Tirana. The speaker becomes symbolically the heart of the ruin, able to send inputs to the citizens through sounds and to create an unconventional dialogue with the city itself. Such intervention reflects on the state of being forgotten even when still part of the city&rsquo;s body, a phenomenon still very present in the Albanian urban landscape even today, making the work very relevant in today&#39;s context. Demetja&rsquo;s intervention &ldquo;Forgotten Places&rdquo; took place in September 2006, as part of the event &ldquo;1:60 Insurgent Space&rdquo; curated by Stefano Romano.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Adela Demetja born in 1984 in Tirana, Albania. She was trained as a painter and studied from 2002 to 2006 at the Academy of Art in Tirana and at College of Art and Design Karlsruhe, Germany. She holds a master&#39;s in &quot;Curatorial and Critical Studies&quot; from St&auml;delschule and Goethe University, Frankfurt/Main. She works with the medium of painting, drawing, writing, and video. She is interested in art as an experience of Self-Realization and Spirituality and performativity in art. Her works have been included in exhibitions and projects at Badischer Kunstverein Karlsruh;, Kultur Kontakt Vienna, Performative Exhibition #1 at Tirana Art Lab; Portland Institute for Contemporary Art; Maxim Gorki Theater Berlin; Ecumene Project Online; Polip Festival Prishtina.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL);
