(18, 9, 'al', '<p>M&euml; nd&euml;rhyrjen &quot;Vende t&euml; harruara&quot; artistja&nbsp;reflekton mbi gj&euml;ndjen e nj&euml; t&euml; tashmeje q&euml; e ka harruar t&euml; shkuar&euml;n, si fizikisht po ashtu edhe mend&euml;risht. Skeleti i nj&euml; nd&euml;rtese q&euml; supozohej t&euml; shnd&euml;rrohej n&euml; nj&euml; spital n&euml; Rrug&euml;n e Barrikadave, kthehet n&euml; sken&euml;n e duhur p&euml;r pun&euml;n e Demetjas. N&euml; nj&euml; vendndodhje t&euml; atill&euml;, instalacioni i saj zanor merr jet&euml; n&euml;p&euml;rmjet tingujve t&euml; frym&euml;marrjes, rrahjeve t&euml; zemr&euml;s dhe pajisjeve spitalore, t&euml; cil&euml;t transmetohen nga nj&euml; amplifikator, duke krijuar k&euml;shtu nj&euml; simfoni surreale n&euml; nj&euml; nga rrug&euml;t m&euml; t&euml; ngarkuara t&euml; Tiran&euml;s. Amplifikatori shnd&euml;rrohet simbolikisht n&euml; zemr&euml;n e rr&euml;noj&euml;s; ai &euml;sht&euml; i aft&euml; t&rsquo;i d&euml;rgoj&euml; shenja qytetar&euml;ve e n&euml;p&euml;rmjet tingujve t&euml; krijoj&euml; nj&euml; dialog jo konvecional me vet&euml; qytetin. Nj&euml; nd&euml;rhyrje e till&euml; reflekton mbi statusin e t&euml; q&euml;nurit i harruar edhe kur je ende pjes&euml; e trupit t&euml; qytetit. Nj&euml; fenomen i till&euml; vazhdon t&euml; jet&euml; tejet i pranish&euml;m n&euml; urbanistik&euml;n shqiptare, duke e b&euml;r&euml; k&euml;t&euml; pun&euml; relevante edhe n&euml; kontekstin e dit&euml;ve t&euml; sotme. Nd&euml;hyrja e Demetjas &ldquo;Vende t&euml; harruara&rdquo; ndodhi n&euml; shtator 2006, si pjes&euml; e eventit &ldquo;1:60 Insurgent Space&rdquo; kuruar nga Stefano Romano.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Adela Demetja lindur m&euml; 1984, n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri, studioi n&euml; deg&euml;n e piktur&euml;s gjat&euml; 2002-2006 ne Akademin&euml; e Arteve, Tiran&euml; si dhe n&euml; Kolegjin e Artit dhe Dizajnit n&euml; Karlsruhe, Gjermani. Ajo ka nj&euml; Master n&euml; Studime Kuratoriale dhe Kritike nga St&auml;delschule dhe Universiteti Goethe, Frankfurt/Main, Gjermani. Demetja punon me mediumin e piktur&euml;s, vizatimit, shkrimit dhe videos. Ajo interesohet p&euml;r artin si eksperienc&euml; e vet&euml;-realizimit dhe spiritualitetit. Punimet e saj jan&euml; p&euml;rfshir&euml; n&euml; ekspozita dhe projekte n&euml; Badischer Kunstverein, Karlsruhe; Kultur Kontakt, Vjen&euml;, Ekspozita Performative #1, Tirana Art Lab; Instituti p&euml;r Artin Bashk&euml;kohor, Portland; Teatri Maxim Gorki, Berlin; Projekti Ecumene, Online; Polip Festival, Prishtin&euml;.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(19, 10, 'en', '<p>&ldquo;Pipifax &ndash; Through the Looking Glass and what we found there&rdquo; is a series of large-scale photographs taken by Haus am Gern in key places of Tirana reverberating the political demonstrations and social unrest that took place during May - June 2011. The concept of &ldquo;inversion&rdquo; that is already inherent in the origin of the word &lsquo;Pipifax&rsquo; can be traced throughout the series. Based on re-enactments of the recent student protests, the photographer&#39;s backdrop reveals itself as laterally reversed; protest plates have been replaced by commercial signs and advertisement and vice versa. &ldquo;The revolution will not be televised&rdquo; Gill Scott Heron once famously stated. The series hence suggests a model of translation that has deliberately &lsquo;gone terribly wrong&rsquo;. It strategically presents &lsquo;nonsense&rsquo; (read: &lsquo;Pipifax&rsquo;) as an attempt to glimpse at political dynamics and political failures that otherwise would become absorbed by their own representation. As the production of the photograph &ndash; &lsquo;Giga Images&rsquo; &ndash; was very laborious, they can also be read as performative works, interventions into the public space that intentionally stir the attention and response of the passer-by. The fact the project involved a great number of local artists and students contributes further to the participatory undercurrent of this work.&nbsp;The work was produced during their Residency at Tirana Art Lab and was exhibited at Tirana Ekspres which was inaugurated with this event. With the participation of: Albi Azuni, Flugers Beci, Doris Beci, Rubin Beqo, Marvina &Ccedil;ela, Ernard Dyli, Rigels Dyrmishi, Alson Dyrmishi, Florjan Fejzollari, Amanda Hyseni, Andri Ibrahimaj, Mustafa Kacurri, Illir Kaso, Sead Kazanxhiu, Klajdi Kruja, Bashkim Kupi, Demir Kurti, Brikena Lila, Dejvi Mu&ccedil;aj, Jovana Muka, Marlo Ndoci, Kristofer Ndreko, Miletovon Nrdeko, Matilda Odobashi, Olsi Odobashi, Arjola Oshafi, Elvisa Pllo&ccedil;i, Alketa Ramaj, Edmond Ramushi, Olta &amp; Redi Saliasi, Redi Qondraj, Armando Qoshku</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">The artist duo Barbara Meyer Cesta and Rudolf Steiner have been working on interdisciplinary projects under the label Haus am Gern since 1998. Their work focuses on socially relevant themes, which they appropriate with lightness, irony, and a sense of sophisticated criticism and translates into context-specific works. Their artistic work is characterized by media diversity, in which drawing, photography, video, object, installation, and performance are interrelated in the context of conceptual works.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(20, 10, 'al', '<p>&ldquo;Pipifax &ndash; P&euml;rtej pasqyr&euml;s dhe &ccedil;far&euml; gjet&euml;m atje&rdquo; &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; seri fotografish me format t&euml; madh nga Haus am Gern n&euml; vende ky&ccedil;e t&euml; Tiran&euml;s q&euml; u bejn&euml; jehon&euml; demonstratave politike dhe trazirave sociale t&euml; ndodhura gjat&euml; periudh&euml;s maj - qershor 2011. Koncepti i &quot;P&euml;rmbysjes&quot; q&euml; &euml;sht&euml; i mbartur n&euml; origjin&euml;n e fjal&euml;s &#39;Pipifax&#39; mund t&euml; gjurmohet gjat&euml; gjith&euml; seris&euml; fotografike. Bazuar n&euml; rishfaqjet e protestave &nbsp;studentore n&euml; 2011, sfondi i fotografive shfaqet i kthyer nga ana e kund&euml;rt; tabelat e protest&euml;s jan&euml; z&euml;vend&euml;suar me tabela tregtare e reklama dhe anasjelltas. &quot;Revolucioni nuk do t&euml; transmetohet n&euml; televizion&quot;, deklaroi dikur Gill Scott Heron. Prandaj, seria sugjeron nj&euml; model p&euml;rkthimi q&euml; q&euml;llimisht ka &#39;p&euml;rfunduar tmerr&euml;sisht keq&#39;. Ai paraqet n&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml; strategjike &quot;pa-kuptimin&quot; (lexo: &quot;Pipifax&quot;) si nj&euml; p&euml;rpjekje p&euml;r t&euml; par&euml; dinamik&euml;n politike dhe d&euml;shtimet politike q&euml; p&euml;rndryshe do t&euml; p&euml;rthitheshin nga p&euml;rfaq&euml;simi i tyre. Duke qen&euml; se realizimi i fotografive &ndash; &lsquo;Giga Images&rsquo; &ndash; ishte shum&euml; i mundimsh&euml;m, ato mund t&euml; lexohen edhe si vepra performuese, nd&euml;rhyrje n&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml;n publike q&euml; nxisin q&euml;llimisht v&euml;mendjen dhe reagimin e kalimtarit. Fakti q&euml; projekti p&euml;rfshiu nj&euml; num&euml;r t&euml; madh artist&euml;sh dhe student&euml;sh vendas kontribuon m&euml; tej n&euml; natyr&euml;n p&euml;rfshir&euml;se t&euml; k&euml;saj pune.&nbsp;Puna u prodhua gjat&euml; Rezidenc&euml;s s&euml; tyre n&euml; Tirana Art Lab dhe u ekspozua n&euml; Tirana Ekspres, q&euml; u p&euml;rurua si hap&euml;sir&euml; me k&euml;t&euml; event.<br />\r\nMe pjes&euml;marrjen e: Albi Azuni, Flugers Beci, Doris Beci, Rubin Beqo, Marvina &Ccedil;ela, Ernard Dyli, Rigels Dyrmishi, Alson Dyrmishi, Florjan Fejzollari, Amanda Hyseni, Andri Ibrahimaj, Mustafa Kacurri, Illir Kaso, Sead Kazanxhiu, Klaj. Bashkim Kupi, Demir Kurti, Brikena Lila, Dejvi Mu&ccedil;aj, Jovana Muka, Marlo Ndoci, Kristofer Ndreko, Miletovon Nrdeko, Matilda Odobashi, Olsi Odobashi, Arjola Oshafi, Elvisa Pllo&ccedil;i, Alketa Ramaj, Edmond Ramushi, Olta, Rendr Sali Armando Qoshku</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Dyshja e artist&euml;ve Barbara Meyer Cesta dhe Rudolf Steiner kan&euml; punuar n&euml; projekte nd&euml;rdisiplinore n&euml;n emrin Haus am Gern q&euml; nga viti 1998. Puna e tyre fokusohet n&euml; tema t&euml; r&euml;nd&euml;sishme shoq&euml;rore, t&euml; cilat ata i p&euml;rvet&euml;sojn&euml; me but&euml;si, ironi dhe nj&euml; ndjenj&euml; kritike t&euml; sofistikuar dhe i p&euml;rkthejn&euml; n&euml; punime specifike. Puna e tyre artistike karakterizohet nga diversiteti mediatik, n&euml; t&euml; cilin vizatimi, fotografia, video, objekti, instalacioni dhe performanca jan&euml; t&euml; nd&euml;rlidhura n&euml; kontekstin e veprave konceptuale.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(21, 11, 'en', '<p>In the work &quot;Meat Shop&quot; Alban Muja invites a butcher to &ldquo;perform&rdquo; his activity in front of the National Gallery of Arts in Tirana, creating an uncanny and provocative scenario. In front of the most important artistic institution which further is placed in the main boulevard of Tirana, this action creates a new reality: simultaneously absurd and theatrical and at the same time genuine and disenchanting. By deciding not to do the performance himself, Muja indirectly lends his artistic &ldquo;privileges&rdquo; to the butcher providing him with a different type of &ldquo;customer&rdquo;. &nbsp;By bringing two distant realities together, Muja&rsquo;s performance raises questions about the role of the artist, the role of art institutions, consumerism within the art field and it can be read as a form of institutional critique. Muja&rsquo;s performance &ldquo;Meat Shop&rdquo; took place in September 2005, as part of the event &ldquo;1:60 Insurgent Space&rdquo; curated by Stefano Romano.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Alban Muja born 1980 is a Kosovan contemporary artist. He lives and works between Berlin and Prishtina. Influenced primarily by the social, political and economic transformation processes in the wider surrounding region, he investigates history and socio-political themes and links them to his position in Kosovo today. &nbsp;Selected exhibitions include: Ludwig Museum, Budapest; Maxxi Museum, Rome; Autostrada Biennale; &nbsp;Charim Gallery, Vienna, Iscp New York, 3rd Industrial Art Biennial, Istria, Croatia ; Crawford Art Gallery, Cork, MOMus Experimental Center for the Arts, Thessaloniki; Kumu Art Museum, Tallinn; Guangdong Museum of Art; Museum Of Contemporary Art &ndash; Skopje; MeetFactory, Prague; Forum Stadpark, Graz; &lsquo;Trieste Contemporanea, Trieste; James Gallery, New York; City Art Gallery of Ljubljana; Zhejiang Art Museum, Hangzhou; Museum of Fine Art, Split; Trieste Contemporanea; Museum of Modern and Contemporary Art, Rijeka; Zachęta National Gallery of Art, Warsaw; &lsquo;2ndBiennial of Contemporary Art in the Atomic shelter in Konjic, BiH; &Scaron;kuc Gallery, Ljubljana; National Gallery of Kosovo; 60&#39;s Berlinale&#39;; Museum of Fine Art, Split; Gagosian Gallery, Beverly Hills; Skuc Gallery, Ljubljana; Slovak National Gallery; Staatliche Kunsthalle, Baden-Baden; 28th Ljubljana Graphic Biennale; nGbK, Berlin; National Gallery of Arts, Tirana; Cetinje Biennale and others. In 2019, Muja represented the Pavilion of the Republic of Kosovo at the 58th Venice Biennale with &ldquo;Family Album&rdquo; project.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(22, 11, 'al', '<p>N&euml; vepr&euml;n &quot;&ldquo;Dyqan Mishi&rdquo; Alban Muja fton nj&euml; kasap p&euml;r t&euml; &ldquo;performuar&rdquo; aktivitetin e tij p&euml;rball&euml; Galeris&euml; Komb&euml;tare t&euml; Arteve n&euml; Tiran&euml;, duke krijuar k&euml;shtu nj&euml; skenar t&euml; &ccedil;uditsh&euml;m dhe provokues. P&euml;rball&euml; institucionit m&euml; t&euml; r&euml;nd&euml;sish&euml;m artistik n&euml; vend, i cili p&euml;rpos k&euml;saj ndodhet edhe n&euml; bulevardin kryesor t&euml; Tiran&euml;s, kjo nd&euml;rhyrje krijon nj&euml; realitet t&euml; ri: absurd e teatral dhe n&euml; t&euml; nj&euml;jt&euml;n koh&euml; t&euml; &ccedil;ilt&euml;r e &ccedil;magjeps&euml;s. Duke vendosur t&euml; mos e kryej&euml; personalisht performanc&euml;n, n&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml; indirekte Muja ia kalon &ldquo;privilegjet&rdquo; e tija artistike kasapit, duke i falur k&euml;tij t&euml; fundit nj&euml; tjet&euml;r lloj &ldquo;klientele&rdquo;. Duke sjell&euml; bashk&euml; dy realitete normalisht t&euml; larg&euml;ta, performanca e Muj&euml;s ngre pyetje mbi rolin e artistit, rolin e institucioneve artistike, konsumerizmin n&euml; fush&euml;n e artit dhe mund t&euml; interpretohet si nj&euml; lloj kritike institucionale. Performanca e Muj&euml;s &ldquo;Dyqan Mishi&rdquo; ndodhi n&euml; shtator 2005, si pjes&euml; e eventit &ldquo;1:60 Insurgent Space&rdquo; kuruar by Stefano Romano.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Alban Muja lindur m&euml; 1980 &euml;sht&euml; nje artist kontemporan kosovar. Ai jeton dhe punon mes Berlinit dhe Prishtin&euml;s. I influencuar kryesisht nga pro&ccedil;eset transformative sociale, politike dhe ekonomike t&euml; rajonit, ai hulumton mbi historin&euml; dhe tematika socio-politike, duke i lidhur ato me pozicionin e Kosov&euml;s sot. Disa prej ekspozitave t&euml; tij p&euml;rfshijne: Ludwig Museum, Budapest; Maxxi Museum, Rome; Autostrada Biennale; &nbsp;Charim Gallery, Vienna, Iscp New York, 3rd Industrial Art Biennial, Istria, Croatia ; Crawford Art Gallery, Cork, MOMus Experimental Center for the Arts, Thessaloniki; Kumu Art Museum, Tallinn; Guangdong Museum of Art; Museum Of Contemporary Art &ndash; Skopje; MeetFactory, Prague; Forum Stadpark, Graz; &lsquo;Trieste Contemporanea, Trieste; James Gallery, New York; City Art Gallery of Ljubljana; Zhejiang Art Museum, Hangzhou; Museum of Fine Art, Split; Trieste Contemporanea; Museum of Modern and Contemporary Art, Rijeka; Zachęta National Gallery of Art, Warsaw; &lsquo;2ndBiennial of Contemporary Art in the Atomic shelter in Konjic, BiH; &Scaron;kuc Gallery, Ljubljana; National Gallery of Kosovo; 60&#39;s Berlinale&#39;; Museum of Fine Art, Split; Gagosian Gallery, Beverly Hills; Skuc Gallery, Ljubljana; Slovak National Gallery; Staatliche Kunsthalle, Baden-Baden; 28th Ljubljana Graphic Biennale; nGbK, Berlin; National Gallery of Arts, Tirana; Cetinje Biennale e shum&euml; t&euml; tjera. N&euml; 2019, Muja p&euml;rfaq&euml;soi Republik&euml;n e Kosov&euml;s ne Biennalen e 58 t&euml; Venecias, me projektin &ldquo;Albumi i familjes&rdquo;.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(23, 12, 'en', '<p>The work &ldquo;Q(&euml;)ndra Rinore&rdquo; is a light installation playing with words and concepts. Thanks to the interaction of switching a part of the letters on and off, it is possible at times to read &ldquo;Qendra rinore&rdquo; (youth&rsquo;s center) and other times &ldquo;endra rinore&rdquo; (youth&rsquo;s dreams). This almost naive calligraphy lights up an abandoned area in the periphery of the city. While working close to the community living in the area and that also participated in the making of the installation, one of the most crucial problems that Ramaj has identified is the fact that local youth doesn&rsquo;t have a meeting point where to socialize, spend time with each other, develop new hobbies and share personal interests. The installation plays with the words &ldquo;youth&rdquo; &ldquo;center&rdquo; and &ldquo;dreams&rdquo; by making possible a moment of reflection and also of action in an area that unfortunately seems to have accepted its &ldquo;abandoned&rdquo; destiny in a passive way; This kind of passivity is often found in many Albanian social realities. The light of this installation tries to trigger thoughts of change and why not, even dreams, in the citizen&rsquo;s mind and soul.<br />\r\nRamaj&rsquo;s intervention &ldquo;Q(&euml;)ndra Rinore&rdquo; took place in February 2019, as part of the event &ldquo;Artivizem&rdquo; organized by Art Kontakt and curated by Andi Tepelena.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Alketa Ramaj&nbsp;born in 1983 in P&euml;rmet, Albania lives and works in Berlin, Germany. She graduated in 2006 from the University of Arts in Tirana. Her work is represented by an&nbsp;incessant curiosity and permanent study of new forms of expression, which reveal striking&nbsp;independence in terms of applying her own critical and personal working methods.&nbsp;The emotional relationship the artist builds with the environment she lives in, in terms of social&nbsp;connection, historical and political context, is reflected in her practice that develops in different&nbsp;mediums. She received the 2012&nbsp;&rdquo;Onufri Prize&rdquo;&nbsp;and 2013&nbsp;&rdquo;Ardhje Award&rdquo;. Her solo shows include: About a Tree, Ministry of Culture, Tirana;&nbsp;Lust, Zeta Gallery, Tirana; Salon, ISCP - International Studio &amp; Curatorial Program, New York; No Title, Stacion &ndash; Center for Contemporary Art, Prishtina and Where I End You Begin (together with Dritan Hyska); La Fenice Gallery, Venice. Group exhibitions include: Ambitions, &nbsp;National Gallery of Arts, Tirana and Prishtine; A for Unapologetic, Vaska Emanouilova Sofia;&nbsp;D&eacute;jeuner avec Marubi, Vienna; Ex-Gratia,&nbsp;Collezione Giuseppe Iannaccone, Milano;&nbsp;Bienal de Curitiba &rsquo;17, Curitiba; Expressive Gestures, Galerie Heike Strelow, Frankfurt/Main;&nbsp;Focus: Ex-Yugoslavia and Albania, viennacontemporary, Vienna;&nbsp;Art D-0 ARK Underground, 3rd&nbsp;Edition of Project Biennial of Contemporary, Konjic;&nbsp;Bienal del Fin del Mundo, Mar Del Plata, Valparaiso;&nbsp;Fondazione Museo Pino Pascali, Bari.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(24, 12, 'al', '<p>Puna &ldquo;Q(&euml;)ndra Rinore&rdquo; &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; instalacion drite q&euml; luan me fjal&euml; dhe me koncepte. Fal&euml; nd&euml;rveprimit q&euml; krijon fikja dhe ndezja e nj&euml; pjese t&euml; shkronjave, mund&euml;sohet leximi i dy shkrimeve t&euml; ndryshme: &ldquo;Q&euml;ndra rinore&rdquo; dhe &ldquo;&euml;ndra rinore&rdquo;. Kjo kaligrafi thuajse naive ndri&ccedil;on nj&euml; zon&euml; &nbsp;t&euml; braktisur n&euml; periferi t&euml; qytetit. Duke punuar pran&euml; komunitetit t&euml; zon&euml;s, i cili gjithashtu ka marr&euml; pjes&euml; n&euml; krijimin e instalacionit, nj&euml; prej problemeve kryesore q&euml; artistja Ramaj identifikoi, ishte pik&euml;risht fakti q&euml; rinia lokale nuk kishte nj&euml; pik&euml; takimi, socializimi, nd&euml;rveprimi e ku mund t&euml; ndaheshin interesa personale e t&euml; krijoheshin interesa t&euml; reja. Instalacioni luan me fjal&euml;t &ldquo;rini&rdquo;, &ldquo;q&euml;nd&euml;r&rdquo; dhe &ldquo;&euml;nd&euml;rr&rdquo; duke mund&euml;suar k&euml;shtu nj&euml; moment reflektimi dhe gjithashtu nj&euml; veprim t&euml; ri n&euml; nj&euml; zon&euml; e cila fatkeqsisht duket sikur e ka pranuar statusin e &ldquo;braktisjes&rdquo; n&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml; pasive; nj&euml; lloj pasiviteti shpesh i pranish&euml;m n&euml; disa realitete sociale n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri. Drita e k&euml;tij instalacioni mundohet t&euml; ngacmoj&euml; mendime p&euml;r ndryshim, dhe p&euml;rse jo, mundohet edhe t&euml; ngacmoj&euml; &euml;ndrrat n&euml; mendjen dhe shpirtin e qytetarit. Nd&euml;rhyrja e Alketa Ramaj &ldquo;Q(&euml;)ndra Rinore&rdquo; ndodhi n&euml; shkurt 2019, si pjes&euml; e eventit &ldquo;Artiviz&euml;m&rdquo; organizuar nga Art Kontakt dhe kuruar nga Andi Tepelena.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Alketa Ramaj lindur m&euml; 1983 n&euml; P&euml;rmet, Shqip&euml;ri, jeton e punon n&euml; Berlin, Gjermani. Ajo diplomohet n&euml; 2006 n&euml; Universitetin e Arteve n&euml; Tiran&euml;. Puna e saj karkterizohet nga nj&euml; kuriozitet i palodhur dhe nj&euml; studim i vazhduesh&euml;m i formave t&euml; rejave t&euml; s&euml; shprehurit, t&euml; cilat tregojn&euml; nj&euml; pavar&euml;si n&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml;n se si artistja i aplikon ato n&euml; metodat e saj t&euml; pun&euml;s personale dhe kritike. Lidhja emocionale q&euml; artistja nd&euml;rton me ambientin ku jeton, pra mar&euml;dh&euml;niet sociale, kontekstit historik dhe politik, reflektohen n&euml; praktiken e saj q&euml; zhvillohet n&euml; mediume t&euml; ndryshme. Ne 2021 ajo fitoi &ldquo;&Ccedil;mimin Onufri&rdquo; dhe n&euml; 2013 &ldquo;&Ccedil;mimin Ardhje&rdquo;. Disa ekspozita personale p&euml;rfshijne: About a Tree , Ministria e Kultur&euml;s, Tirana; Lust, Zeta Gallery, Tirana; Salon, ISCP - International Studio &amp; Curatorial Program, New York; No Title, Stacion &ndash; Center for Contemporary Art, Prishtina and Where I End You Begin (together with Dritan Hyska); La Fenice Gallery, Venice. Disa ekspozita grupi perfshijne: Ambitions, Galeria Kombetare e Arteve, Tiran&euml; dhe Prishtin&euml;; A for Unapologetic, Vaska Emanouilova Gallery, Sofia; D&eacute;jeuner avec Marubi, Vienna; Ex-Gratia, Collezione Giuseppe Iannaccone, Milano; Bienal de Curitiba &rsquo;17, Curitiba; Expressive Gestures, Galerie Heike Strelow, Frankfurt/Main; Focus: Ex-Yugoslavia and Albania, viennacontemporary, Vienna; Art D-0 ARK Underground, 3rd Edition of Project Biennial of Contemporary, Konjic; Bienal del Fin del Mundo, Mar Del Plata, Valparaiso; Fondazione Museo Pino Pascali, Bari.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(25, 13, 'en', '<p>The idea behind Serjanaj&rsquo;s work &quot;Fridom&quot; arises from a frequent question in the artist&rsquo;s mind: &ldquo;Why isn&#39;t there a commemoration sign at the place where once the statue of dictator Enver Hoxha was demolished by the Albanian students on 20 February 1991?&rdquo; Indeed, the location of such an event which for Albanians has symbolized an action and moment of freedom is found in the middle of Skanderbeg Square and has never had a commemoration sign on it.&nbsp;But the artist deepens his reflection by taking action: he decides to create a tombstone with the date of the event on it. Why a tombstone? Because according to the artist freedom in Albania is a corrupted concept, or better said: dead. The work which was meant to be titled &ldquo;Freedom&rdquo; was actually titled &ldquo;Fridom&rdquo; (as its pronunciation would be written in Albanian) because of an orthographic mistake made by the tombstone&rsquo;s artisan, not able to speak or write in English, creating so a naif and interesting effect. The tombstone was put by the artist in the exact location where the statue of Hoxha was located in Skanderbeg Square on 20 February 2018, at 2 pm. &quot;Fridom&quot; was realized for STRIKE (Sk&euml;nderbej Square) in collaboration with Debatik Center of Contemporary Art.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Arjan Serjanaj born 1982 in Tirana, Albania. Serjanaj holds a Bachelor&rsquo;s and Master&rsquo;s Degree from the Academy of Fine Arts of Bologna where he graduated in 2009. He has returned and worked in the Albanian artistic scene since 2013. Some of his main activities include: Ideator &amp; Organizer of Postum Trauma at Tirana Ekspres - The alternative art space, Tirana, Albania; Curator of Movie Night at Tirana Ekspres - The alternative art space, Tirana, Albania; Artist in residency at Bando S&igrave;, Bologna, Italy; Selected Artist for Transzinxhir at FAB Gallery, Tirana, Albania; Selected Artist for Kol Idromeno Prize at National Gallery, Shkodra, Albania; Selected Artist for Primo Premio Internazionale in Mogliano, Italy. Serjanaj has also been actively engaged in Albanian cinematography as a set painter, props maker, and assistant scenographer.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(26, 13, 'al', '<p>Ideja e pun&euml;s &quot;Fridom&quot;&nbsp;lind nga nj&euml; pyetje q&euml; rikthehet shpesh n&euml; mendjen e artistit: &ldquo;P&euml;rse nuk ka nj&euml; shenj&euml; perkujtimore n&euml; vendin ku dikur studentet shemb&euml;n statuj&euml;n e ish-diktatorit Enver Hoxha n&euml; 20 shkurt 1991?&rdquo; Me t&euml; drejte, vendodhja e nj&euml; ndodhie t&euml; till&euml;, e cila p&euml;r shqiptaret ka p&euml;rfaqsuar nj&euml; veprim dhe moment historik lirie, &euml;sht&euml; pik&euml;risht n&euml; Sheshin Sk&euml;nderbe dhe kurr&euml; nuk ka patur nj&euml; shenj&euml; p&euml;rkujtimore. N&euml; k&euml;t&euml; rast artisti e thellon reflektimin e tij duke vepruar: ai vendos t&euml; krijoj&euml; nj&euml; gur varri me dat&euml;n e ngjarjes gdhendur mbi t&euml;. P&euml;rse pik&euml;risht nj&euml; gur varri? Sepse sipas artistit, liria n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; koncept i korruptuar, ose m&euml; qart&euml;sisht: &euml;sht&euml; nje koncept i vdekur. Puna, e cila duhej t&euml; titullohej &ldquo;Freedom&rdquo; (Liri), titullohet &ldquo;Fridom&rdquo; (ashtu si&ccedil; do t&euml; shkruhej shqiptimi i fjal&euml;s n&euml; shqip) p&euml;r shkak t&euml; nj&euml; gabimi ortografik &nbsp;b&euml;r&euml; nga puntori q&euml; prodhoi gurin e varrit, i cili n&euml; pamund&euml;sin&euml; e tij p&euml;r t&euml; folur, shkruar e kuptuar anglisht, krijon nj&euml; efekt naiv dhe interesant n&euml; mbishkrim. M&euml; 20 shkurt 2019, ora 14:00, n&euml; Sheshin Sk&euml;nderbe, guri i varrit u vendos nga vet&euml; artisti n&euml; vendndodhjen ekzakte ku dikur ndodhej statuja i Enver Hoxh&euml;s. Puna &ldquo;Fridom&rdquo; e Serjanaj u realizua p&euml;r rubrik&euml;n STRIKE (Skanderbeg Square) n&euml; bashk&euml;punim me Debatik Center.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Arjan Serjanaj lindur m&euml; 1982 n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri, ka nj&euml; diplom&euml; Bachelor dhe Master nga Akademia e Arteve e Bolognas, ku diplomohet n&euml; 2009. Ai &euml;sht&euml; kthyer dhe ka punuar n&euml; sken&euml;n artistike shqiptare q&euml; prej 2013. Disa prej aktiviteteve t&euml; tij kryesore p&euml;rfshijn&euml;: Ideator dhe Organizator i Postum Trauma tek Tirana Ekpres - The alternative art space, Tiran&euml;; Kurator i Movie Night tek Tirana Ekspres - The alternative art space, Tiran&euml;; Artist n&euml; rezidenc&euml; tek Bando S&igrave;, Bologna, Itali; Artist p&euml;r &nbsp;Transzinxhir at FAB Gallery, Tiran&euml;; Artist i p&euml;rzgjedhur p&euml;r &Ccedil;mimin Kol Idromeno, Galeria Komb&euml;tare, Shkod&euml;r; Artist i p&euml;rzgjedhur p&euml;r &Ccedil;mimin Primo Premio Internazionale, Mogliano, Itali.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(27, 14, 'en', '<p>A sense of fear and anxiety caused by the degradation and wild urbanization of the city inspired Shkreli&rsquo;s &ldquo;Insects&rdquo;. The artist places the self-made metal insects in such a position that they look as if they were coming out from the Lana River, illustrating them as new creatures belonging to such an environment. Lana is the only stream crossing Tirana which unfortunately doesn&rsquo;t look and sometimes doesn&rsquo;t even smell very good: it becomes water flowing container taking and accepting within many wastes from the city. Shkreli&rsquo;s sculptures create a sense of dystopia but also mysticism, as they tend to draw a parallel reality to what is already existing, charging the insects with some kind of power. It seems as if they are trying to tell something new to the citizens by putting them in an almost uncomfortable and unfamiliar situation; what arises from such a process of reflection is indeed very familiar because they are daily problems in a big, expanding, capital city. Shkrelis&rsquo;s intervention &ldquo;Insects&rdquo; took place in April 2006, as part of the exhibition &ldquo;And the art in-between&rdquo; in collaboration with Dutch artist Helmut Dick. The exhibition was part of &ldquo;1:60 Insurgent Space&rdquo; curated by Stefano Romano.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Syabhit Shkreli born in 1981 in Shkodra, Albania lives and works in Tirana, Albania. He studied art at the Academy of Arts in Tirana, where he graduated in 2004, and from 2006-2007 he studied Visual Arts and Communication Design at Sabanci University, Istanbul. His works have been exhibited among others in: Love it or Leave it, Cetina Biennial, Cetina, Montenegro; Here &amp; Now, Bergamo, Italy; Saze on Tour, Hoorn, Netherlands; Surviving Insects, in 1/60 insurgent space, Tirana, Albania; A Political Exhibition, Tirana, Albania; My Space 03. Tirana-Berlin, Berlin, Germany; For those who can not enter, Tirana, Albania; Teatri i Gjeb&euml;rimit, Tirana, Albania. Alongside his artistic practice, he has been active as a producer for numerous exhibitions and art projects in Albania.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(28, 14, 'al', '<p>&quot;Insektet&quot; e Shkrelit frym&euml;zohen nga nj&euml; ndjenj&euml; frike dhe ankthi e shkaktuar nga degradimi dhe urbanizimi i eg&euml;r i qytetit. Artisti i krijon dhe i vendos insektet metalike n&euml; nj&euml; pozicion t&euml; till&euml; q&euml; t&euml; duken sikur po dalin nga lumi i Lan&euml;s; papritur ato ngjajn&euml; si krijesa t&euml; reja q&euml; i p&euml;rkasin nj&euml; mjedisi t&euml; till&euml;. Lana &euml;sht&euml; i vetmi lum q&euml; p&euml;rshkon p&euml;rmes Tiran&euml;n, nj&euml; lum q&euml; fatkeq&euml;sisht nuk ka pamje dhe er&euml; shum&euml; t&euml; mir&euml;: kjo rrjedh&euml; uji e p&euml;rshkon qytetin duke mbartur brenda vetes shum&euml; mbeturina e mbetje prej tij. Skulpturat e Shkrelit krijojn&euml; nj&euml; ndjenj&euml; distopike, por edhe misticizmi, pasi ato tentojn&euml; t&euml; krijojn&euml; nj&euml; realitet paralel me at&euml; q&euml; tashm&euml; ekziston, duke i ngarkuar insektet me nj&euml; lloj fuqie. Insektet, duket sikur po p&euml;rpiqen t&#39;u thon&euml; di&ccedil;ka t&euml; re qytetar&euml;ve duke i v&euml;n&euml; n&euml; nj&euml; situat&euml; thuajse t&euml; pak&euml;ndshme dhe t&euml; panjohur; ajo q&euml; lind nga nj&euml; pro&ccedil;es i till&euml; reflektimi &euml;sht&euml; n&euml; t&euml; v&euml;rtet&euml; shum&euml; e njohur, sepse b&euml;het fjal&euml; p&euml;r probleme t&euml; p&euml;rditshme n&euml; nj&euml; kryeqytet t&euml; madh e n&euml; zhvillim e sip&euml;r. Nd&euml;rhyrja e Shkrelit &ldquo;Insektet&rdquo; ndodhi n&euml; prill 2006, si pjes&euml; e ekspozit&euml;s &ldquo;Dhe arti n&euml; mes&rdquo; n&euml; bashk&euml;punim me artistin holandez Helmut Dick. Ekspozita ishte pjes&euml; e eventit &ldquo;1:60 Insurgent Space&rdquo; kuruar nga Stefano Romano.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Syabhit Shkreli i lindur m&euml; 1981 n&euml; Shkod&euml;r, Shqip&euml;ri jeton dhe punon n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. Ai studioi art n&euml; Akademin&euml; e Arteve n&euml; Tiran&euml;, ku u diplomua n&euml; vitin 2004 dhe nga viti 2006-2007 studioi &nbsp;arte pamore dhe dizajn komunikimi n&euml; Universitetin Sabanci, Stamboll. Veprat e tij jan&euml; ekspozuar nd&euml;r t&euml; tjera n&euml;: Love it or Leave it, Cetina Biennial, Cetina, Montenegro; Here &amp; Now, Bergamo, Italy; Saze on Tour, Hoorn, Netherlands; Surviving Insects, 1/60 insurgent space, Tirana, Albania; A Political Exhibition, Tirana, Albania; My Space 03. Tirana-Berlin, Berlin, Germany; For those who can not enter, Tirana, Albania; Teatri i Gjeb&euml;rimit, Tirana, Albania. Krahas praktik&euml;s s&euml; tij artistike ai ka qen&euml; aktiv si producent p&euml;r ekspozita dhe projekte t&euml; shumta artistike n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(29, 15, 'en', '<p>The&nbsp;work &quot;The tool makes the master&quot; was born during Bellomo&rsquo;s residency at Tirana Art Lab and therefore is deeply connected to the city&rsquo;s social dynamics. The artist focuses his attention precisely on a very busy point at one of the entrances of Tirana: Shqiponja (Eagle) &nbsp;Square, known among citizens also as &ldquo;Dogana&rdquo;. This space was not only busy with vehicles entering and exiting the capital but was also a standing point for unemployed workers who, with their tools, waited for someone to hire them occasionally. Having their tools already with them made their fast hiring even more possible. Such a scene, almost &ldquo;normal&rdquo; in the Albanian society context, becomes the basis for the artist&rsquo;s work which develops in an intervention/performance and documentation of it in photography/video. In this case, the artist is not the performer; he invites one of the workers to be the man. Bellomo asks him to engrave with his jackhammer on one of Dogana&rsquo;s walls the following statement in Albanian: Vegla ben ustain (The tool makes the master). Such a quote, which is used as a popular saying in Albania, becomes tangible on the wall and an integrated part of the worker&rsquo;s scene waiting for a job, an opportunity, waiting for something. Bellomo&rsquo;s &ldquo;The tool makes the master&rdquo; was realized during his residency at Tirana Art Lab and it was exhibited in the exhibition &ldquo;Double Feature #3 - Fabrizio Bellomo &amp; Elton Baxhaku&rdquo; at Tirana Art Lab.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Fabrizio Bellomo born in 1982, lives and works in Bari, Italy. He is a multi-disciplinary artist, curator, writer and director that carries out his research in a hybrid and experimental way. His approach to the art is broad: he works with archival and historic material, videos and public installations. His art switches between the real and the digital world. His works have been exhibited in personal and collective exhibitions, through public projects, film festivals and presentations. Among them: 38th Turin Film Festival; Archipelago Italy. Projects for the future of the country&#39;s internal territories &quot;- Italian Pavilion at the 16th International Architecture Exhibition of the Venice Biennale; There is time for medlars - ICCD Central Institute for Cataloging and Documentation Rome; REFOCUS, MiBACT - MuFoCo - Triennale di Milano; Italy Zokugo - Italian Cultural Institute Tokyo; About a City 2019 - Giangiacomo Feltrinelli Foundation Milan; &quot;Mechanism&quot; - KCB Kulturni Centar Beograda; Talent Prize 2017 - MACRO Contemporary Art Museum Rome; plat (t) form 2015 - Fotomuseum Winterthur; Unseen 2019 - Amsterdam; Teatri i Gjelberimit - Galeria Fab Tirana; Erosioni - Fundaci&ograve; Enric Miralles Barcelona; 2004-2014, Works and Projects of the Museum of Contemporary Photography - Triennale di Milano; ArtAround - MuFoCo Museum of Contemporary Photography; Milan, a minute before - Forma Foundation for photography; REcall - European Conflict Archaeological Landscape Reappropriation - Nordic Embassies in Berlin; OnLife - Vi lla Romana Florence; Metaphotography - BACO Bergamo; 55th Festival dei Popoli of Florence; 39th Bellaria Film Festival; 34e Cinemed - international festival du cin&eacute;ma m&eacute;diterran&eacute;en de Montpellier; The Shape of Things - The Chimera San Vito dei Normanni.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(30, 15, 'al', '<p>Puna &quot;Vegla b&euml;n Ustain&quot; lind gjat&euml; periudh&euml;s s&euml; rezidenc&euml;s s&euml; Bellomos n&euml; Tirana Art Lab n&euml; Tiran&euml;, dhe p&euml;r k&euml;t&euml; arsye ajo &euml;sht&euml; thell&euml;sisht e lidhur me dinamik&euml;n sociale t&euml; kryeqytetit. Artisti e p&euml;rq&euml;ndron v&euml;mendjen e tij pik&euml;risht n&euml; nj&euml; pik&euml; shum&euml; t&euml; frekuentuar n&euml; nj&euml; nga hyrjet e Tiran&euml;s: Sheshi Shqiponja, i njohur ndryshe p&euml;r qytetar&euml;t edhe si &ldquo;Dogana&rdquo;. Kjo hap&euml;sir&euml;, ​​jo vet&euml;m ishte e ngarkuar me automjete q&euml; hynin dhe dilnin nga kryeqyteti, por ishte edhe nj&euml; pik&euml; q&euml;ndrimi p&euml;r pun&euml;tor&euml;t e papun&euml; q&euml; me veglat e tyre prisnin q&euml; dikush t&#39;i pun&euml;sonte rast&euml;sisht. Duke patur mjetet e tyre gjithmon&euml; me vete, shanset p&euml;r t&rsquo;u pun&euml;suar n&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml; t&euml; shpejt&euml; prej dikujt q&euml; kalonte aty rriteshin. Nj&euml; sken&euml; e till&euml;, thuajse &ldquo;normale&rdquo; n&euml; kontekstin shqiptar&euml;, b&euml;het shtys&euml; p&euml;r vepr&euml;n e artistit Bellomo e cila zhvillohet si nj&euml; nd&euml;rhyrje/performanc&euml; dhe nj&euml; dokumentim i saj n&euml; fotografi/video. N&euml; k&euml;t&euml; rast artisti nuk &euml;sht&euml; interpretuesi; ai fton nj&euml; nga pun&euml;tor&euml;t t&euml; jet&euml; personazhi kryesor performues. Bellomo i k&euml;rkon punetorit t&euml; gdhend&euml; me &ccedil;eki&ccedil;in e tij n&euml; nj&euml; nga muret e Dogan&euml;s k&euml;to fjal&euml; n&euml; shqip: Vegla b&euml;n ustain. Nj&euml; citim i till&euml;, q&euml; p&euml;rdoret si nj&euml; th&euml;nie popullore n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri, b&euml;het e prekshme n&euml; mur dhe kthehet n&euml; pjes&euml; t&euml; integruar t&euml; sken&euml;s s&euml; pun&euml;torit q&euml; pret nj&euml; pun&euml;, nj&euml; mund&euml;si; q&euml; thjesht pret di&ccedil;ka. Puna e Bellomos &ldquo;Vegla b&euml;n Ustatin&rdquo; u realizua gjat&euml; q&euml;ndrimit t&euml; tij n&euml; rezidenc&euml; n&euml; Tirana Art Lab dhe u ekspozua n&euml; ekspozit&euml;n &ldquo;Double Feature #3 - Fabrizio Bellomo &amp; Elton Baxhaku&rdquo; n&euml; Tirana Art Lab.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Fabrizio Bellomo lindur n&euml; vitin 1982, jeton dhe punon n&euml; Bari, Itali. Ai &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; artist, kurator, shkrimtar dhe regjisor multidisiplinar q&euml; e kryen k&euml;rkimin e tij n&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml; hibride dhe eksperimentale. Qasja e tij ndaj artit &euml;sht&euml; e gjer&euml;: ai punon me materiale arkivore dhe historike, video dhe instalacione publike. Arti i tij kalon mes bot&euml;s reale dhe asaj dixhitale. Punimet e tij jan&euml; ekspozuar n&euml; ekspozita personale dhe kolektive, p&euml;rmes projekteve publike, festivaleve filmike dhe prezantimeve. Midis tyre: 38th Turin Film Festival; Archipelago Italy. Projects for the future of the country&#39;s internal territories &quot;- Italian Pavilion at the 16th International Architecture Exhibition of the Venice Biennale; There is time for medlars - ICCD Central Institute for Cataloging and Documentation Rome; REFOCUS, MiBACT - MuFoCo - Triennale di Milano; Italy Zokugo - Italian Cultural Institute Tokyo; About a City 2019 - Giangiacomo Feltrinelli Foundation Milan; &quot;Mechanism&quot; - KCB Kulturni Centar Beograda; Talent Prize 2017 - MACRO Contemporary Art Museum Rome; plat (t) form 2015 - Fotomuseum Winterthur; Unseen 2019 - Amsterdam; Teatri i Gjelberimit - Galeria Fab Tirana; Erosioni - Fundaci&ograve; Enric Miralles Barcelona; 2004-2014, Works and Projects of the Museum of Contemporary Photography - Triennale di Milano; ArtAround - MuFoCo Museum of Contemporary Photography; Milan, a minute before - Forma Foundation for photography; REcall - European Conflict Archaeological Landscape Reappropriation - Nordic Embassies in Berlin; OnLife - Villa Romana Florence; Metaphotography - BACO Bergamo; 55th Festival dei Popoli of Florence; 39th Bellaria Film Festival; 34e Cinemed - international festival du cin&eacute;ma m&eacute;diterran&eacute;en de Montpellier; The Shape of Things - The Chimera San Vito dei Normanni.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(31, 16, 'en', '<p>Bujari&rsquo;s action in public space for &ldquo;Bus Stops&rdquo; was born purely out of necessity. Back in 2006, in a city with many bus lines and stations, there were no bus schedules to inform the citizens about the system of public transportation. In such conditions, the artist takes upon himself a responsibility belonging to the Municipality of Tirana and creates a map of the bus lines operating in the capital. He installed the map illegally in several bus stops, covering up the advertisements that filled the public stations. Such a gesture might be interpreted as a &ldquo;gift&#39;&#39; to the citizens but it also functioned as a wake-up call for the structures which should be held responsible for these issues. Bujari&rsquo;s intervention deals with the needs of citizens within the city&rsquo;s context but also functions as an individual and protesting action by an artist who is part of the same context. Bujari, as an engaged artist, notices dysfunctionalities and through his actions/art highlights them by giving voice to those who usually stay silent and absorb everything the city does or does not offer. Bujari&rsquo;s intervention &ldquo;Bus Stops&rdquo; took place in May 2006, as part of the event &ldquo;1:60 Insurgent Space&rdquo; curated by Stefano Romano.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\nNikolin Bujari born 1984 in Shkodra, Albania lives and works in Tirana, Albania. He graduated from Tirana Art Academy in 2006 with Professor Edi Hila and was a guest student at the College of Design in Karlsruhe Germany in the Media class with Professor Mischa Kuball. Among others his works have been shown in exhibitions in institutions like: Badischer Kunstverein, Karlsruhe Germany; Nassauischer Kunstverein, Wiesbaden, Germany; Haus am L&uuml;tzowplatz, Berlin Germany; National Gallery of Art, Tirana Albania; 3-rd Tirana Biennale Albania, Tirana Art Lab - Center for Contemporary Art, etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(32, 16, 'al', '<p>Aksioni i Bujarit n&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml;n publike p&euml;r &ldquo;Stacionet e autobusit&rdquo; lind thjesht nga nevoja. N&euml; vitin 2006, n&euml; nj&euml; qytet me shum&euml; linja dhe stacione autobus&euml;sh, nuk ekzistonin ende orare t&euml; autobus&euml;ve p&euml;r t&euml; informuar qytetar&euml;t mbi sistemin e transportit publik. N&euml; kushte t&euml; tilla, artisti merr mbi vete nj&euml; p&euml;rgjegj&euml;si q&euml; i p&euml;rket Bashkis&euml; s&euml; Tiran&euml;s dhe krijon nj&euml; hart&euml; t&euml; linjave t&euml; autobus&euml;ve q&euml; operojn&euml; n&euml; kryeqytet. Ai e vendos hart&euml;n n&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml; t&euml; paligjshme n&euml; disa stacione autobus&euml;sh, duke mbuluar reklamat q&euml; mbushnin stacionet publike. Nj&euml; gjest i till&euml; mund t&euml; interpretohet si nj&euml; &ldquo;dhurat&euml;&rdquo; p&euml;r qytetar&euml;t, por sh&euml;rben edhe si nj&euml; paralajm&euml;rim p&euml;r strukturat q&euml; duhet t&euml; mbajn&euml; p&euml;rgjegj&euml;si p&euml;r k&euml;to &ccedil;&euml;shtje. Nd&euml;rhyrja e Bujarit trajton nevojat e qytetar&euml;ve brenda kontekstit t&euml; qytetit, por funksionon edhe si veprimi individual dhe protestues i nj&euml; artisti q&euml; &euml;sht&euml; pjes&euml; i t&euml; nj&euml;jtit realitet. Bujari, si nj&euml; artist i angazhuar, v&euml;ren mosmbar&euml;vajtje dhe p&euml;rmes veprimeve/artit t&euml; tij i v&euml; n&euml; dukje duke u dh&euml;n&euml; z&euml; atyre q&euml; zakonisht heshtin dhe thithin gjith&ccedil;ka q&euml; ofron ose nuk ofron qyteti. Nd&euml;rhyrja e Bujarit &ldquo;Stacionet e autobusit&rdquo; ndodhi n&euml; maj 2006, si pjes&euml; e eventit &ldquo;1:60 Insurgent Space&rdquo; kuruar nga Stefano Romano.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Nikolin Bujari i lindur m&euml; 1984 n&euml; Shkod&euml;r, Shqip&euml;ri jeton dhe punon n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. Ai u diplomua n&euml; Akademin&euml; e Arteve n&euml; Tiran&euml; n&euml; vitin 2006 me profesor Edi Hila dhe ishte student i ftuar n&euml; Kolegjin e Dizajnit n&euml; Karlsruhe, Gjermani n&euml; klas&euml;n Media Art &nbsp;me profesor Mischa Kuball. Nd&euml;r t&euml; tjerash, veprat e tij jan&euml; shfaqur n&euml; ekspozita e institucione si: Badischer Kunstverein, Karlsruhe Gjermani; Nassauischer Kunstverein, Wiesbaden, Gjermani; Haus am L&uuml;tzowplatz, Berlin Gjermani; Galeria Komb&euml;tare e Arteve, Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri; Bienalja e 3-t&euml; e Tiran&euml;s n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri, Tirana Art Lab - Qendra p&euml;r Artin Bashk&euml;kohor, etj.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(33, 17, 'en', '<p>In &quot;Bia Project&quot; (2017-2021), Donika &Ccedil;ina deals with Bia a famous lady who lived&nbsp;in Myslym Shyri Street; famous among citizens because she was constantly keeping clean and painting white the facade of her apartment but also part of the public street. Since her death, the apartment remained empty and the space once known for its cleanliness became dirty and started turning grey. Inspired by the collective memory of the city of Tirana, and the undefinable materially borders of the public space, on the 15th of October 2017 Donika &Ccedil;ina together with Katarina Staedtler headed to Rruga Myslym Shyri to reenact the everyday routine of cleaning and painting in lime the fa&ccedil;ade of Bia&rsquo;s house. Bia, not only refused to transform her house into a profitable service unit-like all other neighbors did but also manifested her refusal to change into a brightening everyday ritual promptly evident to the public. For technical malfunction, the video documentation of the performance,, is in a standby coma waiting to be recovered by a cleanroom procedure. While the exterior of the house is still intact, this little white house and a bright spot on a street promoting up-to-date consumerism resemble the futures of a social monument yet to disappear which, like a time-capsule interval, has grasped what was not recorded. For this reason, at this stage of the project, the artists <a href=\"https://greenterprise.eu/BIA2/BIA2.html\">encapsulated virtually</a> the sight of that fragment of the street and presented to the Municipality of Tirana a proposal to preserve the facade of the house by performing the same cleaning and painting ritual quotidianly and transform the house and that segment of the street into a permanent contemporary art intervention. The second part of &ldquo;Bia Project&rdquo; was produced during her residency at Tirana Art Lab - Center for Contemporary art, as part of Beyond Matter collaboration project.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Donika &Ccedil;ina born in 1988 in Kor&ccedil;a, Albania, studied at Academy of Arts in Tirana Albania, University of Arts and Design Cluj-Napoca Romania and at University of Art Braunschweig, Germany. She lives and works in Tirana, Albania. &Ccedil;ina works with video art, video installation, and short movies. The subject of most of her works is herself, her biography and the story of her family or those surrounding her. Her works often concentrate in capturing those specific moments where the inner perception of the individual and the exterior collective consciousness clash. By dealing with real stories and characters as well as historical events her works often operate in the field of historical documentation. Her works have been exhibited in numerous exhibitions including: MSUB/MoCAB Belgrade, Serbia; TIA MUCH KLIMA, Halle 50, Munich, Germany; Albania is not Cuba, Havana, Cuba; Dejeuner avec Marubi, Belvedere 21, Vienna, Austria; In-Between, Zeta Gallery, Tirana, Albania; Double Feature #7, Tirana Art Lab, Tirana, Albania; Ardhja Award, Zeta Gallery, Tirana, Albania; Tirana Open 1 Book and Art Festival, Tirana, Albania; Archivitionism (archivism-activism-exhibitionism), Galeria Plan B Cluj-Napoca, Romania; Autopia Cycle, Eliava Market, Tbilisi, Georgia; The Office Tirana, National Gallery, Tirana, Albania and Museo Orientale, Torino, Italy.</p>', NULL, NULL);
