(34, 17, 'al', '<p>N&euml; &quot;Projekti Bia&quot;, Donika &Ccedil;ina flet p&euml;r Bian nj&euml; zonj&euml; e famshme q&euml; jetonte n&euml; rrug&euml;n Myslym Shyri; ajo ishte e njohur mes qytetar&euml;ve sepse mbante vazhdimisht past&euml;r dhe lyente me gelqere t&euml; bardh&euml; fasad&euml;n e banes&euml;s s&euml; saj por edhe nj&euml; pjes&euml; t&euml; rrug&euml;s publike. Q&euml; prej vdekjes s&euml; saj, apartamenti mbeti i zbraz&euml;t dhe hap&euml;sira dikur e njohur p&euml;r past&euml;rti nisi t&euml; ndotej. Frym&euml;zuar nga kujtesa kolektive e qytetit t&euml; Tiran&euml;s dhe kufijt&euml; e pap&euml;rcaktuar materialisht t&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml;s publike, m&euml; 15 tetor 2017, Donika &Ccedil;ina s&euml; bashku me Katarina Staedler u nis&euml;n drejt Rrug&euml;s Myslym Shyri p&euml;r t&euml; rikthyer rutin&euml;n e p&euml;rditshme t&euml; pastrimit dhe lyerjes n&euml; g&euml;lqere te fasad&euml;s s&euml; sht&euml;pis&euml; s&euml; Bias. Bia, jo vet&euml;m q&euml; refuzoi ta transformonte sht&euml;pin&euml; e saj n&euml; nj&euml; nj&euml;si sh&euml;rbimi fitimprur&euml;se, si&ccedil; b&euml;n&euml; t&euml; gjith&euml; fqinj&euml;t e tjer&euml;, por gjithashtu shfaqi refuzimin e saj i cili u shnd&euml;rrua n&euml; nj&euml; ritual t&euml; p&euml;rditsh&euml;m t&euml; shndritsh&euml;m, i duksh&euml;m menj&euml;her&euml; p&euml;r publikun. P&euml;r mosfunksionim teknik videodokumentacioni i performanc&euml;s, &euml;sht&euml; n&euml; gjendje kome n&euml; pritje p&euml;r t&#39;u rimarr&euml; me pro&ccedil;edur&euml;n e &ldquo;dhom&euml;s s&euml; past&euml;r&rdquo;. Nd&euml;rsa pjesa e jashtme e sht&euml;pis&euml; &euml;sht&euml; ende e paprekur, kjo sht&euml;pi e vog&euml;l e bardh&euml; dhe nj&euml; vend i ndritsh&euml;m n&euml; nj&euml; rrug&euml; q&euml; promovon konsumizmin e sot&euml;m, perfaqson t&euml; ardhmen e nj&euml; monumenti social q&euml; rrezikon t&euml; zhduket, i cili, si brenda nje kapsule kohore, ka kapur at&euml; q&euml; nuk ishte regjistruar.&nbsp;P&euml;r k&euml;t&euml; arsye n&euml; k&euml;t&euml; faz&euml; t&euml; projektit artistjat <a href=\"https://greenterprise.eu/BIA2/BIA2.html\">p&euml;rmblodhi virtualisht</a> pamjen e atij fragmenti t&euml; rrug&euml;s dhe i paraqiti Bashkis&euml; s&euml; Tiran&euml;s nj&euml; propozim p&euml;r t&euml; ruajtur fasad&euml;n e sht&euml;pis&euml;, duke kryer t&euml; nj&euml;jtin ritual pastrimi dhe lyerjeje n&euml; m&euml;nyr&euml; konstante dhe duke e transformuar sht&euml;pin&euml; dhe ate segment t&euml; rrug&euml;s n&euml; nj&euml; nd&euml;rhyrje t&euml; p&euml;rhershme arti bashk&euml;kohor. Pjesa e dyt&euml; e &ldquo;Projekti Bia&rdquo; u realizua gjat&euml; rezidences s&euml; artistes n&euml; Tirana Art Lab &ndash; Qender p&euml;r Artin Bashk&euml;kohor, si pjes&euml; e projektit t&euml; bashk&euml;punimit Beyond Matter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Donika &Ccedil;ina lindur m&euml; 1988 n&euml; Kor&ccedil;&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri, ka studiuar n&euml; Akademin&euml; e Arteve n&euml; Tiran&euml;,&nbsp;Universitetin e Arteve dhe Dizajnit Cluj-Napoca Rumani dhe n&euml; Universitetin e Artit, Braunschweig, Gjermani. Ajo jeton n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. &Ccedil;ina punon me video art, video instalacion dhe filma t&euml; shkurt&euml;r. Subjekti i shumic&euml;s s&euml; veprave t&euml; saj &euml;sht&euml; ajo vet&euml;, biografia e saj dhe historia e familjes s&euml; saj apo atyre q&euml; e rrethojn&euml;. Veprat e saj shpesh p&euml;rqendrohen n&euml; kapjen e atyre momenteve specifike ku p&euml;rplasen perceptimi i brendsh&euml;m i individit dhe vet&euml;dija e jashtme kolektive. Duke u marr&euml; me histori dhe personazhe reale, si dhe me ngjarje historike, veprat e saj shpesh operojn&euml; n&euml; fush&euml;n e dokumentacionit historik. Punimet e saj jan&euml; ekspozuar n&euml; ekspozita t&euml; shumta duke p&euml;rfshir&euml;: &nbsp;MSUB/MoCAB Belgrade; TIA MUCH KLIMA, Halle 50, Munich; Albania is not Cuba, Havana; Dejeuner avec Marubi, Belvedere 21, Vienna; In-Between, Zeta Gallery, Tirana; Double Feature #7, Tirana Art Lab; Ardhja Award, Zeta Gallery, Tirana; Tirana Open 1 Book and Art Festival, Tirana; Archivitionism (archivism-activism-exhibitionism), Galeria Plan B Cluj-Napoca; Autopia Cycle, Eliava Market,Tbilisi; The Office Tirana, National Gallery, Tirana, and Museo Orientale, Torino.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(35, 18, 'en', '<p>The performance &quot;Use your mouth&quot;&nbsp;happened intentionally at the center of the capital, Skanderbeg Square, where HAVEIT brings an intimate, home-like situation as the act of eating a family meal altogether into the public context. This mechanism/game of inside-outside is brought in also through the basic act of eating, which during the performance relieves its shades of violence, pressure, and anger, becoming always more ambiguous towards the end. HAVEIT focuses on the concept of slavery in the family context but expands it also socially, by proposing their action outside, making it accessible in the city&rsquo;s center to everyone, and by provoking deep reflection through mixed sensations.<br />\r\n&ldquo;Use your mouth&rdquo; happened during the one-month residency in Tirana, organized by LGBT Alliance Tirana and The Unstraight Museum Stockholm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\nHaveit is an artistic collective of 4 girls from Kosovo: Hana and Vesa Qena and Alketa and Lola Sylaj, who use the medium of public performances, photography, and video to explore social issues in Kosovo, such as strengthening the social position of women, LGBT + community rights as well as many other topics. The collective was founded in 2011, as a form of protest after the murder of Diana Kastrati, in the city center by her ex-husband. Haveit, are characterized by their artistic performances on the streets, which in most cases protest against patriarchal domination in Kosovo, gender stereotypes, discrimination against women, and the LGBT + community. In 2018, the Haveit collective received the Democracy Award shared by the Open Society Foundations as a promoter of democracy in the country, reacting to gender inequality, violence against women, and discrimination against the LGBT community.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(36, 18, 'al', '<p>Performanca &quot;Jepi me goj&euml;&quot; u zhvillua q&euml;llimisht n&euml; qend&euml;r t&euml; kryeqytetit, n&euml; sheshin Sk&euml;nderbej, ku HAVEIT sjell nga konteksti privat n&euml; kontekstin publik nj&euml; situat&euml; intime, si&ccedil; &euml;sht&euml; akti i t&euml; ngr&euml;nit t&euml; nj&euml; vakti familjar n&euml; sht&euml;pi. Ky mekaniz&euml;m brenda-jasht&euml; &euml;sht&euml; i pranish&euml;m n&euml; performanc&euml; edhe n&euml;p&euml;rmjet aktit bazik t&euml; ushqyerjes, i cili gjat&euml; performanc&euml;s merr nuanca dhune, presioni dhe zem&euml;rimi, duke u b&euml;r&euml; gjithnj&euml; m&euml; i paqart&euml; drejt fundit. HAVEIT fokusohet n&euml; konceptin e skllav&euml;ris&euml; brenda kontekstit familjar, por e zgjeron at&euml; edhe n&euml; aspektin social, me propozimin e performanc&euml;s publike n&euml; qend&euml;r t&euml; qytetit, duke e b&euml;r&euml; at&euml; t&euml; aksesueshme nga kushdo dhe duke provokuar k&euml;shtu nj&euml; reflektim t&euml; thell&euml; p&euml;rmes ndjesish t&euml; p&euml;rziera.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Jepi me goj&euml;&rdquo; u realizua gjat&euml; q&euml;ndrimit nj&euml;mujor t&euml; HAVEIT n&euml; Tiran&euml; n&euml; rezidenc&euml;n e organizuar nga Aleanca LGBT Tirana dhe The Unstraight Museum Stockholm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Haveit jan&euml; nj&euml; kolektiv artistik i p&euml;rb&euml;r&euml; prej kat&euml;r vajzash nga Kosova: Hana e Vesa Qena dhe Alketa e Lola Sylaj, t&euml; cilat p&euml;rdorin mediumin e performancave publike, fotografis&euml; dhe videos p&euml;r t&euml; eksploruar &ccedil;&euml;shtjet sociale n&euml; Kosov&euml;, si fuqizimi i pozit&euml;s shoq&euml;rore t&euml; gruas, t&euml; drejtat e komunitetit LGBT+ si dhe plot tema t&euml; tjera. Kolektivi u themelua n&euml; vitin 2011, si form&euml; proteste pas vrasjes s&euml; Diana Kastratit, n&euml; qend&euml;r t&euml; qytetit nga ish-burri i saj. Haveit, karakterizohen p&euml;r p&euml;rformancat e tyre artistike n&euml; rrug&euml;, q&euml; n&euml; t&euml; shumt&euml;n e rasteve protestojn&euml; kund&euml;r dominanc&euml;s patriarkale n&euml; Kosov&euml;, steriotipeve gjinore, diskriminimit t&euml; gruas dhe komunitetit LGBT+. P&euml;r vitin 2018, kolektivi Haveit mori &Ccedil;mimin p&euml;r Demokraci i ndar&euml; nga Fondacioni p&euml;r Shoq&euml;ri t&euml; Hapur, si nxit&euml;s i demokracis&euml; n&euml; vend, duke reaguar ndaj pabarazis&euml; gjinore, dhun&euml;s ndaj grave dhe diskriminimit t&euml; komunitetit LGBT.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(37, 19, 'en', '<p>The work &ldquo;I need a radical change&rdquo; started appearing around the city of Tirana as a personal repetitive protest of artist Dren Maliqi. One of the spots where it was placed was in front of the Academy of Fine Arts in Tirana, to express a necessity for change that he and his generation experienced while studying at a similar institution. By using the word &ldquo;I&rdquo; instead of &ldquo;us&rdquo;, Maliqi shifts the focus of responsibility first on himself and fosters a reflective process about change that needs to start first with each of us; without changing oneself no other changes can be made. &nbsp;While the stencil writing and its message remain the same by being placed in diverse spots around the city, it generates new meaning every time as it allows the citizens to identify with it no matter their cause.<br />\r\nMaliqi&rsquo;s intervention &ldquo;I need a radical change&rdquo; took place in December 2005, as part of the event &ldquo;1:60 Insurgent Space&rdquo; curated by Stefano Romano.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Dren Maliqi born in 1981 in Pristina, Kosovo lives and works in Pristina, Kosovo. He has studied Arts and Sociology at the University of Pristina. As an artist and independent cultural worker, he is constantly engaged in a range of cultural projects in Kosovo. Selected exhibitions include: The Whale That Was a Submarine, Ludwig Museum of Contemporary Art, Budapest, Hungary; Muslim Mulliqi International Art Prize, National Gallery of Kosovo, Pristina; In the Gorges of the Balkans, Kunsthalle Fridericianum, Kassel, Germany.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(38, 19, 'al', '<p>Puna &ldquo;M&rsquo;vyn ndrrim radikar&rdquo; nisi t&euml; shfaqej n&euml;p&euml;r qytetin e Tiran&euml;s si nj&euml; protest&euml; personale e p&euml;rs&euml;ritur e artistit Dren Maliqi. Nj&euml; nga pikat ku u shfaq ishte p&euml;rball&euml; Akademis&euml; s&euml; Arteve t&euml; Bukura n&euml; Tiran&euml;, p&euml;r t&euml; shprehur domosdoshm&euml;rin&euml; e ndryshimit q&euml; ai dhe brezi i tij p&euml;rjetuan gjat&euml; studimeve n&euml; nj&euml; institucion t&euml; ngjash&euml;m. Me an&euml; t&euml; k&euml;saj pune Maliqi e zhvendos fokusin e p&euml;rgjegj&euml;sis&euml; s&euml; pari tek vetja dhe nxit nj&euml; proces reflektimi kundrejt ndryshimit q&euml; duhet t&euml; nis&euml; s&euml; pari me secilin prej nesh; pa ndryshuar fillimisht veten nuk mund t&euml; b&euml;hen ndryshime t&euml; tjera. Nd&euml;rsa shkrimi dhe mesazhi i tij mbetet njesoj teksa vendoset n&euml; pika t&euml; ndryshme n&euml;p&euml;r qytet, ai gjeneron kuptim t&euml; ri &ccedil;do her&euml; pasi lejon qytetar&euml;t t&euml; identifikohen me t&euml; pavar&euml;shisht kauz&euml;s s&euml; gjithsecilit. Nd&euml;rhyrja e Maliqit &ldquo;M&rsquo;vyn ndrrim radikar&rdquo; ndodhi n&euml; dhjetor 2005, si pjes&euml; e eventit &ldquo;1:60 Insurgent Space&rdquo; kuruar nga Stefano Romano.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Dren Maliqi lindur m&euml; 1981 n&euml; Prishtin&euml;, Kosov&euml; jeton dhe punon n&euml; Prishtin&euml;, Kosov&euml;. Ai ka studiuar Arte dhe Sociologji n&euml; Universitetin e Prishtin&euml;s. Si artist dhe pun&euml;tor i pavarur kulturor ka qen&euml; vazhdimisht i angazhuar n&euml; nj&euml; s&euml;r&euml; projektesh kulturore n&euml; Kosov&euml;. Ekspozitat e p&euml;rzgjedhura p&euml;rfshijn&euml;: The Whale That Was a Submarine, Ludwig Museum of Contemporary Art, Budapest, Hungari; &Ccedil;mimi Nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar i Artit Muslim Mulliqi, Galeria Komb&euml;tare e Kosov&euml;s, Prishtin&euml;; In the Gorges of the Balkans, Kunsthalle Fridericianum, Kassel, Gjermani.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(39, 20, 'en', '<p>&ldquo;Last Hope&rdquo; shows the journey of a geodesic dome from its construction location to its final destination: The artificial lake of Tirana. Zaloshnja creates such an object with the idea of it functioning as an aquaculture platform in the waters of the lake, which has been decreasing year after year. Intentionally, he chooses to document the journey of the dome on the transport truck along the streets of the city where concrete construction is noticed everywhere the dome passes. The artist creates a parallelism between two worlds, that of nature and of man, which in the second case is over-doing. He chooses to nourish the world of nature, by doing a symbolic yet powerful act of letting the dome go in the waters, carrying beans, more or less like &ldquo;Noah&rsquo;s Ark&rdquo; as the artist himself sees it. As the dome sails peacefully, two written words, one for each side, are distinguished on it, that when read together take a whole different meaning: Last Hope.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Ergin Zaloshnja&nbsp;born in 1979 in&nbsp;Tirana, Albania is a visual artist and activist who currently lives and works in Tirana, Albania. He studied at the Academy of Fine Arts in Florence graduating in 2012. Besides his primary media - photography, installation, and video - he has developed a series of street art interventions under the pseudonym Diver Santi. He is also the founder of the political and subculture fanzine Sputnik and a collaborator of D.C.C.A, Debatik Center of Contemporary Art, Tirana. Zaloshnja is also an art educator on the subculture of street art: in 2017 he was one of the workshop leaders during the International Documentary and Short Film Festival held in Prizren, Kosova for MARUBI x DOKUPHOTO, a collaboration program between DokuFest and the Marubi National Museum of Photography in Shkoder. Apart from his solo exhibition DE-LUDII, Miza Gallery, Tirana, and personal outdoors intervention Weed Nation - Gallery On The Move, Tirana, he has mainly participated in group exhibitions and collaborative projects, among which the most notable are: Videos aus Albanien, Blickle Kino - Belvedere Museum, Vienna ; shitet toka - Aktuelle Anmerkungen zu Albanien, HDA &ndash; Haus der Architektur, Graz; Double Feature #8, Tirana Art Lab, Tirana; Stranger than Kindness, 22nd International Onufri Prize, National Art Gallery, Tirana; Teatri I Gjelb&euml;rimit - Department of Eagles, FAB Gallery, Tirana;&nbsp;Tirana Open1-Project Ultra - SPUTNIK production, Tirana,&nbsp;Let Us Start From The Middle, Tirana Art Lab, Tirana; Praise of Doubt, 20th International Onufri Prize, National Art Gallery, Tirana;&nbsp;Nj&euml;qind vjet vet&euml;var&euml;si, Tirana Art Lab; Tools For Revolution Or Just For Sale - ROTTE METROPOLITANE. Firenze &egrave; sommersa, Villa Romana, Florence ;&nbsp;Our Nature,&nbsp;Villa Serena, Bologna; Contested Space, Spazio Alcatraz, Stazione Leopolda, Florence; U-Topos, 2nd Tirana Biennale,&nbsp;Debatik Center of Contemporary Art, Tirana ; Networking City: La citt&agrave; della gente, Ex Macelli, Prato; The Promised Land, O&#39; Artoteca, Milan; Networking, Palazzo delle Papesse, Siena; Networking, Ex Macelli, Prato.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(40, 20, 'al', '<p>&ldquo;Shpresa e fundit&rdquo; tregon udh&euml;timin e nj&euml; kupole gjeodezike nga vendi i nd&euml;rtimit deri n&euml; destinacionin e saj p&euml;rfundimtar: Liqeni artificial i Tiran&euml;s. Zaloshnja e krijon nj&euml; objekt t&euml; till&euml; me iden&euml; q&euml; ai t&euml; funksionoj&euml; si nj&euml; platform&euml; akua-kulture n&euml; uj&euml;rat e liqenit, t&euml; cilat kan&euml; ardhur duke u pak&euml;suar vit pas viti. Me dashje ai zgjedh t&euml; dokumentoj&euml; udh&euml;timin e kupol&euml;s n&euml; kamionin e transportit p&euml;rgjat&euml; rrug&euml;ve t&euml; qytetit ku v&euml;rehen nd&euml;rtime betoni kudo ku kupola kalon. Artisti krijon nj&euml; paraleliz&euml;m mes dy bot&euml;ve, asaj t&euml; natyr&euml;s dhe t&euml; njeriut, q&euml; n&euml; rastin e dyt&euml; &euml;sht&euml; e tepruar. Ai zgjedh t&euml; ushqej&euml; bot&euml;n e natyr&euml;s, duke b&euml;r&euml; nj&euml; akt simbolik por t&euml; fuqish&euml;m me l&euml;nien e kupol&euml;s n&euml; uj&euml;rat e liqenit. Mbartese farash, ajo i shembellen &quot;Ark&euml;s s&euml; Noes&quot; sipas artistit. E teksa kupola lundron paq&euml;sisht, mbi t&euml; dallohen t&euml; shkruara dy fjal&euml;, nga nj&euml; p&euml;r secil&euml;n an&euml; te kupoles, t&euml; cilat kur lexohen s&euml; bashku marrin nj&euml; kuptim krejt tjet&euml;r: Shpresa e Fundit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">​​Ergin Zaloshnja i lindur m&euml; 1979 n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; artist dhe aktivist pamor i cili aktualisht jeton dhe punon n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. Ai studioi n&euml; Akademin&euml; e Arteve t&euml; Bukura n&euml; Firence duke u diplomuar n&euml; vitin 2012. P&euml;rve&ccedil; medias s&euml; tij kryesore - fotografis&euml;, instalacionit dhe video - ai ka zhvilluar nj&euml; s&euml;r&euml; nd&euml;rhyrjesh n&euml; artin e rrug&euml;s me pseudonimin Diver Santi. Ai &euml;sht&euml; gjithashtu themeluesi i fanzin&euml;s politike dhe subkulturore Sputnik dhe bashk&euml;pun&euml;tor i Debatik Q&euml;ndra e Artit Bashk&euml;kohor. Zaloshnja &euml;sht&euml; gjithashtu nj&euml; edukator arti n&euml; n&euml;nkultur&euml;n e artit t&euml; rrug&euml;s: n&euml; vitin 2017 ai ishte nj&euml; nga udh&euml;heq&euml;sit e seminareve gjat&euml; Festivalit Nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar t&euml; Filmit Dokumentar dhe t&euml; Shkurt&euml;r t&euml; mbajtur n&euml; Prizren, Kosov&euml; p&euml;r MARUBI x DOKUPHOTO, nj&euml; program bashk&euml;punimi midis DokuFest dhe Muzeut Komb&euml;tar i Fotografis&euml; Marubi n&euml; Shkod&euml;r. P&euml;rve&ccedil; ekspozit&euml;s s&euml; tij vetjake DE-LUDII, Galeria Miza, Tiran&euml; dhe nd&euml;rhyrjes personale n&euml; natyr&euml; Weed Nation - Galeria On The Move, Tiran&euml;, ai ka marr&euml; pjes&euml; kryesisht n&euml; ekspozita grupore dhe projekte bashk&euml;punuese, nd&euml;r t&euml; cilat m&euml; t&euml; dalluarat jan&euml;: Videos aus Albanien, Blickle Cinema - Belvedere Museum, Vienna; for sale land - Current services for Albania, HDA - House of Architecture, Graz; Double Feature # 8, Tirana Art Lab, Tiran&euml;; Stranger than Kindness, &Ccedil;mimi i 22-t&euml; Nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar Onufri, Galeria Komb&euml;tare e Arteve, Tiran&euml;; Teatri i Gjelb&euml;rimit - Departments of Eagles, Galeria FAB, Tiran&euml;; Tirana Open1-Project Ultra - prodhim SPUTNIK, Tiran&euml;, Let us start from the middle, Tirana Art Lab, Tiran&euml;; Praise of Doubt, &Ccedil;mimi i 20-t&euml; Nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar Onufri, Galeria Komb&euml;tare e Arteve, Tiran&euml;; Nj&euml;qind vjet vet&euml;var&euml;si, Tirana Art Lab; Tools For Revolution Or Just For Sale - ROTTE METROPOLITANE. Florence&#39;s sommersa, Villa Romana, Florence; Our Nature, Villa Serena, Bologna; Contested Space, Spazio Alcatraz, Stazione Leopolda, Firence; U-Topos, 2nd Tirana Biennale, Debatik Center of Contemporary Art, Tirana; Networking City: La citt&agrave; della gente, Ex Macelli, Prato; The Promised Land, O &#39;Artoteca, Milano; Networking, Palazzo delle Papesse, Siena; Networking, Ex Macelli, Prato.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(41, 21, 'en', '<p>&ldquo;Epopee of the Excavator&rdquo; might sound like an epic title but it&rsquo;s born from the real, contemporary citizens&rsquo; problems of Tirana: in this case those living in the area Bregu i&nbsp;Lumit, mainly poor families belonging to the marginalized Egyptian and Rom community. &nbsp;Individualized as an area for rehabilitation from the Municipality, this area is facing the destruction of the houses of the families actually living there, seen as useless. On one of these houses intended for demolition, &Ccedil;ETA installs the powerful figure of Mic Sokoli facing an excavator with his chest. Mic Sokoli was a famous Albanian nationalist fighter who fell during the battle of Slivova, by putting his own chest in front of a cannon. Such a heroic gesture was painted by famous Albanian painter Sali Shijaku in &nbsp;1969 - a memorable image in Albanian art history. &Ccedil;ETA uses such an image by replacing the cannon with an excavator and adding a contemporary accent to their finished work: The sacrifice of Sokoli stands in solidarity with those in danger from the &ldquo;excavators&rdquo;. This work was realized in collaboration with art historian Raino Isto and the community of citizens living in the area affected by the demolition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\n&Ccedil;ETA&nbsp;is a political street art collective formed by students, activists, and artists. In spring 2016 they began to discuss the formation of a group to oppose the hegemonic structures of capitalist and neoliberal politics and economics in contemporary Albania. From these discussions, a group of street artists&mdash;individually anonymous but known collectively as &Ccedil;ETA&mdash;emerged. The group takes its name from the word used to describe the groups of antifascist guerilla fighters active in the Balkans during the Second World War, and its mission is to use street art as a weapon&mdash;however modest&mdash;in a broader struggle against neoliberal policies dominating Albanian universities, against the destruction of Tirana&rsquo;s few remaining green spaces, and in favor of free public transportation. Functioning as a true collective, the group is made up of members of various ages, with various backgrounds: designers, political scientists, artists, architects.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(42, 21, 'al', '<p>&ldquo;Epopeja e ekskavatorit&rdquo; mund t&euml; ting&euml;lloj&euml; si nj&euml; titull epik, por n&euml; t&euml; v&euml;rtet&euml; lind nga problemet reale, bashk&euml;kohore t&euml; qytetar&euml;ve t&euml; Tiran&euml;s: n&euml; k&euml;t&euml; rast ata jan&euml; qytetar&euml;t q&euml; jetojn&euml; n&euml; zon&euml;n e Bregut t&euml; Lumit, kryesisht familje t&euml; varfra q&euml; i p&euml;rkasin komunitetit t&euml; margjinalizuar egjiptian dhe rom. E individualizuar si zon&euml; rehabilitimi prej Bashkis&euml; s&euml; Tiran&euml;s, kjo zon&euml; po p&euml;rballet me rr&euml;nimin e banesave t&euml; familjeve q&euml; jetojn&euml; realisht aty, t&euml; konsideruara si t&euml; padobishme. N&euml; nj&euml;r&euml;n prej k&euml;tyre sht&euml;pive t&euml; destinuara p&euml;r sh&euml;mbje, &Ccedil;ETA vendos figur&euml;n e fuqishme t&euml; Mic Sokolit me gjoksin p&euml;rball&euml; nj&euml; ekskavatori. Mic Sokoli ishte nj&euml; luft&euml;tar i famsh&euml;m nacionalist shqiptar, i cili vdiq gjat&euml; betej&euml;s s&euml; Slivov&euml;s, pik&euml;risht duke v&euml;n&euml; gjoksin para topit armik. Nj&euml; gjest i till&euml; heroik &euml;sht&euml; pikturuar nga piktori i njohur shqiptar Sali Shijaku n&euml; vitin 1969 - nj&euml; imazh i paharruesh&euml;m n&euml; historin&euml; e artit shqiptar. &Ccedil;ETA e p&euml;rdor nj&euml; imazh t&euml; till&euml; duke z&euml;vend&euml;suar topin me nj&euml; ekskavator dhe duke i shtuar nj&euml; theks bashk&euml;kohor pun&euml;s s&euml; tyre t&euml; p&euml;rfunduar: Sakrifica e Sokolit solidarizohet me ata q&euml; rrezikohen nga &ldquo;ekskavator&euml;t&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">&Ccedil;ETA &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; kolektiv politik i artit rrugor i formuar nga student&euml;, aktivist&euml; dhe artist&euml;. N&euml; pranver&euml;n e 2016-&euml;s ata filluan t&euml; diskutojn&euml; formimin e nj&euml; grupi p&euml;r t&euml; kund&euml;rshtuar strukturat hegjemoniste t&euml; politik&euml;s dhe ekonomis&euml; kapitaliste dhe neoliberale n&euml; Shqip&euml;rin&euml; bashk&euml;kohore. Nga k&euml;to diskutime, doli nj&euml; grup artist&euml;sh t&euml; rrug&euml;s &ndash; individualisht anonim&euml;, por t&euml; njohur kolektivisht si &Ccedil;ETA. Grupi e ka marr&euml; emrin nga fjala e p&euml;rdorur p&euml;r t&euml; p&euml;rshkruar grupet e luft&euml;tar&euml;ve antifashist&euml; guerile aktiv&euml; n&euml; Ballkan gjat&euml; Luft&euml;s s&euml; Dyt&euml; Bot&euml;rore dhe misioni i tij &euml;sht&euml; t&euml; p&euml;rdor&euml; artin e rrug&euml;s si nj&euml; arm&euml; - sado modest - n&euml; nj&euml; luft&euml; m&euml; t&euml; gjer&euml; kund&euml;r politikave neoliberale q&euml; dominojn&euml; Universitetet shqiptare, kund&euml;r shkat&euml;rrimit t&euml; pak hap&euml;sirave t&euml; gjelbra t&euml; mbetura t&euml; Tiran&euml;s dhe n&euml; favor t&euml; transportit publik falas. Duke funksionuar si nj&euml; kolektiv i v&euml;rtet&euml;, grupi p&euml;rb&euml;het nga an&euml;tar&euml; t&euml; moshave t&euml; ndryshme, me prejardhje t&euml; ndryshme: dezaijnera, politolog&euml;, artist&euml;, arkitekt&euml;.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(43, 22, 'en', '<p>The&nbsp;work &quot;Don&rsquo;t buy leeks, buy dynamite (Grandma Zylja strikes again)&quot;&nbsp;is inspired by an incident happening to Grandma Zylja, a 69-year old woman coming from the nearby villages to sell vegetables in Tirana, as many other ambulant sellers do. She was fined and her merchandise (merely leeks) was confiscated by the Municipality police in Myslym Shyri street, one of the busiest shopping streets of Tirana. Shortly after, a photograph of the incident circulated on the Internet and became viral, &ldquo;forcing&rdquo; the mayor of Tirana, Erion Veliaj, to pay the fee for Grandma Zylja and even publicly embrace her. The viral image of the incident is also the basis of this &Ccedil;ETA work where they add a dramatic touch: by substituting the leeks with dynamite, they give to Grandma Zylja and also to the other citizens a power they don&rsquo;t have against the system, in this case, the Municipality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\n&Ccedil;ETA&nbsp;is a political street art collective formed by students, activists, and artists. In spring 2016 they began to discuss the formation of a group to oppose the hegemonic structures of capitalist and neoliberal politics and economics in contemporary Albania. From these discussions, a group of street artists&mdash;individually anonymous but known collectively as &Ccedil;ETA&mdash;emerged. The group takes its name from the word used to describe the groups of antifascist guerilla fighters active in the Balkans during the Second World War, and its mission is to use street art as a weapon&mdash;however modest&mdash;in a broader struggle against neoliberal policies dominating Albanian universities, against the destruction of Tirana&rsquo;s few remaining green spaces, and in favor of free public transportation. Functioning as a true collective, the group is made up of members of various ages, with various backgrounds: designers, political scientists, artists, architects.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(44, 22, 'al', '<p>Puna &ldquo;Mos bli presh, bli dinamit (Non Zylja godet s&euml;risht)&rdquo; frym&euml;zohet nga incidenti i ndodhur me non Zylen, nj&euml; grua 69-vje&ccedil;are e cila vinte &ccedil;do dit&euml; nga fshatrat e af&euml;rta t&euml; kryeqytetit p&euml;r t&euml; shitur perime n&euml; Tiran&euml;, ashtu si&ccedil; b&euml;jn&euml; shum&euml; shit&euml;s t&euml; tjer&euml; ambulant&euml;. Non Zylja u gjobit dhe malli i saj, pra thjesht preshi, u konfiskua nga policia bashkiake n&euml; rrug&euml;n Myslym Shyri, nj&euml; nga rrug&euml;t m&euml; t&euml; frekuentuara t&euml; Tiran&euml;s ku mbizot&euml;rojn&euml; dyqanet. Menj&euml;her&euml; pas k&euml;saj ndodhie, nj&euml; fotografi e ngjarjes qarkulloi n&euml; internet dhe u b&euml; virale, duke &ldquo;detyruar&rdquo; kryebashkiakun e Tiran&euml;s, Erion Veliaj, t&euml; paguaj&euml; gjoben p&euml;r non Zylen dhe madje ta p&euml;rqafoj&euml; at&euml; publikisht. Imazhi viral i incidentit u kthye n&euml; baz&euml;n e k&euml;saj pune, ku &Ccedil;ETA fal nj&euml; prekje dramatike: ata z&euml;vend&euml;sojne preshin me dinamit, duke i dh&euml;n&euml; k&euml;shtu non Zyles dhe qytetar&euml;ve t&euml; tjer&euml; t&euml; Tiran&euml;s nj&euml; lloj fuqie q&euml; nuk e kan&euml; aktualisht kund&euml;r sistemit, n&euml; k&euml;t&euml; rast kund&euml;r Bashkis&euml;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">&Ccedil;ETA &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; kolektiv politik i artit rrugor i formuar nga student&euml;, aktivist&euml; dhe artist&euml;. N&euml; pranver&euml;n e 2016-&euml;s ata filluan t&euml; diskutojn&euml; formimin e nj&euml; grupi p&euml;r t&euml; kund&euml;rshtuar strukturat hegjemoniste t&euml; politik&euml;s dhe ekonomis&euml; kapitaliste dhe neoliberale n&euml; Shqip&euml;rin&euml; bashk&euml;kohore. Nga k&euml;to diskutime, doli nj&euml; grup artist&euml;sh t&euml; rrug&euml;s &ndash; individualisht anonim&euml;, por t&euml; njohur kolektivisht si &Ccedil;ETA. Grupi e ka marr&euml; emrin nga fjala e p&euml;rdorur p&euml;r t&euml; p&euml;rshkruar grupet e luft&euml;tar&euml;ve antifashist&euml; guerile aktiv&euml; n&euml; Ballkan gjat&euml; Luft&euml;s s&euml; Dyt&euml; Bot&euml;rore dhe misioni i tij &euml;sht&euml; t&euml; p&euml;rdor&euml; artin e rrug&euml;s si nj&euml; arm&euml; - sado modest - n&euml; nj&euml; luft&euml; m&euml; t&euml; gjer&euml; kund&euml;r politikave neoliberale q&euml; dominojn&euml; Universitetet shqiptare, kund&euml;r shkat&euml;rrimit t&euml; pak hap&euml;sirave t&euml; gjelbra t&euml; mbetura t&euml; Tiran&euml;s dhe n&euml; favor t&euml; transportit publik falas. Duke funksionuar si nj&euml; kolektiv i v&euml;rtet&euml;, grupi p&euml;rb&euml;het nga an&euml;tar&euml; t&euml; moshave t&euml; ndryshme, me prejardhje t&euml; ndryshme: dezaijnera, politolog&euml;, artist&euml;, arkitekt&euml;.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(45, 23, 'en', '<p>&quot;Smash the walls of privilege (Remember the 1st of May)&quot; intervention by &Ccedil;ETA&nbsp;representing a manual worker smashing with a hammer a cash bankomat, comes as no surprise on the 1st of May, Day of Labour - the symbology of the elements they have used in this work can be read easily as a sign of protest and discontent regarding the worker&rsquo;s position in Albania. &Ccedil;ETA, which usually gives a statement for every intervention they make, has chosen to remain silent about this one, because to them a day and moment like the 1st of May, doesn&rsquo;t need many explanations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\n&Ccedil;ETA&nbsp;is a political street art collective formed by students, activists, and artists. In spring 2016 they began to discuss the formation of a group to oppose the hegemonic structures of capitalist and neoliberal politics and economics in contemporary Albania. &nbsp;From these discussions, a group of street artists&mdash;individually anonymous but known collectively as &Ccedil;ETA&mdash;emerged. The group takes its name from the word used to describe the groups of antifascist guerilla fighters active in the Balkans during the Second World War, and its mission is to use street art as a weapon&mdash;however modest&mdash;in a broader struggle against neoliberal policies dominating Albanian universities, against the destruction of Tirana&rsquo;s few remaining green spaces, and in favor of free public transportation. Functioning as a true collective, the group is made up of members of various ages, with various backgrounds: designers, political scientists, artists, architects.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(46, 23, 'al', '<p>Puna dhe nd&euml;rhyrja&nbsp;&ldquo;Shkallmoni muret e priviligjeve! (Kujtoni 1 Majin)&rdquo;&nbsp;q&euml; na&nbsp;p&euml;rball me nj&euml; pun&euml;tor krahu i cili godet&nbsp;me nj&euml; &ccedil;eki&ccedil; nj&euml; bankomat parash, nuk vjen e papritur me rastin e 1 Majit, Dita e Pun&euml;tor&euml;ve, pasi simbologjia e elementeve t&euml; p&euml;rdorur n&euml; k&euml;t&euml; pun&euml; mund t&euml; lexohet leht&euml;sisht si nj&euml; shenj&euml; proteste dhe pak&euml;naq&euml;sie ndaj pozicionit t&euml; puntorit n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri. &Ccedil;ETA, q&euml; zakonisht shprehet edhe me an&euml; t&euml; shkrimeve p&euml;r nd&euml;rhyrjet q&euml; kryen, ka zgjedhur t&euml; q&euml;ndroj&euml; n&euml; heshtje n&euml; lidhje me k&euml;t&euml; pun&euml;, sepse sipas tyre nj&euml; dit&euml; dhe moment historik si 1 Maji, nuk ka nevoj&euml; &nbsp;p&euml;r shum&euml; shpjegime.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">&Ccedil;ETA &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; kolektiv politik i artit rrugor i formuar nga student&euml;, aktivist&euml; dhe artist&euml;. N&euml; pranver&euml;n e 2016-&euml;s ata filluan t&euml; diskutojn&euml; formimin e nj&euml; grupi p&euml;r t&euml; kund&euml;rshtuar strukturat hegjemoniste t&euml; politik&euml;s dhe ekonomis&euml; kapitaliste dhe neoliberale n&euml; Shqip&euml;rin&euml; bashk&euml;kohore. Nga k&euml;to diskutime, doli nj&euml; grup artist&euml;sh t&euml; rrug&euml;s &ndash; individualisht anonim&euml;, por t&euml; njohur kolektivisht si &Ccedil;ETA. Grupi e ka marr&euml; emrin nga fjala e p&euml;rdorur p&euml;r t&euml; p&euml;rshkruar grupet e luft&euml;tar&euml;ve antifashist&euml; guerile aktiv&euml; n&euml; Ballkan gjat&euml; Luft&euml;s s&euml; Dyt&euml; Bot&euml;rore dhe misioni i tij &euml;sht&euml; t&euml; p&euml;rdor&euml; artin e rrug&euml;s si nj&euml; arm&euml; - sado modest - n&euml; nj&euml; luft&euml; m&euml; t&euml; gjer&euml; kund&euml;r politikave neoliberale q&euml; dominojn&euml; Universitetet shqiptare, kund&euml;r shkat&euml;rrimit t&euml; pak hap&euml;sirave t&euml; gjelbra t&euml; mbetura t&euml; Tiran&euml;s dhe n&euml; favor t&euml; transportit publik falas. Duke funksionuar si nj&euml; kolektiv i v&euml;rtet&euml;, grupi p&euml;rb&euml;het nga an&euml;tar&euml; t&euml; moshave t&euml; ndryshme, me prejardhje t&euml; ndryshme: dezaijnera, politolog&euml;, artist&euml;, arkitekt&euml;.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(47, 24, 'en', '<p>&ldquo;Vojo Kushi is still alive&rdquo; is &Ccedil;ETA&rsquo;s first work produced in April 2016. &Ccedil;ETA starts working and acting with the idea to bring back edited paintings of social-realism in a contemporary Albanian context. The first one is a painting by Sali Shijaku of albanian-yugoslav guerrilla fighter Vojo Kushi, who is remembered for a heroic death. Shijaku&rsquo;s painting depicts a scene happening in the Tirana of 1942, where Kushi and other partisans were surrounded by Italian fascist forces. In one moment Kushi runs out and jumps on an enemy tank, throwing a grenade into it before being killed by the fascist. &Ccedil;ETA brings Kushi&rsquo;s act back in a contemporary context by replacing the grenade in his hand with a Molotov cocktail and the fascist tank with a black Jaguar car (as those purchased by the government back in 2016) holding the Prime Minister&rsquo;s Edi Rama license plate number by making a reference to the actual Rilindja government of Albania. For &Ccedil;ETA, in this new context, Kushi represents the people standing together against any kind of power system.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">&Ccedil;ETA&nbsp;is a political street art collective formed by students, activists, and artists. In spring 2016 they began to discuss the formation of a group to oppose the hegemonic structures of capitalist and neoliberal politics and economics in contemporary Albania. From these discussions, a group of street artists&mdash;individually anonymous but known collectively as &Ccedil;ETA&mdash;emerged. The group takes its name from the word used to describe the groups of antifascist guerilla fighters active in the Balkans during the Second World War, and its mission is to use street art as a weapon&mdash;however modest&mdash;in a broader struggle against neoliberal policies dominating Albanian universities, against the destruction of Tirana&rsquo;s few remaining green spaces, and in favor of free public transportation. Functioning as a true collective, the group is made up of members of various ages, with various backgrounds: designers, political scientists, artists, architects.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(48, 24, 'al', '<p>&ldquo;Vojo Kushi &euml;sht&euml; ende gjall&euml;&rdquo; &euml;sht&euml; vepra e par&euml; e &Ccedil;ETA-s e prodhuar n&euml; prill 2016. &Ccedil;ETA nis pun&euml;n dhe veprimin me iden&euml; p&euml;r t&euml; risjell&euml; t&euml; modifikuara pikturat e realizmit socialist n&euml; nj&euml; kontekst bashk&euml;kohor shqiptar. E para &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; piktur&euml; e Sali Shijakut e luft&euml;tarit shqiptaro-jugosllav Vojo Kushi, i cili mbahet mend p&euml;r nj&euml; vdekje heroike. Piktura e Shijakut p&euml;rshkruan nj&euml; sken&euml; q&euml; ndodh n&euml; Tiran&euml;n e vitit 1942, ku Kushi dhe partizan&euml; t&euml; tjer&euml; asokohe ishin t&euml; rrethuar nga forcat fashiste italiane. N&euml; nj&euml; moment, Kushi vrapon jasht&euml; dhe hidhet mbi nj&euml; tank armik, duke i hedhur brenda nj&euml; granat&euml; p&euml;rpara se t&euml; vritet nga fashist&euml;t. &Ccedil;ETA e rikthen aktin e Kushit n&euml; nj&euml; kontekst bashk&euml;kohor duke z&euml;vend&euml;suar granat&euml;n n&euml; dor&euml; me nj&euml; koktej molotovi dhe tankun fashist me nj&euml; makin&euml; Jaguar t&euml; zez&euml; (si ato t&euml; blera nga qeveria Rilindja n&euml; vitin 2016) e cila jo rast&euml;sisht mban targ&euml;n e kryeministrit Edi Rama. P&euml;r &Ccedil;ETA-n, n&euml; k&euml;t&euml; kontekst t&euml; ri, Kushi p&euml;rfaq&euml;son popullin q&euml; q&euml;ndron i bashkuar kund&euml;r &ccedil;do lloj sistemi pushteti.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">&Ccedil;ETA &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; kolektiv politik i artit rrugor i formuar nga student&euml;, aktivist&euml; dhe artist&euml;. N&euml; pranver&euml;n e 2016-&euml;s ata filluan t&euml; diskutojn&euml; formimin e nj&euml; grupi p&euml;r t&euml; kund&euml;rshtuar strukturat hegjemoniste t&euml; politik&euml;s dhe ekonomis&euml; kapitaliste dhe neoliberale n&euml; Shqip&euml;rin&euml; bashk&euml;kohore. Nga k&euml;to diskutime, doli nj&euml; grup artist&euml;sh t&euml; rrug&euml;s &ndash; individualisht anonim&euml;, por t&euml; njohur kolektivisht si &Ccedil;ETA. Grupi e ka marr&euml; emrin nga fjala e p&euml;rdorur p&euml;r t&euml; p&euml;rshkruar grupet e luft&euml;tar&euml;ve antifashist&euml; guerile aktiv&euml; n&euml; Ballkan gjat&euml; Luft&euml;s s&euml; Dyt&euml; Bot&euml;rore dhe misioni i tij &euml;sht&euml; t&euml; p&euml;rdor&euml; artin e rrug&euml;s si nj&euml; arm&euml; - sado modest - n&euml; nj&euml; luft&euml; m&euml; t&euml; gjer&euml; kund&euml;r politikave neoliberale q&euml; dominojn&euml; Universitetet shqiptare, kund&euml;r shkat&euml;rrimit t&euml; pak hap&euml;sirave t&euml; gjelbra t&euml; mbetura t&euml; Tiran&euml;s dhe n&euml; favor t&euml; transportit publik falas. Duke funksionuar si nj&euml; kolektiv i v&euml;rtet&euml;, grupi p&euml;rb&euml;het nga an&euml;tar&euml; t&euml; moshave t&euml; ndryshme, me prejardhje t&euml; ndryshme: dezaijnera, politolog&euml;, artist&euml;, arkitekt&euml;.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(49, 25, 'en', '<p>In the&nbsp;intervention/performance &quot;Sht&euml;piz&euml;za&quot;, Kazanxhiu installs 2,500 handmade pottery houses in front of the Prime Minister Building as a protesting gesture in public space calling attention to the Roma housing situation. Such action is an intentional endeavor to build a bridge between the artist&#39;s political activism and aesthetic work. The housing situation is disastrous among the Roma community for many reasons as the artists appoint varying from the lack of financial capacities of Roma families to own a home, to the vulnerability that the dependence on national authorities in the Roma housing creates, as well as to the everyday occurrences of eviction and homelessness of Roma families, due to economic oppression and the complete lack of prosperity. The house - a home, which is the base for a community to put its roots, feel safe, and develop sanity, has shifted from a basic need and human right to an almost privileged context.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Sead Kazanxhiu born in 1987 in Fier, Albania, lives and works in Tirana, Albania. He was trained as a painter at the University of Arts in Tirana from 2006 to 2010, where he obtained his Bachelor Degree. Following his studies, he continued to work primarily in the medium of painting, whereas his more recent practice has expanded into sculpture, installation, video, and public space interventions.&nbsp;With nine personal shows since 2012 in Tirana, Budapest, and Brussels, and numerous group exhibitions in Tirana, Prague, Brno, Gothenburg, Berlin, Drezden, Motovun, Krakow, Bucharest, and New Orleans, Sarawak Malaysia, Kazanxhiu remains one of the most engaged younger protagonists in contemporary Albanian cultural scene. His uncompromising position with regard to unfair treatment of the Roma ethnic group presents but a platform to voice individual dissent about the racially biased dynamics that, unfortunately, continues to shape contemporary European worldviews &ndash; on a daily basis, inside and outside of official political arenas. In this sense, his image-making contributes to the positive efforts of a single artist to restore the dignity of a community forcefully and unjustly cornered at the outskirts of European democracy. Currently, he is a PAKIV board member of the European Roma Institute for Art and Culture and a Deputy Chairman of the State Committee for National Minorities in Albania.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(50, 25, 'al', '<p>P&euml;r nd&euml;rhyrjen/performanc&euml;n &quot;Sht&euml;piz&euml;za&quot; Kazanxhiu instaloi p&euml;rpara godin&euml;s s&euml; Kryeministris&euml; 2500 sht&euml;pi qeramike t&euml; punuara me dor&euml; si nj&euml; gjest protestues n&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml;n publike p&euml;r t&euml; t&euml;rhequr v&euml;mendjen ndaj situat&euml;s s&euml; strehimit t&euml; komunitetit rom. Nj&euml; veprim i till&euml; &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; p&euml;rpjekje e q&euml;llimshme p&euml;r t&euml; nd&euml;rtuar nj&euml; ur&euml; nd&euml;rmjet aktivizmit politik t&euml; artistit dhe pun&euml;s s&euml; tij estetike. P&euml;r komunitetin rom situata e strehimit &euml;sht&euml; katastrofike p&euml;r shum&euml; arsye, t&euml; cilat vet&euml; artisti i n&euml;nvizon, q&euml; variojn&euml; nga mungesa e kapaciteteve financiare t&euml; familjeve rome p&euml;r t&euml; zot&euml;ruar nj&euml; sht&euml;pi, tek c&euml;nueshm&euml;ria q&euml; krijon var&euml;sia nga autoritetet komb&euml;tare, si dhe dukurit&euml; e p&euml;rditshme t&euml; d&euml;bimeve dhe t&euml; mos strehimit t&euml; familjeve rome, p&euml;r shkak t&euml; shtypjes ekonomike dhe munges&euml;s s&euml; plot&euml; t&euml; prosperitetit. Sht&euml;pia - e cila &euml;sht&euml; baza e nj&euml; komuniteti p&euml;r t&euml; v&euml;n&euml; rr&euml;nj&euml;t e tij, p&euml;r t&#39;u ndjer&euml; i sigurt dhe p&euml;r t&euml; zhvilluar mendjen e sh&euml;ndosh&euml; - ka kaluar nga nj&euml; nevoj&euml; baz&euml; dhe e drejt&euml; njer&euml;zore themelore n&euml; nj&euml; kontekst pothuajse vet&euml;m e t&euml; privilegjuarve.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Sead Kazanxhiu i &nbsp;lindur m&euml; 1987 n&euml; Fier, Shqip&euml;ri, jeton dhe punon n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. Ka studiur piktur&euml; n&euml; Universitetin e Arteve n&euml; Tiran&euml; nga viti 2006 deri n&euml; vitin 2010, ku ka marr&euml; Diplom&euml;n Bachelor. Pas studimeve, ai vazhdoi t&euml; punoj&euml; kryesisht n&euml; mediumin e piktur&euml;s, nd&euml;rsa praktika e tij s&euml; fundmi &euml;sht&euml; zgjeruar n&euml; skulptur&euml;, instalacion, video dhe nd&euml;rhyrje n&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml;n publike. Me n&euml;nt&euml; ekspozita personale q&euml; nga viti 2012 n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Budapest dhe Bruksel dhe ekspozita t&euml; shumta kolektive n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Prag&euml;, Brno, G&ouml;teborg, Berlin, Drezden, Motovun, Krakov, Bukuresht, New Orleans, Sarawak Malajzi; Kazanxhiu mbetet nj&euml; nga t&euml; rinjt&euml; m&euml; t&euml; angazhuar protagonist&euml; n&euml; sken&euml;n kulturore bashk&euml;kohore shqiptare. Pozicioni i tij i pakompromis n&euml; lidhje me trajtimin e padrejt&euml; t&euml; grupit etnik rom paraqet vet&euml;m nj&euml; platform&euml; p&euml;r t&euml; shprehur mospajtimin individual p&euml;r dinamik&euml;n e nj&euml;anshme racore q&euml;, p&euml;r fat t&euml; keq, vazhdon t&euml; form&euml;soj&euml; bot&euml;kuptimet bashk&euml;kohore evropiane &ndash; n&euml; baza ditore, brenda dhe jasht&euml; arenave politike zyrtare. N&euml; k&euml;t&euml; kuptim, krijimi i imazhit t&euml; tij kontribuon n&euml; p&euml;rpjekjet pozitive t&euml; nj&euml; artisti t&euml; vet&euml;m p&euml;r t&euml; rikthyer dinjitetin e nj&euml; komuniteti t&euml; vendosur me forc&euml; dhe padrejt&euml;sisht n&euml; periferi t&euml; demokracis&euml; evropiane. Aktualisht ai &euml;sht&euml; an&euml;tar bordi i PAKIV i Institutit Evropian t&euml; Rom&euml;ve p&euml;r Art dhe Kultur&euml; dhe Z&euml;vend&euml;s Kryetar i Komitetit Shtet&euml;ror p&euml;r Pakicat Komb&euml;tare n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(51, 26, 'en', '<p>The performers of the&nbsp;intervention &quot;Music Requisites&quot;, as absurd as it may sound, are 1o parked cars. In their physical immobility and seriality, two elements attract the spectator&#39;s attention: they have the same vague, neon light on and they are reproducing the same music: &ldquo;Richard Wagner&rsquo;s opera &ldquo;Die Feen&rdquo;. This music which comes from and belongs to a cosmos of myths is far and almost detached from the urban reality where it is actually being played.&nbsp;Through this intervention, Agostini creates an invisible bridge and dialogue in between two dimensions: German Romanticism is juxtaposed with the urban present; the reality of the metropolis with the symbolism of the late 19th century. The cars, in their industrial character, become for the artist &ldquo;hybrid actors&rdquo;, able to set up an unusual yet symbolic concert in one of the loudest, busiest areas of Tirana: the Bllok of bars and clubs. The sound performance &quot;Music Requisites&quot; was part of Agostini&rsquo;s solo show &ldquo;with open eyes, with eyes closed&quot; at Bazament Art Space in May 2018.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Silva Agostini born in 1979 in Tirana, Albania is a multimedia artist living and working in Berlin, Germany. She attended the Academy of Arts in Tirana and the Berlin University of the Arts, where she graduated as a master&#39;s student in 2005. In her videos, photographs, and performative interventions, she concentrates on the relations between nature, culture, technology, history, and the human body, beyond subjectivation and objectivation, past and present. Her works have been shown in numerous solo and group exhibitions in Germany and Europe, including: Draussenstadt &ndash; Call for action, Berlin; National Gallery of Arts, Tirana; Bazament Art Space, Tirana; Belvedere 21, Wien; Nassauischer Kunstverein, Wiesbaden; Basis, Frankfurt; Grieder Contemporary, Z&uuml;rich; Macedonian Museum of Contemporary Art, Thessaloniki; the Muzeul Național de arta contemporană, Bucharest; Gallery Isabella Czarnowska, Berlin; Kunstsammlung, Gera, as well as at the Tirana Biennale, Tirana. She received the Onufri Award in 2014 and has attended the TICA Residency in 2016 and the Art House in Shkodra 2018. She is a founding member of the project space &ldquo;Very&rdquo; in Berlin.</p>', NULL, NULL);
