(52, 26, 'al', '<p>Interpretuesit e k&euml;saj nd&euml;rhyrjeje, sado absurde t&euml; ting&euml;lloj&euml;, jan&euml; 10 makina t&euml; parkuara. N&euml; serialitetin dhe pal&euml;vizshm&euml;rin&euml; e tyre fizike, jane dy element&euml;t qe t&euml;rheqin v&euml;mendjen e spektatorit; makinat jan&euml; te ndri&ccedil;uara n&euml; brend&euml;sin&euml; e tyre nga e nj&euml;jta drit&euml; e vak&euml;t neoni dhe po ashtu ato riprodhojn&euml; t&euml; nj&euml;jt&euml;n muzik&euml;: opera e Richard Wagner &quot;Die Feen&quot;. Kjo muzik&euml; q&euml; vjen nga dhe i p&euml;rket nj&euml; kozmosi mitologjik, &euml;sht&euml; thuajse e shk&euml;putur nga realiteti dhe konteksti urban n&euml; t&euml; cilin performanca e vendos. N&euml;p&euml;rmjet k&euml;saj nd&euml;rhyrjeje, Agostini krijon nj&euml; ur&euml; t&euml; padukshme dhe nj&euml; dialog midis dy dimensioneve: Romantizmi gjerman p&euml;rballet me t&euml; tashmen urbane; realiteti i metropolit p&euml;rplaset me simbolik&euml;n e fundit t&euml; shekullit XIX. Makinat, n&euml; karakterin e tyre industrial, kthehen p&euml;r artistin n&euml; &ldquo;aktor&euml; hibrid&euml;&rdquo;. T&euml; aft&euml; p&euml;r t&euml; mbajtur nj&euml; koncert t&euml; pazakont&euml; por simbolik, n&euml; nj&euml; nga zonat m&euml; t&euml; zhurmshme t&euml; Tiran&euml;s: Blloku i lokaleve dhe klubeve. Performanca zanore &ldquo;Music Requisites&rdquo; ishte pjes&euml; e ekspozit&euml;s personale t&euml; artistes &ldquo;with open eyes, with eyes closed&quot; n&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml;n e artit Bazament n&euml; Maj 2018.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Silva Agostini e lindur m&euml; 1979 n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; artiste multimediale q&euml; jeton dhe punon n&euml; Berlin, Gjermani. Ajo ndoqi Akademin&euml; e Arteve n&euml; Tiran&euml; dhe Universitetin e Arteve t&euml; Berlinit, ku u diplomua si studente master n&euml; vitin 2005. N&euml; videot, fotografit&euml; dhe nd&euml;rhyrjet e saj performative ajo p&euml;rqendrohet n&euml; marr&euml;dh&euml;niet midis natyr&euml;s, kultur&euml;s, teknologjis&euml;, historis&euml; dhe trupit t&euml; njeriut, p&euml;rtej subjektivimit dhe objektivizimit, t&euml; shkuar&euml;s dhe t&euml; tashmes. Punimet e saj jan&euml; shfaqur n&euml; ekspozita t&euml; shumta personale dhe kolektive n&euml; Gjermani dhe Evrop&euml;, duke p&euml;rfshir&euml;: Draussenstadt &ndash; Call for action, Berlin; Galeria Kombetare e Arteve, Tirana; Bazament Art Space, Tirana; Belvedere 21, Wien; Nassauischer Kunstverein, Wiesbaden; Basis, Frankfurt; Grieder Contemporary, Z&uuml;rich; Macedonian Museum of Contemporary Art, Thessaloniki; the Muzeul Național de arta contemporană, Bucharest; Gallery Isabella Czarnowska, Berlin; Kunstsammlung, Gera, po ashtu edhe n&euml; Tirana Biennale, Tirana. Ajo fitoi &ccedil;mimin Onufri n&euml; 2014 dhe ka ndjekur rezidencat TICA n&euml; 2016 dhe Art House n&euml; Shkod&euml;r 2018. Ajo &euml;sht&euml; themeluese e projektit &ldquo;Very&rdquo; n&euml; Berlin, Gjermani.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(53, 27, 'en', '<p>Infiltration.<br />\r\nme in Tirana<br />\r\nBloku<br />\r\nOn my back<br />\r\na huge loudspeaker<br />\r\nIn an open-air parking<br />\r\nI recite all the Albanian words I learned,<br />\r\nas a novice,<br />\r\nCoating myself with red and white paint<br />\r\n(liquefied Albanian flag)<br />\r\nMy linguistic betrothal gift<br />\r\nA near-near-me<br />\r\nSinging on a microphone<br />\r\nBroadcasting passionately<br />\r\nLIKE A Fr. SUITE<br />\r\nECONOMY OF MEANS<br />\r\nOCCURRING AT NIGHT<br />\r\nWHEN WE ARE ASLEEP<br />\r\nSTENTOR EVENING<br />\r\nTHE LOUDEST VOICE</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;STENTOR EVENING&rdquo; was part of the &ldquo;Performative Exhibition #1 - Center for Integration&rdquo; at Tirana Art Lab, curated by Adela Demetja and collective Patriotisme on 26 July 2018.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Gabriele Rendina Cattani born in 1990 in Rome, Italy lives and works in Frankfurt am Main, Germany. He graduated in Music Composition from S.Cecilia Conservatory and EHESS/ENSAD in Paris and he is currently studying at St&auml;delschule in Frankfurt. Rendina&#39;s practice draws from religious iconography, tableaux vivants, post-concert culture, and new technologies in between text, performance, installation, and experimental music. Since 2018 he is part of ALMARE, an artistic-curatorial collective focused on contemporary sound practices and performance. He has published articles, poems as well as his regular column for the french semiannual video game magazine IMMERSION. His works have been featured in institutions and museums such as Fondazione Prada, Venice; Castello di Rivoli Museum of Contemporary Art; Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo; MACRO, Rome; OUTPOST Gallery, Norwich; HeK-Haus der elektronischen K&uuml;nste, Basel; Mediterranea 19 Young Artists Biennale, San Marino.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(54, 27, 'al', '<p>Infiltrim.<br />\r\nUn&euml; n&euml; Tiran&euml;<br />\r\nBlloku<br />\r\nN&euml; shpin&euml;n time<br />\r\nnj&euml; altoparlant i madh<br />\r\nN&euml; nj&euml; parking t&euml; hapur<br />\r\nRecitoj t&euml; gjitha fjal&euml;t shqip q&euml; kam m&euml;suar,<br />\r\nsi rishtar,<br />\r\nP&euml;rlyej veten me boj&euml; t&euml; kuqe dhe t&euml; bardh&euml;<br />\r\n(flamuri i l&euml;ngsh&euml;m shqiptar)<br />\r\nDhurata ime gjuh&euml;sore e fejes&euml;s<br />\r\nUn&euml; af&euml;r meje<br />\r\nDuke k&euml;nduar n&euml; mikrofon<br />\r\nTransmetoj me pasion<br />\r\nSI NJ&Euml; Fr. SUITE<br />\r\nEKONOMIA E MJETEVE<br />\r\nNDODH N&Euml; NAT&Euml;<br />\r\nKUR JEMI N&Euml; GJUM&Euml;<br />\r\nMBREMJE E FUQISHME<br />\r\nZ&Euml;RI M&Euml; I LART&Euml;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;STENTOR EVENING&quot; u prezantua si pjes&euml; e &quot;Ekspozit&euml;s Performative #1 - Qendra p&euml;r Integrim&quot; n&euml; Tirana Art Lab, kuruar nga Adela Demetja dhe kolektivi Patriotisme m&euml; 26 Korrik 2018.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Gabriele Rendina Cattani lindur n&euml; 1990 n&euml; Rom&euml;, Itali jeton dhe punon n&euml; Frankfurt am Main, Gjermani. Ai &euml;sht&euml; diplomuar p&euml;r Kompozim muzikor n&euml; Konservatorin S.Cecilia dhe EHESS/ENSAD n&euml; Paris dhe aktualisht &euml;sht&euml; duke studiuar n&euml; St&auml;delschule n&euml; Frankfurt. Praktika e Rendin&euml;s bazohet n&euml; ikonografi fetare, tableau vivants, kultur&euml; post-koncertesh dhe teknologji t&euml; reja mes tekstit, performanc&euml;s, instalimit dhe muzik&euml;s eksperimentale. Q&euml; nga viti 2018 &euml;sht&euml; pjes&euml; e ALMARE, nj&euml; kolektiv artistiko-kuratorial i fokusuar n&euml; praktikat dhe performanc&euml;n bashk&euml;kohore t&euml; tingullit. Ai ka botuar artikuj, poezi si dhe rubrik&euml;n e tij t&euml; rregullt p&euml;r revist&euml;n franceze gjysm&euml;vjetore t&euml; videoloj&euml;rave IMMERSION. Punimet e tij jan&euml; paraqitur n&euml; institucione dhe muze si: Fondazione Prada, Venice; Castello di Rivoli Museum of Contemporary Art; Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo; MACRO, Rome; OUTPOST Gallery, Norwich; HeK-Haus der elektronischen K&uuml;nste, Basel; Tirana Art Lab, Tirana; &nbsp;Mediterranea 19 Young Artists Biennale, San Marino.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(55, 28, 'en', '<p>Since arriving in Tirana this September Hanna Hildebrand has been thinking about grids. With this insight, in her installation LWCE T1, Hildebrand is exploring the grid as a space between &lsquo;the concrete&rsquo;, the imagined, the ideal, and memories. The installation included an Augmented Reality work, part of a series of Augmented Reality works which have been spread around the city of Tirana and can be viewed by using an AR app over an AR marker printed on a printed sticker temporarily placed in various locations.&nbsp;Through the AR app, five AR visions can be activated and seen in their three-dimensionality: five different grids with specific structures and shapes inserted in the context of a city that is undergoing continuous change. The three-dimensional objects attempt to make us reflect on what is happening around us in terms of matter and how we structure the &ldquo;beyond matter&rdquo;: forms of abstraction of thoughts and memory. Hanna would like to thank Erida Bendo for her outstanding technical assistance.<br />\r\nThe project &quot;LWCE T1&quot; was created during her residency at Tirana Art Lab as part of the &quot;Beyond Matter, Artists in Residency Program&quot; and was exhibited for the first time at the Bulevard Art and Media Institute between 4-20 of&nbsp;November 2021.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\nHanna Hildebrand is a multimedia artist with Italian &amp; Swiss citizenship. She completed her studies at the St&auml;delschule in Frankfurt am Main in 2009. Film and photography are her main means of expression. The genesis of her work often has a documentary foundation, with emotionally driven narratives drawn from her observations of contemporary life. At the moment she is concluding the ongoing project &ldquo;Omega Transit&rdquo;. This multidisciplinary work has a science-fiction plot touching on topics related to contemporary society while reflecting its utopias and dystopias. It is an expressionist oniric story that follows a group of oppressed beings who flee their own planet, to start a better life on a new one. One central element of the work is the use of the existing architecture of Chiasso, Switzerland, the border town with Italy. The trilogy of videos is produced in collaboration with la rada, Locarno, with a cast of young non-professional actors.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(56, 28, 'al', '<p>Q&euml; prej mb&euml;rritjes n&euml; Tiran&euml; k&euml;t&euml; shtator, Hanna Hildebrand ka menduar p&euml;r rrjet&euml;n. Me k&euml;t&euml; mendim, n&euml; instalacionin e saj &quot;LWCE T1&quot;, Hildebrand eksploron rrjet&euml;n si nj&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml; ​​midis &#39;konkretes&#39;, imagjinat&euml;s, ideales dhe kujtimeve. Instalimi p&euml;rfshin nj&euml; vep&euml;r Augmented Reality, pjes&euml; e nj&euml; serie punimesh Augmented Reality, t&euml; cilat jan&euml; shp&euml;rndar&euml; n&euml; t&euml; gjith&euml; qytetin e Tiran&euml;s dhe mund t&euml; p&euml;rjetohen duke p&euml;rdorur nj&euml; aplikacion AR mbi nj&euml; sh&euml;nues AR t&euml; printuar n&euml; nj&euml; ngjit&euml;s t&euml; printuar t&euml; vendosur p&euml;rkoh&euml;sisht n&euml; vende t&euml; ndryshme. N&euml;p&euml;rmjet aplikacionit AR, pes&euml; vizione AR mund t&euml; aktivizohen dhe shihen n&euml; tre dimensionalitetin e tyre: pes&euml; rrjeta t&euml; ndryshme me struktura dhe forma specifike t&euml; futura n&euml; kontekstin e nj&euml; qyteti q&euml; po jeton n&euml; nj&euml; ndryshim t&euml; vazhduesh&euml;m. Objektet tridimensionale p&euml;rpiqen t&euml; na b&euml;jn&euml; t&euml; reflektojm&euml; mbi at&euml; q&euml; po ndodh rreth nesh n&euml; aspektin e materies dhe se si ne e strukturojm&euml; &quot;p&euml;rtej materies&quot;: forma te abstraksionit t&euml; mendimeve dhe kujtes&euml;s. Hanna d&euml;shiron t&euml; fal&euml;nderoj&euml; Erida Bendo p&euml;r ndihm&euml;n e saj t&euml; jasht&euml;zakonshme teknike. Projekti &quot;LWCE T1&quot; u krijua gjat&euml; q&euml;ndrimit t&euml; saj n&euml; Tirana Art Lab si pjes&euml; e programit &quot;Beyond Matter, Artists n&euml;&nbsp;Rezidenc&euml;&quot; dhe u ekspozua p&euml;r her&euml; t&euml; par&euml; n&euml; Institutin e Artit dhe Medias Bulevard nga data 4 deri n&euml; 20 N&euml;ntor 2021.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Hanna Hildebrand, &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; artiste multimediale me n&euml;nshtet&euml;si italiane dhe zvicerane. Ajo p&euml;rfundoi studimet n&euml; St&auml;delschule n&euml; Frankfurt am Main n&euml; vitin 2009. Filmi dhe fotografia jan&euml; mjetet e saj kryesore shpreh&euml;se. Zanafilla e pun&euml;s s&euml; saj shpesh ka nj&euml; baz&euml; dokumentuese, me rr&euml;fime t&euml; nxitura emocionalisht t&euml; nxjerra nga v&euml;zhgimet e saj mbi jet&euml;n bashk&euml;kohore. P&euml;r momentin ajo &euml;sht&euml; n&euml; p&euml;rfundim t&euml; projektit &ldquo;Omega Transit&rdquo;. Kjo vep&euml;r multidisiplinare ka nj&euml; plot fantastiko-shkencor q&euml; prek tema q&euml; lidhen me shoq&euml;rin&euml; bashk&euml;kohore duke pasqyruar utopit&euml; dhe distopit&euml; e saj. &Euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; histori onirike ekspresioniste q&euml; ndjek nj&euml; grup qeniesh t&euml; shtypura q&euml; ikin nga planeti i tyre, p&euml;r t&euml; filluar nj&euml; jet&euml; m&euml; t&euml; mir&euml; n&euml; nj&euml; planet t&euml; ri. Nj&euml; element q&euml;ndror i pun&euml;s &euml;sht&euml; p&euml;rdorimi i arkitektur&euml;s ekzistuese t&euml; Chiasso, Zvic&euml;r, qyteti kufitar me Italin&euml;. Trilogjia e videove &euml;sht&euml; prodhuar n&euml; bashk&euml;punim me la rada, Locarno, me nj&euml; kast aktor&euml;sh t&euml; rinj jo profesionist&euml;.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(57, 29, 'en', '<p>This intervention implies two covered statues of Lenin and Stalin which for political reasons were taken off the public space and were conserved at the backyard of the National Gallery of Arts. The covering came as a consequence because of several attacks on them, creating a &ldquo;Christo effect&rdquo; as Konstandini says. &nbsp;The artist&rsquo;s intervention here is fast and bold; she wraps a pink ribbon over the packed statues and turns them into mysterious, giant surprises. These covered statues with no visual identity become a white canvas where one can project all leaders, rising and falling as preferred. With such action, the artist&rsquo;s aim is to push thoughts towards the notion of leadership and the blurred line between power and oppression, past and future, experience and expectations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\nLedia&nbsp;Kostandini born 1983 in Pogradec, Albania lives and works in Tirana, Albania.&nbsp;A graduate of the University of Arts, Tirana, her practice spans over diverse media, including photography, painting, installation, public interventions, and illustration. Her work refers to social transformations, the inherited or lost culture.&nbsp;She is interested in contemporary habits by associating them to archaic, obsolete&nbsp;objects, places or venues.&nbsp;&ldquo;Identity on transition&rdquo; is her focal subject. She uses parallelism, comparison, and juxtapositions in order to reveal paradoxical situations.&nbsp;Her works try to provoke ambiguous emotions, mingling imagination, curiosity, and humor.&nbsp;Her work has been exhibited internationally and locally. Her solo shows include:&nbsp;&Ccedil;entro Estetike, Miza Gallery, Tirana; &nbsp;Blockwork, Tulla Culture Center, Tirana; Let Us Meet in Between, Bazament Art Space, Tirana; I Look at Them They Look Back at Me, Private Print Studio, Skopje. She has participated in numerous group exhibitions in Albania, Germany, France, Austria, etc.&nbsp;She was awarded the Ardhje Award in 2012. She has attended AiR programs in New York and Croatia.&nbsp;She is a freelance&nbsp;illustrator since 2008. Actually, she works as an Art Professor at Polis University.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(58, 29, 'al', '<p>Kjo nd&euml;rhyrje p&euml;rfshin dy statuja t&euml; mbuluara t&euml; Leninit dhe Stalinit t&euml; cilat p&euml;r arsye politike u hoq&euml;n nga hap&euml;sira publike dhe u ruajt&euml;n n&euml; oborrin pas Galeris&euml; Komb&euml;tare t&euml; Arteve. Mbulimi i tyre erdhi si pasoj&euml; e disa sulmeve, duke krijuar k&euml;shtu mbi to nj&euml; &ldquo;efekt Christo&rdquo; si&ccedil; thot&euml; dhe vet&euml; Konstandini. N&euml; k&euml;t&euml; rast nd&euml;rhyrja e artistes &euml;sht&euml; e shpejt&euml; dhe e guximshme; ajo lidh nga nj&euml; fjongo roz&euml; mbi statujat e mbuluara dhe i kthen ato n&euml; surpriza misterioze, gjigante. K&euml;to statuja t&euml; mbuluara, pa identitet vizual, kthehen n&euml; nj&euml; kanavac&euml; te bardh&euml; ku mund t&euml; projektohen t&euml; gjith&euml; lider&euml;t e bot&euml;s, t&euml; cil&euml;t nrgihen e bien sipas d&euml;shir&euml;s s&euml; spektatorit. Me nj&euml; veprim t&euml; till&euml;, synimi i artistes &euml;sht&euml; t&euml; shtyj&euml; t&euml; menduarit drejt kuptimeve t&euml; udh&euml;heqjes dhe kufizimit t&euml; paqart&euml; midis pushtetit dhe shtypjes, s&euml; shkuar&euml;s dhe s&euml; ardhmes, p&euml;rvoj&euml;s dhe pritjeve.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Ledia Kostandini e lindur m&euml; 1983 n&euml; Pogradec, Shqip&euml;ri jeton dhe punon n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. E diplomuar n&euml; Universitetin e Arteve, Tiran&euml;, praktika e saj shtrihet n&euml; media t&euml; ndryshme, duke p&euml;rfshir&euml; fotografin&euml;, piktur&euml;n, instalacionin, nd&euml;rhyrjet publike dhe ilustrimin. Puna e saj i referohet transformimeve shoq&euml;rore, kultur&euml;s s&euml; trash&euml;guar apo t&euml; humbur. Ajo &euml;sht&euml; e interesuar p&euml;r zakonet bashk&euml;kohore duke i lidhur ato me objekte, hap&euml;sira ose vende arkaike, t&euml; vjet&euml;ruara. &ldquo;Identiteti n&euml; tranzicion&rdquo; &euml;sht&euml; tema kryesore e k&euml;rkimit te saj. Ajo p&euml;rdor paralelizmin, krahasimin dhe p&euml;rballjet p&euml;r t&euml; zbuluar situata paradoksale. Punimet e saj p&euml;rpiqen t&euml; provokojn&euml; emocione t&euml; paqarta, imagjinat&euml; t&euml; p&euml;rzier, kuriozitet dhe humor. Puna e saj &euml;sht&euml; ekspozuar n&euml; nivel nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar dhe komb&euml;tar. Disa ekspozita personale p&euml;rfshijn&euml;: &Ccedil;entro Estetike, Miza Gallery, Tirana; &nbsp;Blockwork, Tulla Culture Center, Tirana; Let Us Meet in Between, Bazament Art Space, Tirana; I Look at Them They Look Back at Me, Private Print Studio, Skopje. Ajo ka marr&euml; pjes&euml; n&euml; ekspozita t&euml; shumta kolektive n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri, Gjermani, Franc&euml;, Austri etj. Ajo &euml;sht&euml; vler&euml;suar me &Ccedil;mimin Ardhje n&euml; vitin 2012. Kostandini ka ndjekur programet e AirR n&euml; Nju Jork dhe Kroaci. Ajo &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; ilustratore e pavarur q&euml; nga viti 2008. Aktualisht punon si Profesore e Artit n&euml; Universitetin Polis, Tiran&euml;.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(59, 30, 'en', '<p>In &quot;Purchasing Silence&quot; we see a pink shopping cart, an icon representing a symbol of commercialization, industrialization, and prosperity. The artist takes this icon out of its virtual context, which has become part of our daily routine with online shopping and creates a tangible, material icon that can be touched and moved. She moves the self-made icon into former industrial sites in and out of Tirana, sites that used to be Albania&rsquo;s national symbol of pride and prosperity and nowadays are just mere ruins. In Tirana Kostandini chooses the Textile Factory in Kombinat: the pink cart photographed in the gloomy abandoned spaces creates an almost dystopian impression of collapsing times. For the artist, this whole process is about exploration and confrontation in-between times; at once, it aims at a global and local understanding of notions like consumerism, transition, collapse, and progress.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Ledia&nbsp;Kostandini born 1983 in Pogradec, Albania lives and works in Tirana, Albania.&nbsp;&nbsp;A graduate of the University of Arts, Tirana, her practice spans over diverse media, including photography, painting, installation, public interventions, and illustration. Her work refers to social transformations, the inherited or lost culture.&nbsp;She is interested in contemporary habits by associating them with archaic, obsolete&nbsp;objects, places, or venues.&nbsp;&ldquo;Identity on transition&rdquo; is her focal subject. She uses parallelism, comparison, and juxtapositions in order to reveal paradoxical situations.&nbsp;Her works try to provoke ambiguous emotions, mingling imagination, curiosity, and humor.&nbsp;Her work has been exhibited internationally and locally. Her solo shows include:&nbsp;&Ccedil;entro Estetike, Miza Gallery, Tirana; &nbsp;Blockwork, Tulla Culture Center, Tirana; Let Us Meet in Between, Bazament Art Space, Tirana; I Look at Them They Look Back at Me, Private Print Studio, Skopje. She has participated in numerous group exhibitions in Albania, Germany, France, Austria, etc.&nbsp;She was awarded the Ardhje Award in 2012. She has attended AiR programs in New York and Croatia.&nbsp;She is a freelance&nbsp;illustrator since 2008. Actually, she works as an Art Professor at Polis University.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(60, 30, 'al', '<p>N&euml; &quot;Blerja e Heshtjes&quot; shikojm&euml; nj&euml; karroc&euml; roz&euml;, nj&euml; ikon&euml; q&euml; p&euml;rfaq&euml;son nj&euml; simbol t&euml; komercializimit, industrializimit dhe prosperitetit. Artistja e nxjerr k&euml;t&euml; ikon&euml; nga konteksti i saj virtual, i cili &euml;sht&euml; b&euml;r&euml; pjes&euml; e rutin&euml;s son&euml; t&euml; p&euml;rditshme me blerjet online, dhe krijon nj&euml; ikon&euml; t&euml; gjall&euml;, materiale q&euml; mund t&euml; preket dhe l&euml;vizet. Ajo e zhvendos ikon&euml;n e b&euml;r&euml; vet&euml;, n&euml; lokacione ish-industriale brenda dhe jasht&euml; Tiran&euml;s, vende t&euml; cilat dikur ishin simboli komb&euml;tar i krenaris&euml; dhe prosperitetit t&euml; Shqip&euml;ris&euml; e nd&euml;rsa sot jan&euml; thjesht g&euml;rmadha. N&euml; Tiran&euml;, Kostandini zgjedh Kombinatin e Tekstileve: karroca roz&euml; e fotografuar n&euml; hap&euml;sirat e zymta t&euml; braktisura krijon nj&euml; p&euml;rshtypje pothuajse distopike n&euml; koh&euml; shkat&euml;rrimi. P&euml;r artisten, i gjith&euml; ky proces ka t&euml; b&euml;j&euml; me eksplorimin dhe p&euml;rballjen mes koh&euml;rave; ai synon kuptimin global dhe lokal t&euml; koncepteve si konsumizmi, tranzicioni, shembja dhe progresi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Ledia Kostandini e &nbsp;lindur m&euml; 1983 n&euml; Pogradec, Shqip&euml;ri jeton dhe punon n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. E diplomuar n&euml; Universitetin e Arteve, Tiran&euml;, praktika e saj shtrihet n&euml; media t&euml; ndryshme, duke p&euml;rfshir&euml; fotografin&euml;, piktur&euml;n, instalacionin, nd&euml;rhyrjet publike dhe ilustrimin. Puna e saj i referohet transformimeve shoq&euml;rore, kultur&euml;s s&euml; trash&euml;guar apo t&euml; humbur. Ajo &euml;sht&euml; e interesuar p&euml;r zakonet bashk&euml;kohore duke i lidhur ato me objekte, hapesira ose vende arkaike, t&euml; vjetruara. &ldquo;Identiteti n&euml; tranzicion&rdquo; &euml;sht&euml; tema kryesore e kerkimit te saj. Ajo p&euml;rdor paralelizmin, krahasimin dhe p&euml;rballjet p&euml;r t&euml; zbuluar situata paradoksale. Punimet e saj p&euml;rpiqen t&euml; provokojn&euml; emocione t&euml; paqarta, imagjinat&euml; t&euml; p&euml;rzier, kuriozitet dhe humor. Puna e saj &euml;sht&euml; ekspozuar n&euml; nivel nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar dhe vendor. Disa ekspozita personale p&euml;rfshijn&euml;: &Ccedil;entro Estetike, Miza Gallery, Tirana; &nbsp;Blockwork, Tulla Culture Center, Tirana; Let Us Meet in Between, Bazament Art Space, Tirana; I Look at Them They Look Back at Me, Private Print Studio, Skopje. Ajo ka marr&euml; pjes&euml; n&euml; ekspozita t&euml; shumta kolektive n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri, Gjermani, Franc&euml;, Austri etj. Ajo &euml;sht&euml; vler&euml;suar me &Ccedil;mimin Ardhje n&euml; vitin 2012. Kostandini ka ndjekur programet e AirR n&euml; Nju Jork dhe Kroaci. Ajo &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; ilustratore e pavarur q&euml; nga viti 2008. Aktualisht punon si Profesore e Artit n&euml; Universitetin Polis, Tirane.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(61, 31, 'en', '<p>Zogu i Zi roundabout is one of the main city entrances of the capital Tirana. Back in 2005, when Bujari realized this intervention, there were works going on for building a crossover. Construction works started but got blocked because of a political conflictual situation, creating chaos in the local urban transport situation as it is an important and busy area of passage. As the promotional banner of the crossover project was not useful anymore because the deadline dates written on it were not being respected, the artist saw it as a possibility and space to make an intervention. Bujari&rsquo;s action consisted in covering the existing banner with a new one on which he printed a real image from the Zogu i Zi area and enhanced how it really looked: trapped in between chaos and uncertainty.- With such intervention, the artist revealed to the city and the citizens a hidden sense of truth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\nNikolin Bujari born 1984 in Shkodra, Albania lives and works in Tirana, Albania. He graduated from Tirana Art Academy in 2006 with Professor Edi Hila and was a guest student at the College of Design in Karlsruhe Germany in the Media class with Professor Mischa Kuball.<br />\r\nAmong others his works have been shown in exhibitions in institutions like: Badischer Kunstverein, Karlsruhe Germany; Nassauischer Kunstverein, Wiesbaden, Germany; Haus am L&uuml;tzowplatz, Berlin Germany; National Gallery of Art, Tirana Albania; 3-rd Tirana Biennale Albania, Tirana Art Lab - Center for Contemporary Art, etc.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(62, 31, 'al', '<p>Rrethrrotullimi i Zogut t&euml; Zi &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; nga hyrjet kryesore t&euml; kryeqytetit Tiran&euml;. N&euml; vitin 2005, kur Bujari realizoi k&euml;t&euml; nd&euml;rhyrje, po punohej p&euml;r nd&euml;rtimin e nj&euml; mbikalimi. Punimet e nd&euml;rtimit nis&euml;n por u bllokuan p&euml;r shkak t&euml; nj&euml; situate konfliktuale politike, duke krijuar rr&euml;muj n&euml; situat&euml;n e transportit urban lokal. Duke q&euml;n&euml; se posteri promovues i projektit t&euml; kryq&euml;zimit nuk ishte m&euml; i dobish&euml;m p&euml;r shkak se nuk respektoheshin afatet e shkruara mbi t&euml;, artisti e pa at&euml; si nj&euml; mund&euml;si dhe hap&euml;sir&euml; ​​p&euml;r t&euml; kryer nj&euml; nd&euml;rhyrje. Veprimi i Bujarit konsistoi n&euml; mbulimin e posterit ekzistues me nj&euml; poster t&euml; ri, mbi t&euml; cilin ai shtypi nj&euml; imazh t&euml; v&euml;rtet&euml; dhe aktual nga zona e Zogut t&euml; Zi dhe theksoi pamjen e tij t&euml; v&euml;rtet&euml;: d bllokuar mes rr&euml;muj&euml;s dhe pasiguris&euml;. Me nj&euml; nd&euml;rhyrje t&euml; till&euml; artisti i zbuloi qytetit dhe qytetar&euml;ve nj&euml; an&euml; t&euml; fsheht&euml; t&euml; s&euml; v&euml;rtet&euml;s.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Nikolin Bujari i lindur m&euml; 1984 n&euml; Shkod&euml;r, Shqip&euml;ri jeton dhe punon n&euml; Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri. Ai u diplomua n&euml; Akademin&euml; e Arteve n&euml; Tiran&euml; n&euml; vitin 2006 me profesor Edi Hila dhe ishte student i ftuar n&euml; Kolegjin e Dizajnit n&euml; Karlsruhe, Gjermani n&euml; klas&euml;n Media Art &nbsp;me profesor Mischa Kuball. Nd&euml;r t&euml; tjerash, veprat e tij jan&euml; shfaqur n&euml; ekspozita e institucione si: Badischer Kunstverein, Karlsruhe Gjermani; Nassauischer Kunstverein, Wiesbaden, Gjermani; Haus am L&uuml;tzowplatz, Berlin Gjermani; Galeria Komb&euml;tare e Arteve, Tiran&euml;, Shqip&euml;ri; Bienalja e 3-t&euml; e Tiran&euml;s n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri, Tirana Art Lab - Qendra p&euml;r Artin Bashk&euml;kohor, etj.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(63, 32, 'en', '<p>In this work, &Ccedil;ETA refers to one of the most iconic Albanian art history images: &ldquo;Motra Tone&rdquo; (Sister Tone) by Kol Idromeno. Painted in 1883, it is considered the first realist portrait in Albanian art initiating a new era. &Ccedil;ETA takes such a symbolic image and uses it as a parallelism for what is happening in the Albanian economy in the private sector where a new era is initiating as well: referring precisely to the business of call centers whose worker&rsquo;s target is that of the student-worker. More than 25,000 students were hired by around 300 Italian companies at the time of the intervention, and many of them regularly complained of bad working conditions. Influenced by Italian Television, the generation growing up after the 90&rsquo;s got to learn and speak Italian, by making Albanian youngsters today a great target for Italian call center companies selling different services, sometimes also erotic.&nbsp;That&rsquo;s why sister Tone is modified by &Ccedil;ETA with a breast hanging out from her traditional dress and big earphones with a microphone, making her iconic shy presence even more terrified, almost violated. In the meantime, as the Italian Government was discussing whether to shut down such businesses, the anxiety of the Albanian students rose: the fear of losing a job is always a struggle and it makes the vicious circle hard to be broken.<br />\r\n&ldquo;Buongiorno, vi parla l&rsquo;Albania&rdquo; was commissioned by Tirana Art Lab and exhibited at&nbsp;&ldquo;Triple Feature #5&rdquo;, as part of the collaboration project &nbsp;&ldquo;Heroes we love&#39;&#39;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\n&Ccedil;ETA&nbsp;is a political street art collective formed by students, activists, and artists. In spring 2016 they began to discuss the formation of a group to oppose the hegemonic structures of capitalist and neoliberal politics and economics in contemporary Albania. From these discussions, a group of street artists&mdash;individually anonymous but known collectively as &Ccedil;ETA&mdash;emerged. The group takes its name from the word used to describe the groups of antifascist guerilla fighters active in the Balkans during the Second World War, and its mission is to use street art as a weapon&mdash;however modest&mdash;in a broader struggle against neoliberal policies dominating Albanian universities, against the destruction of Tirana&rsquo;s few remaining green spaces, and in favor of free public transportation. Functioning as a true collective, the group is made up of members of various ages, with various backgrounds: designers, political scientists, artists, architects.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(64, 32, 'al', '<p>N&euml; k&euml;t&euml; pun&euml; &Ccedil;ETA i referohet nj&euml; prej imazheve m&euml; ikonike t&euml; historis&euml; s&euml; artit shqiptar: &ldquo;Motra Tone&rdquo; e Kol Idromenos. E pikturuar n&euml; vitin 1883, konsiderohet si portreti i par&euml; realist n&euml; artin shqiptar, me t&euml; cilin nis nj&euml; epok&euml; e re. &Ccedil;ETA e merr k&euml;t&euml; imazh simbolik dhe e p&euml;rdor si paraleliz&euml;m p&euml;r at&euml; q&euml; po ndodh n&euml; ekonomin&euml; shqiptare n&euml; sektorin privat ku gjitashtu po nis nj&euml; epok&euml; e re: ata i referohen pik&euml;risht biznesit t&euml; qendrave telefonike, ku pjesa m&euml; e madhe e punonj&euml;sve jan&euml; studen&euml;-pun&euml;tor. M&euml; shum&euml; se 25,000 student&euml; u pun&euml;suan nga rreth 300 kompani italiane teksa kjo pun&euml; po realizohej, dhe shum&euml; prej tyre jan&euml; ankuar rregullisht p&euml;r kushtet e k&euml;qija t&euml; pun&euml;s. I ndikuar nga televizioni italian, brezi i rritur pas viteve 90-t&euml; n&euml; kushte modeste ka arritur t&euml; m&euml;soj&euml;/flas&euml; italisht, duke i b&euml;r&euml; sot t&euml; rinjt&euml; shqiptar&euml; nj&euml; shenjest&euml;r p&euml;r kompanit&euml; italiane t&euml; call center-it t&euml; cilat ofrojn&euml; sh&euml;rbime t&euml; ndryshme shitjeje, ndonj&euml;her&euml; edhe erotike.<br />\r\nP&euml;r k&euml;t&euml; arsye &ldquo;Motra Tone&rdquo; modifikohet nga &Ccedil;ETA me nj&euml; gjoks jasht&euml; fustanit t&euml; saj tradicional dhe gjithashtu ajo mban kufjet e m&euml;dha me mikrofon, tipike t&euml; nj&euml; punetori n&euml; call center. K&euml;t&euml; elemente t&euml; shtuara e b&euml;jn&euml; imazhin e saj q&euml; njihet si i t&euml;rhequr, t&euml; duket edhe m&euml; t&euml; tmerruar, thuajse t&euml; dhunuar. Nd&euml;rkoh&euml;, teksa qeveria italiane po diskuton mbylljen e mundshme t&euml; bizneseve t&euml; tilla, ankthi i student&euml;ve shqiptar&euml; shtohet: frika e humbjes s&euml; vendit t&euml; pun&euml;s &euml;sht&euml; gjithmon&euml; nj&euml; luft&euml; dhe e b&euml;n t&euml; v&euml;shtir&euml; thyerjen e rrethit vicioz ku shpesh punetori gjendet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">&ldquo;Mirm&euml;ngjes, ju flet Shqip&euml;ria&rdquo; &euml;sht&euml; komisionuar nga Tirana Art Lab si pjes&euml; e ekspozit&euml;s &ldquo;Triple Feature #5&rdquo;, pjes&euml; e projektit t&euml; bashk&euml;punimit &ldquo;Heroes we love&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&Ccedil;ETA &euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; kolektiv politik i artit rrugor i formuar nga student&euml;, aktivist&euml; dhe artist&euml;. N&euml; pranver&euml;n e 2016-&euml;s ata filluan t&euml; diskutojn&euml; formimin e nj&euml; grupi p&euml;r t&euml; kund&euml;rshtuar strukturat hegjemoniste t&euml; politik&euml;s dhe ekonomis&euml; kapitaliste dhe neoliberale n&euml; Shqip&euml;rin&euml; bashk&euml;kohore. Nga k&euml;to diskutime, doli nj&euml; grup artist&euml;sh t&euml; rrug&euml;s &ndash; individualisht anonim&euml;, por t&euml; njohur kolektivisht si &Ccedil;ETA. Grupi e ka marr&euml; emrin nga fjala e p&euml;rdorur p&euml;r t&euml; p&euml;rshkruar grupet e luft&euml;tar&euml;ve antifashist&euml; guerile aktiv&euml; n&euml; Ballkan gjat&euml; Luft&euml;s s&euml; Dyt&euml; Bot&euml;rore dhe misioni i tij &euml;sht&euml; t&euml; p&euml;rdor&euml; artin e rrug&euml;s si nj&euml; arm&euml; - sado modest - n&euml; nj&euml; luft&euml; m&euml; t&euml; gjer&euml; kund&euml;r politikave neoliberale q&euml; dominojn&euml; Universitetet shqiptare, kund&euml;r shkat&euml;rrimit t&euml; pak hap&euml;sirave t&euml; gjelbra t&euml; mbetura t&euml; Tiran&euml;s dhe n&euml; favor t&euml; transportit publik falas. Duke funksionuar si nj&euml; kolektiv i v&euml;rtet&euml;, grupi p&euml;rb&euml;het nga an&euml;tar&euml; t&euml; moshave t&euml; ndryshme, me prejardhje t&euml; ndryshme: dezaijnera, politolog&euml;, artist&euml;, arkitekt&euml;.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(65, 33, 'en', '<p>With the&nbsp;work &quot;A Lecture on Punishment&quot;&nbsp;&Ccedil;ETA reflects and protests about the usurpation of public space by the Municipality of Tirana; in this actual case, the spaces are the city&rsquo;s walls. The walls, which become accessible spaces for the citizens to manifest their thoughts, anger, or just purely presence, are treated and filled by the Municipality with commercial advertising. &ldquo;A Lecture on punishment&rdquo; happens on one of those treated walls ready to be filled; for the Albanian citizen the image is direct: it is inspired by the famous 1976 movie &ldquo;Lulkuqe mbi mure&rdquo; (Poppies on walls) about Albania under the Italian fascist regime. In the movie, two Albanian boys living in the same orphanage are forced to slap each other&rsquo;s faces under the command of their Professor, The professor stands for a symbol of authority supporting fascism against Albania and by putting the boys against each other he is also putting the future of the country against the country itself. &Ccedil;ETA makes another move by replacing the face of the Professor with that of George Soros as the personification of the international oligarch figure which influences and creates other oligarchic models in smaller and poorer realities, such as they refer to the actual Mayor of Tirana: Erion Veliaj.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">&Ccedil;ETA&nbsp;is a political street art collective formed by students, activists, and artists. In spring 2016 they began to discuss the formation of a group to oppose the hegemonic structures of capitalist and neoliberal politics and economics in contemporary Albania. From these discussions, a group of street artists&mdash;individually anonymous but known collectively as &Ccedil;ETA&mdash;emerged. The group takes its name from the word used to describe the groups of antifascist guerilla fighters active in the Balkans during the Second World War, and its mission is to use street art as a weapon&mdash;however modest&mdash;in a broader struggle against neoliberal policies dominating Albanian universities, against the destruction of Tirana&rsquo;s few remaining green spaces, and in favor of free public transportation. Functioning as a true collective, the group is made up of members of various ages, with various backgrounds: designers, political scientists, artists, architects.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL),
(66, 33, 'al', '<p>Me pun&euml;n&nbsp;&quot;Leksion mbi nd&euml;shkimin&quot; &Ccedil;ETA reflekton dhe proteston p&euml;r uzurpimin e hap&euml;sir&euml;s publike nga Bashkia e Tiran&euml;s; n&euml; k&euml;t&euml; rast hap&euml;sirat jan&euml; muret e qytetit. Muret, t&euml; cilat b&euml;hen hap&euml;sir&euml; ​​e aksesueshme p&euml;r qytetar&euml;t p&euml;r t&euml; shfaqur mendimet, zem&euml;rimin apo thjesht pranine e tyre, trajtohen dhe mbushen nga Bashkia me reklama komerciale. &quot;Leksion mbi nd&euml;shkimin&quot; ndodh pikerisht n&euml; nj&euml; nga ato muret gati p&euml;r t&#39;u mbushur serisht me reklama; p&euml;r qytetarin shqiptar imazhi &euml;sht&euml; i drejtp&euml;rdrejt&euml;: ai &euml;sht&euml; i frym&euml;zuar nga filmi i famsh&euml;m i vitit 1976 &ldquo;Lulkuqe mbi mure&rdquo; q&euml; trajton Shqip&euml;rin&euml; n&euml;n regjimin fashist italian. N&euml; k&euml;t&euml; film, dy djem shqiptar&euml; q&euml; jetojn&euml; n&euml; t&euml; nj&euml;jt&euml;n jetimore detyrohen t&euml; godasin me shuplak&euml; nj&euml;ri-tjetrin n&euml;n komand&euml;n e profesorit t&euml; tyre. Profesori, edhe pse shqiptar, p&euml;rfaq&euml;son nj&euml; simbol t&euml; autoritetit q&euml; mb&euml;shtet fashizmin kund&euml;r Shqip&euml;ris&euml; dhe duke i v&euml;n&euml; djemt&euml; kund&euml;r nj&euml;ri-tjetrit ai vendos te ardhmen e vendit kund&euml;r vet&euml; vendit. &Ccedil;ETA shton nj&euml; detaj tjet&euml;r duke z&euml;vend&euml;suar fytyr&euml;n e profesorit me at&euml; t&euml; George Soros si personifikimi i figur&euml;s s&euml; oligarkut nd&euml;rkomb&euml;tar i cili ndikon dhe krijon modele t&euml; tjera oligarkike n&euml; realitete m&euml; t&euml; vogla e m&euml; t&euml; varfra, ashtu si ata i referohen kryetarit aktual t&euml; Bashkis&euml; s&euml; Tiran&euml;s: Erion Veliaj. (&Ccedil;ETA)</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">&Ccedil;ETA&nbsp;&euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; kolektiv politik i artit rrugor i formuar nga student&euml;, aktivist&euml; dhe artist&euml;. N&euml; pranver&euml;n e 2016-&euml;s ata filluan t&euml; diskutojn&euml; formimin e nj&euml; grupi p&euml;r t&euml; kund&euml;rshtuar strukturat hegjemoniste t&euml; politik&euml;s dhe ekonomis&euml; kapitaliste dhe neoliberale n&euml; Shqip&euml;rin&euml; bashk&euml;kohore. Nga k&euml;to diskutime, doli nj&euml; grup artist&euml;sh t&euml; rrug&euml;s &ndash; individualisht anonim&euml;, por t&euml; njohur kolektivisht si &Ccedil;ETA. Grupi e ka marr&euml; emrin nga fjala e p&euml;rdorur p&euml;r t&euml; p&euml;rshkruar grupet e luft&euml;tar&euml;ve antifashist&euml; guerile aktiv&euml; n&euml; Ballkan gjat&euml; Luft&euml;s s&euml; Dyt&euml; Bot&euml;rore dhe misioni i tij &euml;sht&euml; t&euml; p&euml;rdor&euml; artin e rrug&euml;s si nj&euml; arm&euml; - sado modest - n&euml; nj&euml; luft&euml; m&euml; t&euml; gjer&euml; kund&euml;r politikave neoliberale q&euml; dominojn&euml; Universitetet shqiptare, kund&euml;r shkat&euml;rrimit t&euml; pak hap&euml;sirave t&euml; gjelbra t&euml; mbetura t&euml; Tiran&euml;s dhe n&euml; favor t&euml; transportit publik falas. Duke funksionuar si nj&euml; kolektiv i v&euml;rtet&euml;, grupi p&euml;rb&euml;het nga an&euml;tar&euml; t&euml; moshave t&euml; ndryshme, me prejardhje t&euml; ndryshme: dezaijnera, politolog&euml;, artist&euml;, arkitekt&euml;.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(67, 34, 'en', '<p>The&nbsp;work &quot;The fall and the rebirth&quot; is&nbsp;born from the necessity to reflect on the worker&rsquo;s condition in Albania, which in the last decade has deteriorated even into death. Many deaths in the working place have been reported especially from construction workers, miners, or oil drillers. Their death cases remain unresolved and the reasons behind this could be many, but at the end of the day the only security those workers have in their working environment is fear and death.&nbsp;&Ccedil;ETA uses Tintoretto&rsquo;s &ldquo;The Deposition of Christ&rdquo; as a symbolic image for this situation, by replacing the figure of Christ with that of a construction worker.&nbsp;The idea behind such replacement is that of liberating the worker from the fear and the owner, as the only way toward dignified work and finally a &ldquo;rebirth&rdquo; not only as a worker, but also as a citizen, and &nbsp;a human being able to enjoy &nbsp;all his human rights.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\n&Ccedil;ETA&nbsp;is a political street art collective formed by students, activists, and artists. In spring 2016 they began to discuss the formation of a group to oppose the hegemonic structures of capitalist and neoliberal politics and economics in contemporary Albania. From these discussions, a group of street artists&mdash;individually anonymous but known collectively as &Ccedil;ETA&mdash;emerged. The group takes its name from the word used to describe the groups of antifascist guerilla fighters active in the Balkans during the Second World War, and its mission is to use street art as a weapon&mdash;however modest&mdash;in a broader struggle against neoliberal policies dominating Albanian universities, against the destruction of Tirana&rsquo;s few remaining green spaces, and in favor of free public transportation. Functioning as a true collective, the group is made up of members of various ages, with various backgrounds: designers, political scientists, artists, architects.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(68, 34, 'al', '<p>Pune &quot;R&euml;nja dhe rilindja&quot; lind nga nevoja p&euml;r t&euml; reflektuar mbi gjendjen e pun&euml;torit n&euml; Shqip&euml;ri, e cila n&euml; dekad&euml;n e fundit &euml;sht&euml; p&euml;rkeq&euml;suar deri n&euml; vdekje. Shum&euml; vdekje n&euml; vendin e pun&euml;s jan&euml; raportuar ve&ccedil;an&euml;risht nga pun&euml;tor&euml;t e nd&euml;rtimit, minator&euml;t ose punetoret e naft&euml;s. Keto raste vdekjeje mbeten shpesh t&euml; pazgjidhura e arsyet pas k&euml;saj mund t&euml; jen&euml; t&euml; shumta, por n&euml; fund t&euml; dit&euml;s siguria e vetme q&euml; ata pun&euml;tor&euml; kan&euml; n&euml; mjedisin e tyre t&euml; pun&euml;s &euml;sht&euml; frika dhe vdekja. &Ccedil;ETA p&euml;rdor vepr&euml;n &ldquo;Rr&euml;zimi i Krishtit&rdquo; nga Tintoretto-s si nj&euml; imazh simbolik p&euml;r k&euml;t&euml; situat&euml;, duke z&euml;vend&euml;suar figur&euml;n e Krishtit me at&euml; t&euml; nj&euml; pun&euml;tori nd&euml;rtimi. Ideja q&euml; q&euml;ndron pas nj&euml; z&euml;vend&euml;simi t&euml; till&euml; &euml;sht&euml; ajo e &ccedil;lirimit t&euml; pun&euml;torit nga frika dhe nga pronari, si e vetmja rrug&euml; drejt nj&euml; pune dinjitoze dhe ndoshta drejt nj&euml; &ldquo;rilindje&rdquo; jo vet&euml;m si pun&euml;tor, por edhe si qytetar dhe qenie njer&euml;zore e aft&euml; t&euml; g&euml;zoj&euml; t&euml; gjitha t&euml; drejtat e tij.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">&Ccedil;ETA&nbsp;&euml;sht&euml; nj&euml; kolektiv politik i artit rrugor i formuar nga student&euml;, aktivist&euml; dhe artist&euml;. N&euml; pranver&euml;n e 2016-&euml;s ata filluan t&euml; diskutojn&euml; formimin e nj&euml; grupi p&euml;r t&euml; kund&euml;rshtuar strukturat hegjemoniste t&euml; politik&euml;s dhe ekonomis&euml; kapitaliste dhe neoliberale n&euml; Shqip&euml;rin&euml; bashk&euml;kohore. Nga k&euml;to diskutime, doli nj&euml; grup artist&euml;sh t&euml; rrug&euml;s &ndash; individualisht anonim&euml;, por t&euml; njohur kolektivisht si &Ccedil;eta. Grupi e ka marr&euml; emrin nga fjala e p&euml;rdorur p&euml;r t&euml; p&euml;rshkruar grupet e luft&euml;tar&euml;ve antifashist&euml; guerile aktiv&euml; n&euml; Ballkan gjat&euml; Luft&euml;s s&euml; Dyt&euml; Bot&euml;rore dhe misioni i tij &euml;sht&euml; t&euml; p&euml;rdor&euml; artin e rrug&euml;s si nj&euml; arm&euml; - sado modest - n&euml; nj&euml; luft&euml; m&euml; t&euml; gjer&euml; kund&euml;r politikave neoliberale q&euml; dominojn&euml; Universitetet shqiptare, kund&euml;r shkat&euml;rrimit t&euml; pak hap&euml;sirave t&euml; gjelbra t&euml; mbetura t&euml; Tiran&euml;s dhe n&euml; favor t&euml; transportit publik falas. Duke funksionuar si nj&euml; kolektiv i v&euml;rtet&euml;, grupi p&euml;rb&euml;het nga an&euml;tar&euml; t&euml; moshave t&euml; ndryshme, me prejardhje t&euml; ndryshme: dezaijnera, politolog&euml;, artist&euml;, arkitekt&euml;.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(69, 35, 'en', '<p>The installation &quot;Paris Commune Revisited&quot; was created in Tirana in 2019 and features an image of resistance painted on cardboard boxes that are mounted on wooden constructions. Rena &amp; Vladan&rsquo;s aim was to create art objects that could be transformed into objects that have a use-value and to share them as a common good. They met up with different politically or socially engaged groups in Tirana and discussed with them whether these art objects could be of use in their struggles. Finally, the objects were taken over by a protest movement against the privatization of public space which tried to prevent the demolition of the National Theater in Tirana. On the last day of the exhibition, the objects were carried on a protest walk to the occupied theater where they were erected as a kind of barricade and served as a platform for the speeches of the activists. From then on, they became part of the life of the occupied theater and were used as a mise-en-sc&egrave;ne for protest events, plays, and concerts. When Tirana was shaken by a strong earthquake in November 2019, the boxes were used to distribute clothes and food to people who lost their homes. In May 2020, during the ban on assembly due to the pandemic, the National Theater was violently demolished by the government.<br />\r\nThe installation was developed as part of the &quot;Performative Exhibition #2. Komuna e Parisit Revisited&quot; at Tirana Art Lab.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Rena Raedle &amp; Vladan Jeremic are Belgrade-based artists whose research-oriented work comprises drawing and text, video, photography, installation, and intervention in public space. In their collaborative practice, Rena &amp; Vladan explore the relation between art and politics, unveiling the contradictions of today&rsquo;s societies and developing transformative potentials of art in the context of social struggles. They engage with current debates and struggles in collaboration with social movements and disseminate their artworks through reproduction in various media. They have recently exhibited at Brooklyn Museum, NY; 56th October Salon, Belgrade; Museum of Contemporary Art, Ljubljana; EKKM, Tallinn; District, Berlin; Autrostrada Biennale, Prizren; Politics of Dissonance in the framework of Manifesta 12, Palermo; MMOMA, Moscow; &lt; rotor &gt; within Steirischer Herbst, Graz; Galleria del Progetto, Politecnico di Milano, Milano; Intercultural Museum, Oslo and MoCA, Skopje.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL);
