(70, 35, 'al', '<p>Instalacioni &quot;Komuna e Parisit e Rivizituar&quot;&nbsp;u krijua n&euml; Tiran&euml; n&euml; vitin 2019 dhe paraqet nj&euml; pamje t&euml; rezistenc&euml;s t&euml; pikturuar n&euml; kuti kartoni q&euml; jan&euml; montuar n&euml; konstruksione druri. Q&euml;llimi i Rena &amp; Vladan ishte t&euml; krijonin objekte arti q&euml; mund t&euml; shnd&euml;rroheshin n&euml; objekte p&euml;rdorimi dhe ti ndanin ato me t&euml; tjer&euml;t si nj&euml; e mir&euml; e p&euml;rbashk&euml;t. Ata u takuan me grupe t&euml; ndryshme t&euml; angazhuara n&euml; sfer&euml;n politiko-shoq&euml;rore n&euml; Tiran&euml; dhe diskutuan me ta n&euml;se k&euml;to objekte arti mund t&euml; ishin t&euml; dobishme n&euml; &ccedil;&euml;shtjet e tyre. Si p&euml;rfundim, objektet u huazuan nga nj&euml; grup protestuesish kund&euml;r privatizimit t&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml;s publike i cili tentoi t&euml; parandalonte shembjen e Teatrit Komb&euml;tar n&euml; Tiran&euml;. N&euml; dit&euml;n e fundit t&euml; ekspozit&euml;s, objektet u transportuan n&euml; nj&euml; kortezh protestues deri tek Teatri ku u ngrit&euml;n si nj&euml; lloj barrikade dhe sh&euml;rbyen si platform&euml; p&euml;r fjalimet e aktivist&euml;ve. Q&euml; at&euml;her&euml;, ato u b&euml;n&euml; pjes&euml; e jet&euml;s s&euml; teatrit t&euml; mbrojtur nga artist&euml;t dhe u p&euml;rdor&euml;n si mise-en-sc&egrave;ne p&euml;r manifestime, protesta, shfaqje dhe koncerte. Kur Tirana u trondit nga nj&euml; t&euml;rmet i fort&euml; n&euml; n&euml;ntor 2019, kutit&euml; u p&euml;rdor&euml;n p&euml;r t&euml; shp&euml;rndar&euml; rroba dhe ushqime p&euml;r njer&euml;zit n&euml; nevoj&euml;. N&euml; maj 2020, gjat&euml; ndalimit t&euml; tubimeve p&euml;r shkak t&euml; pandemis&euml;, Teatri Komb&euml;tar u shemb me dhun&euml; nga qeveria. Instalacioni dhe nd&euml;rhyrja u zhvillua si pjes&euml; e &quot;Ekspozit&euml;s Performative #2 - Komuna e Parisit e Revisituar&quot; n&euml; Tirana Art Lab.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\">Rena Raedle dhe Vladan Jeremic jan&euml; artist&euml; q&euml; jetojn&euml; e punojn&euml; &nbsp;n&euml; Beograd, Serbi. Praktika dhe k&euml;rkimi i tyre artistik p&euml;rfshin vizatimin, tekstin, videon, fotografin&euml;, instalacionin dhe nd&euml;rhyrjen n&euml; hap&euml;sir&euml;n publike. N&euml; praktik&euml;n e tyre bashk&euml;punuese, Rena &amp; Vladan eksplorojn&euml; marr&euml;dh&euml;nien midis artit dhe politik&euml;s, duke zbuluar kontradiktat e shoq&euml;rive t&euml; sotme dhe duke zhvilluar potencialet transformuese t&euml; artit n&euml; kontekstin e betejave shoq&euml;rore. Ata angazhohen me debate dhe beteja aktuale n&euml; bashk&euml;punim me l&euml;vizje shoq&euml;rore dhe shp&euml;rndajn&euml; veprat e tyre t&euml; artit p&euml;rmes riprodhimit n&euml; media t&euml; ndryshme. S&euml; fundmi ata kan&euml; ekspozuar n&euml;: Brooklyn Museum, NY ; 56th October Salon, Beograd; Museum of Contemporary Art, Ljubljana; EKKM, Tallin; District, Berlin; Autrostrada Biennale, Prizren; Politics of Dissonance in the framework of Manifesta 12, Palermo; MMOMA, Moske; &lt; rotor &gt; within Steirischer Herbst, Graz; Galleria del Progetto, Politecnico di Milano, Milano; Intercultural Museum, Oslo and MoCA, Shkup.</p>', NULL, NULL),
(71, 36, 'en', '<p>Georgia Kotretsos, an artist, researcher, writer, activist, and institution runner embodies an example of a multifunctional contemporary artist, hopping from one role and engagement to the other and at the same time maintaining clear boundaries between them. In collaboration with Tirana Art Lab, Kotretsos developed three signs, which were placed at the main Boulevard in Tirana as part of the intervention. The totalitarian fascist and socialist regimes, but, above all, the neoliberal ones, have continuously used this privileged and semiotic charged space to disclose the &quot;theatre&quot; of self-promotion through art. The three signs metaphorically intervene in the landscape of the Boulevard questioning the relation between art and politics in different political regimes.<br />\r\nThis work was produced for the exhibition &ldquo; Triple Feature #5&rdquo; at Tirana Art Lab, as part of the collaboration project &ldquo; Heroes We Love&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"smallEditor\"><br />\r\nGeorgia Kotretsos born in 1978 in Thessaloniki, Greece is a visual artist and researcher based in Athens, Greece. She moved to South Africa in her early teens while the abolition of apartheid was underway. Kotretsos holds an MFA Degree from The School of the Art Institute of Chicago on a Full Merit Scholarship in 2004 in the United States and a BFA Degree from the Durban Institute of Technology, in KwaZulu Natal, in 2000 in South Africa. 